user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Big portion for the price and good to order a few dishes to share.  Good for friends gathering.  Love their scallops and beef carpaccio.
Local draft beer 🍺 must order","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXw1zecHQ23lGeRBHPjkfKQhwg4wkRaa4ZkaAV&fid=0x0:0x856c38bd76a2003f"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Jodine Morehouse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkI3ILmstAY-XeAWqv2CETEpjWiJVODW602jRpnYogrvfslqk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a wonderful experience tonight at The One Sixty. I’m so excited to have fine dining level food available in the tri-cities. The atmosphere is lovely and the service was great. The scallops were delicious, the bruschetta was packed with flavour and the braised beef just melted in your mouth. I highly recommend for a special night. I’m looking forward to coming back to try their brunch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnznTdpcizO1WRUBEefyByqjg7edAYscyY7Npj&fid=0x0:0x856c38bd76a2003f"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Lorie Biscuit","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3SaZMEozG_thkRie2w25mtZeGitWffDdS330nchcjzeVoj0Gc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came here for the first time for a brunch date and the vibes at this place are so chill, friendly and the place looked very elegant. The food was amazing their waffles are extremely crispy. They also have a real coffee machine not one of those instant ones so the lattes are amazing. The lady who made mine even did little bunny art in mine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXiQ2FVkzia9lseH7PpOGJeVqw6mq8yYaNRxVe&fid=0x0:0x856c38bd76a2003f"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Simon Hardy-Francis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUB8AdQYxUYJCAE_cHqFT87JPS7eQsmUoL3mGal92dnU64RGEWt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Finally had the chance to go here, but ended up disappointed in the end. Why? I guess it's because I entered hungry and unfortunately left hungry :-( The dinner menu was divided into smaller and larger dishes. I went for the larger pasta, but it ended up being the smallest pasta portion I've had in a long time. See photo. It probably about 4 or 5 fork fulls. I've seen other reviewers unhappy with their food portion size too.

My wife was happy with her tuna salad portion size though. I would have been too.

Other issues: We arrived about 4:40 PM and weren't sure if we just sit down ourselves or wait to be seated. We were given the happy hour menu, at first, and then they took it away, saying it's too late in the kitchen. Never experienced something like that in a restaurant before.

I don't think I will go again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZ-wC6IZ3ZTcRnq_JJRs_mKeXgt1wfwdd9LiIR&fid=0x0:0x856c38bd76a2003f"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Michael Tetrault","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUOblNGbdNZ4FfoMdwgRA-V8sixAEwnNyg7ZpUaoUxqov7wNyQphQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The One Sixty experience was both elegant and casual, where our party felt comfortable without getting too dressed up, but we're impressed with both the well-decorated dining area and the presentation and quality of the food. Whether it's a date night, hanging with a colleague after work, or just want to bring the family together, this place is worth checking out! Quality wine pairings and delicious appetizers rounded out our excellent dinner entrees.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3r9Pw2Qw2a3MFYf4EQTI9Vl4-LBxxyUNNzDfV&fid=0x0:0x856c38bd76a2003f"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Elsa K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLd8sh-s3bj5Jhs9_gPQsxuVZe4ZgkjQADi9C6BFijopOhbl73=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The One Sixty Wine Bar and Cafe offers a delightful culinary experience with its exquisite fries, delicious gnocchi, and generous portions. The fries are perfectly crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, making them an irresistible treat. Their gnocchi is cooked to perfection, with a melt-in-your-mouth texture and rich flavors that leave a lasting impression. What sets this restaurant apart is their commitment to serving sizable portions, ensuring that every diner leaves fully satisfied. Whether you're a fan of classic comfort food or gourmet delights, The One Sixty Wine Bar and Cafe delivers an unforgettable dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzBFAJVt_f7DIftGLKL65sEhCBlWNcM1979pzB&fid=0x0:0x856c38bd76a2003f"],"When":"2024-3-17"},{"Name":"Paulina Pedrero Miranda","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXoiOld2vaC2Dv18bWNi8EDRiykD7MSCRsU3RK7RESh6xQghXxb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"In general was ok, but i think that the experience could be better if the food is tastier, in general all was well ordered was fine nothing really amazing, we went for a brunch with friends, stay in the patio and the sun was intense, they only have 2 umbrellas in good conditions but both were occupied, the staff gave us one that was broken but fortunately it was enough, maybe brunch is not their forte, so maybe next time i’ll go for the wine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONugmowXjhT1q8E7vJFBebNwhjM1qcrc-tDRj0&fid=0x0:0x856c38bd76a2003f"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The bruschetta was amazing, but the additional price for the goat cheese was odd as it should have been included. $42 for the halibut entree and it was underwhelmingly small. The chocolate mousse was lovely. The latte seemed more like a cafe au lait so I assume it was a single shot drowning in milk.

I can appreciate if they are aspiring to fine dining - small portions with great flair and service. That’s where I think the let down was. Our appetizer plates were left on the table for at least ten minutes after we finished eating, and our entrees were placed on the table with the dirty dishes. I was asked if I wanted to keep my dirty cutlery, which was at this point on my appetizer plate in the server’s hand. I declined and asked for clean cutlery, and the server scooped a set off the table next to us. The attention to detail that their prices suggest just wasn’t there.

I’m glad we went, but I’m not sure we’ll be back. It’s a shame because I wanted to love it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM006Luhn5MngmiJMxAN6KzVd3fmh-LvGiAbZMs&fid=0x0:0x856c38bd76a2003f"],"When":"2024-5-10"}]

If you take beef, I think the short rib is the best.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNn6t4L--Y9YDNgfv_mxG3_Je57eMIORSut5iuf&fid=0x0:0xa546a8148ac1af76"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"E Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXSf46GoVDYA6DwVd9VW9_YDSbB2ZybZwD8Gjg5Qpn6bN0v14Wr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Not serving too many options here comparing to other Korean restaurants. But the focus pays off because their food are delicious! Staff were super nice and friendly, even when the place was busy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyceySv8Hb6l2E0NPWjggveBqDFxE7xIChwATo&fid=0x0:0xa546a8148ac1af76"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"A.J. Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I do love the stone bowl bibimbap, seafood pancake and Ox bone soup. The service is to be desired sometimes. But it is clean and organized. Great Port Moody neighborhood Korean food restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9asta18NSNe90oN67w2S9cLK4Je7lt3bUNDtF&fid=0x0:0xa546a8148ac1af76"],"When":"2024-2-23"},{"Name":"Erica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIUh3fEd3c7Qz7J80daKhFwS0w6Gog9YOVYUtlC7X3GBid9qw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Have been coming to this place for many years.  Solid spot for pork bone soup that is in walking distance from Port Moody station.  Before 7pm, the soup comes with hot stone rice.  🍚 Tip: to enjoy hot stone rice, scoop out the rice into another bowl (don’t touch the stone pot directly as its very hot!), and pour a little bit of the room temperature water (not too much) just to cover the remaining grains (nurungji - toasted rice grains) that are stuck to the bottom of the stone pot and cover with the lid.  Check on it cause sometimes the water fizzes up. After a few minutes, or at the end of your meal mix and enjoy.

탕, 냉면 유명한 탕집이에요
감자탕을 먹었는데 7pm전에 돌솥밥도 나와서 좋아요. 포트 무디 역에서 걸어서 11분 정도 거리예요","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmttkJu5QINMekvgptXW5Sr6je7_lYsByqGXeD&fid=0x0:0xa546a8148ac1af76"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"Joey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJl9szXFCvkqiDIj8ffgxhpU02VBcZUaH8smB2SMyI4TIXdsaA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It serves traditional Korean foods, like pork bone soup and cold noodles. The pork bone soup is a must-try, other dishes are also yummy. Friendly staff and cozy ambiance make it a good choice for Korean cuisine enthusiasts.(hope it will serve jajangmyeon someday","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0YLaIzQGOvqYPeP8arLMZZeGy5KQ9poDoykkj&fid=0x0:0xa546a8148ac1af76"],"When":"2023-9-17"},{"Name":"Carla Cabrera","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyAMgtnaFupCyPAv17OwvwftYUJ_kVL13H0OIF7_nMrISRiNQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Definitely good corean food! Special highlight for the pork cutlet and seafood pancake, both were incredibly delicious. The menu does not have a big list of options but are enough to not get lost, I prefer that way. Affordable prices compare to downtown Vancouver. Service was fast and accurate. It is one of those places that does not look fancy but has the most important thing what matters in a restaurant which is great food. I would love to go back to explore other options in the menu even though the commute is really far from my home, probably next year during a more shiny and warm season like spring or summer so I can try the cold noodles.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUnfErdTZeFaGqvAnCIl1qs0BabDghSFdVcjul&fid=0x0:0xa546a8148ac1af76"],"When":"2023-12-23"},{"Name":"Y L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV236YiWDAw91lf0BivhX8vPLApY6lFjId9AQG1MMNy3GQCimu9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really good korean food. I had high expectations. It wasn't up to the hype but it was still good. The pork cutlet sauce was little bland.  The pork bone soup is delicious. The kimchi's were delicious. Very good pricing point. Friendly service as well. I would like to visit again and try other things on their menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsh08nIhM0Kk_tgI5IzJsAoSTiRy50UnB-J0xP&fid=0x0:0xa546a8148ac1af76"],"When":"2023-3-28"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Luckily I beat the lunch rush (Came here around 11:50am)
Got sat right away and food came out fast!
Their Pork Cutlet was fantastic, especially with their house made sauce!
Definitely coming back for more!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTRbJtZmKjCs2KqOuXr0NTVZIPeDnJfINDdylK&fid=0x0:0xa546a8148ac1af76"],"When":"2022-10-16"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Daisy Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVu1nxOTin_LouqpMg8SuZhcgesKimL_02BtAAmRSIlR4zjoDPR2g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"You have to reserve and order ahead of time at Henry's. The menu is constantly changing. It seems like chef likes to try different things constantly but the trade-off is that there is a lack of consistency. A dessert that you like last time might not taste the same the next. There is a lot of care put into the food and service of this restaurant run by a sweet couple.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-q6zJivd1CL2zzFfrr1DchcwIVKvsH_EDj7mi&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2023-5-31"},{"Name":"B W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJp85P5JohieEKJOfTMzyjH1aTNit_eIhBL3dFVyxf0xS2BxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Missus and I have driven by Henry's Kitchen many times on St. Johns Street and always wanted to try. We were happy we finally did.

Jasmine provided exceptional table service and tended to our needs. She has a very friendly demeanor and we had a nice chat. The food is freshly made after you arrive. One could taste the high quality of the food preparation. We thoroughly enjoyed our Caesar Salad, Crab Cake, Linguine Pescatora, German Pork Knuckle, Tiramisu and Chocolate Ganache. The homemade bread was a good way to start of our meal.

The restaurant has limited hours. Reservations are required as well as preordering your meal to avoid food waste. There is plenty of parking in the area.

We would highly recommend for a nice evening dinner.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSdv88ZgQm9qtGBG1FxL08P4IFiM_SDP2nj4pO&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2024-1-21"},{"Name":"P L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdkQ26g4o3dvVCWU9ihtXPpJaS5QpzFy1cxMTo4qJB3Lj-Rw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Exceptional service and food. From reservation to dining in, Jasmine was extraordinarily efficient with communication and  excellent with her service even decorating our table with a happy birthday sign and confetti! She was extremely attentive and made my party which included a toddler feel welcomed and comfortable. All servers should learn from her. She was so kind and caring to my toddler even when he was running around. The food by Henry was all beautifully presented and delicious with different elements of texture and flavour and perfection in terms of doneness of our meats. We look forward to more celebrations at this gem of a restaurant!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ali Pourhadi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2iXVISnnHvJyKbaIf5Y2ya0kPji3HgqAXHVvDJ4VAf-MjLkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If possible, I would give 10 stars. I made a reservation at Henry’s kitchen for our anniversary. They had arranged a very beautiful table for us. Food and desserts could not be better. Great service and a nice ambiance","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMANAae1CWeLWOflBXXLBrT4NNuvOGXroeyrU06&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Cora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9YQmsmKhqCSvMVPAZKT18eImIWQ2QjEOLJi24FjTkNMSIg53C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Henry's Kitchen is back open for dine in! Make sure you make a reservation via email with your preorders because that's the only way to get in! Everything was cooked perfectly and large portions for French cuisine! We had the duck breast, beef wellington as mains. Escargot and house made bread as starters. I highly recommend the duck! I'm so glad they're back open for dining in as ordering to go just wasn't the same. We will for sure be back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMDWuLgZexqbvRkmEGWeWCxqaoHBDFeJxMiTR0&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2022-4-5"},{"Name":"Dan Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWn20SO-hez6CdOPY0et6YJIfsXqZVK2JjuFROy8lc6ciazjVwLCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our group reserved a table here, we also pre ordered few days in advance. Food doesn't get prepared till everyone in your group arrives. The food was amazing! Presentation was good and the taste was good. Service was amazing. Desserts were great too. Nice cozy little place with nice interior. Parking is around but may be tough depending on what time you go. I highly recommend this place! Thank you Henry's Kitchen!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMBQPTpY9z9iVFVEqgOq7HvWAYBv54mYL1lVVE9&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2018-11-12"},{"Name":"Dave Cameron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhpdoAj31MMy3I4viRnxDZTmsnr5-27AbISuaFHBaKYcNQJ78n=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In a world of Cactus Clubs and Earls' restaurants like this are sorely missed. It is not the best food to be found in Metro Vancouver, but it is very good and a good value for money. Service is outstanding.

The concept is very interesting, instead of spending 10 mins pouring over a menu; pre-ordering like this makes dinner all about dinner. Also nice to be eating freshly prepared food rather than something made yesterday and warmed up in a microwave or stovetop.

I really like the atmosphere, self-decorated rather than the usual restaurant ikea furniture. Pictures and drawings from the past instead of a TV showing yesterday's sports highlights. Place is about the food and about the dinner.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Justin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVslDT3IjpBSLKbUfPD64hmIByw3PZ3A7YKnhNaaweMTcLb-EE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for dinner with my friends. Everything that we had was very tasty and fresh with rich flavours. I got the Lobster Taglierine which was stunning and my friend got the beef wellington which was perfectly done. The the service is excellent. Highly recommend and its important to make a reservation in advanced if you want to go and we ordered in advanced too. Will be back soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdkQW2M3YNy_2--tuQGG4c4L8rHzntwTiqtUrP&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2018-9-22"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Nicholas Sperling","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqkJbnJpe916U8AIcQSHFScMMCPJK87tF8E1CagYxQYLBMEBgS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The beer is great, but honestly, I come here for the Detroit-style pizza. It’s consistent, delicious, and filling. The dough is fluffy and flavorful, and their pizzas are loaded with toppings. The sauce is simple and delicious, and the ranch dip is some of the best I have ever had. Worth the money, in my opinion. The 80's/90's theme is fun, and the decor is spot on.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEBC7tcXDhnoAORy-cE7smaCyMOFa3oGKqbiZ8&fid=0x0:0x14d9ccae103befd"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Louis R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrYe-7QfP2vfwc7xOUKf0c065DMsoA3l4BelIB85bdV1lyQpM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I often cycle from Vancouver to Port Moody, and Rewind Beer Co. has quickly become my favorite stop. The beer is fantastic with a great selection, and the atmosphere is welcoming and relaxed—a perfect spot to unwind after a long ride.

But what really sets Rewind apart is the pizza. It’s simply outstanding—super tasty, perfectly cooked, and a must-try if you’re in the area. Honestly, it’s some of the best pizza I’ve had, and it pairs perfectly with their beer.

If you’re in Port Moody, Rewind Beer Co. should definitely be on your list. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWbHtqfzp6Py_DQe8OlwKwxfzA77Bwv_BLKujx&fid=0x0:0x14d9ccae103befd"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Bekah French","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiYLh-7emQ9AthzE2N_CGxwmtRUdZguPeMRuVIWmhyOtllxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time here last night. Had a great time, super happy they had an in-house pizza kitchen. Pizza was delicious, they even have vegan cheese (but I opted no cheese on my half). The beers were very tasty too. Hubby got the IPA and I always go for the sour. Staff were very friendly and atmosphere is very retro. We will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtXXQa6U2Mr7AY_oFvUmIaTVQrNWJkKcB6rGwi&fid=0x0:0x14d9ccae103befd"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Brittany","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHTcuSM-4ly1uIP3q2-jgQ_2Vqi7GhBmGO9JykCcOlnN1NYOmqYg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Don’t let the decor fool you, it’s not just a gimmick - Rewind is the cutest and most delicious brewery on the row.

The Chicago style pizza is seriously amazing and well priced. We were pleasantly surprised at the vegetarian options, the special was the “Light Brite” a crispy pie with loads of garlic, fresh basil, roasted baby broccolini, mozz, cherry tomatoes, pesto and balsamic. The beer is also tasty with some unique flavor profiles, though for me, it plays second flute to the food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_kXmGzaKUA-iGQ5hwFaoOUCrFLFBp9KPj4o-A&fid=0x0:0x14d9ccae103befd"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Mark Tollins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLjv4dKPwFD6u9eCYsYJBewc3m1w_Gzjw_8E3VI2nUw60luHQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The beer is okay, the pizza is delicious and very filling. Fun decor. It is pretty small (especially without a patio in winter months) so it can be hard to get a table if you come in with a larger group.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9_ioYYeZmkOeaGocaKEh-RdIM1e_2bbRp3p_G&fid=0x0:0x14d9ccae103befd"],"When":"2024-11-26"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's like stepping into a sunny blast from the past. If that past resonates with you, you're in for a treat! Port Moody's Brewers Row is one of those places where every brewery has its moment, and Rewind screams summer with its laid-back vibe and light, breezy beers perfect for those blazing hot days. While I've yet to dive into their food menu, the buzz around their pizza is getting hard to ignore, so we'll need to check it out soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1LMBtUnPpc2b1KQiLqYoZuDsOs3SaAy_Czl0U&fid=0x0:0x14d9ccae103befd"],"When":"2024-7-2"},{"Name":"H S Madan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTu4oMkDk1Z3MjNV_7rONLy371tsTTJL-xX0jcQ-rhkA8blIkVlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went in for a few drinks and had some food also. They have a great retro vibe to the brewery, very friendly staff. The pizza is very good and usually sells out. So if you want to try it order as soon as you arrive. They do tend to get very busy so budget your time will or just hop into another brewery for a few min and then come back. They also have cockfields on tap but they are once again. Also very sweet. This place has a great atmosphere and really good music. Definitely a place where you can have a few drinks and lose track of time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOg6dDn7XfBQXfNHP1KRHwQQI2R3OhLk9cuoBk1&fid=0x0:0x14d9ccae103befd"],"When":"2024-4-16"},{"Name":"Kelly I","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXquEahqi64vPbCeET717zYpgegwA8i3NW9-l7MkI7Qwpb7QLT5Sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Quite a happening scene of microbreweries by Rocky point. We liked the polka king pizza. @$24 per pie. Crispy pan pizza. The bacon could have been more generous, all in all a tasty pizza. Cool decor with 90s movie theme.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiFpjLBwr-eSt_9U35rCxWCaiK3uPGaeEo9vO9&fid=0x0:0x14d9ccae103befd"],"When":"2024-2-20"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Natthan Plessis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIi5OO8qdZSERfycP491FJEZGbUdddqyZOJRleSFIuej8I50Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Overall, great atmosphere and service. The bartenders and servers are constantly working hard and pushing out drinks to make sure the customers are satisfied. Overall, for how hard they work and their service to get the drink out to you asap, you should be Tipping 20% always... plus, they are not just sending out poor drinks they are making sure the drinks are well mixed for the perfect cocktail. user_reviews: [{"Name":"Champagne Kingdom","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT9L6nbhgKeVF6uvC80gh6he8ZgVExYxBb0bRQFJovbeiruBo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had an amazing experience here! We stopped by on Saturday to enjoy the patio and savor some delicious beers - the Mexican cerveza and sours were our favorites! We also ordered mouth-watering brisket from the food truck. We loved it so much that we came back the next day (Sunday) for their breakfast special, which was not only delicious but also a steal at just $8! We highly recommend this place!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfEk-c1QAmpyXpVqdrVvl9WAKt2iFj3uzEE9WI\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Meagan O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsIpETfJCnO9swLQBZUTKHiE8RdzaCfMqoS1jEt2QgcgkZNi0L_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We hosted a reception for a funeral at Trainwreck Brewery. My beloved mother in law loved pubs and live music so this was the perfect venue. The owner Chris was an absolute gem to deal with and was more than willing to let us use the space as we wanted to with decor, a mix of food that we brought with food available at the brewery and a beer cheers to my mother in law. Anna and Max were our servers and were absolutely wonderful and so attentive. Mike on the Mic played some renditions of classic rock that my mother in law would have adored. Looking forward to visiting again on a happier occasion.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkXKOhLdL3MGDe_p4AhYEL6Mblp9v4_bRaEwqz\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Ruby E.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTXhvN-EpNac4Qr_mgdf5IDJLY8uKSuinXxuVkhfUtlVyIdrlu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for the flight of sours ($9) - a great way to sample a variety of brews.  Also tried a couple of the meads, which aren't available less than 12 oz so you can't sample those in a flight but both the Orange Saffron mead and Lingonberry-Elderberry were delicious!  We happened to be there for the live music and the guys performing on Nov.1 were very talented and provided great ambience.  Best to reserve a table in advance for your friend group. For hot food, you can order burgers, poutine, Mac \u0026 cheese from the on-site food truck, but i recommend eating at Sushi Modo or Karumba across the street instead.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoNQKV3pgdoxqg10PinoLS5tfdkIJJH4yjRr85\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"ANTONIO TOTAN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKCtjigHEHqTcQK9K0HpS0C6AQPHd5Ae_UDjB1Vt_RFtE3Lrg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I celebrated my birthday at Train Wreck Brewing and it was an extraordinary experience! The atmosphere was perfect, the staff was very kind and attentive, and the food and drinks were excellent. All my guests had a great time, and the music and decor complemented the evening perfectly. Thank you to the team for an unforgettable birthday! I highly recommend it!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"A.J. Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Train Wreck brewery in Port Moody is spacious and has a good beer, cider and mead selection.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFMSPDPKxPVuV3eUqO4TA56VugToIT5JGvhSlL\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"H S Madan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTu4oMkDk1Z3MjNV_7rONLy371tsTTJL-xX0jcQ-rhkA8blIkVlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stopped by to have a few drinks. They have a very large selection of drafts on tap. At the present time there is nothing that you can buy and take home. But the server said it will happen soon. I also ordered some cocktails on tap. They were extremely sweet and not very strong so if that is something that you look for the new would definitely enjoy it. Personally for my taste it was way too sweet. They do have a barbecue truck outside that you can order food from. We ordered two poutines and the poutines were really good. This is a very nice place to hang out. They have an large outdoor patio and a large indoor seating area. The servers are very friendly. The patio that is up front is right on the street so you do get a lot of Street noise. But you are in the Sun.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkBI3MZpIjEPBjne5BJ5sSz1o4QNvZ_nN98esD\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-4-16"},{"Name":"DJ Robichaud","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUpMQna8Vc_nXWe_E4gkarRFa-7vGEALVmsnGeLEYoQVG4M4q4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The live music they had was so warm and entertaining, and the staff and I were not stop laughing and enjoying each others company. I am not an avid drinker but they have the best craft cream soda I have ever had! It is a must try!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFjGzci_I2jfYDZ-1ERLp22KCkjJgFyhLNVtru\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-2-19"},{"Name":"Mohammad Ghorbani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLhM08Ep2NCTojfd1QxmX4qnCTzzQfI85j3VW30xREciyNrcn6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I finally found one of the best breweries in Canada! They serve an excellent hefeweizen that could easily make them one of the top breweries around. Any Bavarian missing a good hefeweizen should definitely come here and give it a try. They’ve also been recognized for their British pale ale, which is outstanding.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnXDKkTETrmKC-lqIhQMKRCRZEZnpQpihjHbkr\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-11-14"}]

Ordered a lot and had to take some left, home.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1kxObDA58HiLw-vboZnzgwGt3PvPxh7kDpBHB&fid=0x0:0xe61d2e311efae220"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Nevaeh Ann Wilbur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJKvH9cDErkLNX5twcLaE24s59R5L_MNQM5VNrk4waSRJOmqA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Honestly, if you are in the area, this is the absolute spot! The staff is amazing, and so, so sweet.

I went here with my family in between one of my family members’ hockey games. Currently I’m sitting here writing this in awe of the amazing food, service and atmosphere. I would go back if in the neighborhood.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODp8D6zPTvOVdVLCNzbiaCnL8saEvj4lFhk0sG&fid=0x0:0xe61d2e311efae220"],"When":"2024-5-28"},{"Name":"j liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCg9VgNWqVOZVSRe2o79EF4lui3FP4P9Y0V7-6LlpYMqk_LQ_G=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"the atmosphere is so cozy and warm, every single piece of furniture is so carefully articulated and suited for the customer. we ordered the viper roll, lobster roll, leo roll, soba noodles, and sashimi. the sashimi was so rich and melts in your mouth and the presentation of the dishes were stunning. the servers are nice and frequently checked up on us. even the washrooms are clean and nice. overall, this restaurant is amazing and i would recommend eating here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwoKJ-JdSM_qWfdrryU6tVh1VrqLk7hmZvpJgx&fid=0x0:0xe61d2e311efae220"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Mohammad Kharaji","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLrVWCBB5Rm2Neq1hybyR8pCivXxISYSj0hHwceZrAdh62x=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am a regular customer at Murasaki Restaurant. [{"Name":"Alina Medvedeva","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUD6ECfsC55wutar5cz1KkGoddnBUcS3JF5eEAgas1YddOUWeHaXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a fantastic experience at Sabor A Mexico! The food was absolutely delicious, fajitas and nachos 🔥. Nice options for the kids. The staff was friendly, attentive, and made sure we had everything we needed. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCMJYj4YtEG7hGtimtNyp_vDdDwY76VIVxevMv&fid=0x0:0xa7058c9abc9572bf"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Alexia Sarvan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVc6JDa1yYfq0nUgWFW8ECuapxVZ66hckQHzZsZmHnjPE9Lhhnx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had dinner at Sabor A Mexico for the first time with a friend last week and had an excellent experience! The restaurant is small so I made a reservation for that night. Service was great and all employees were very friendly. The music was great. My tacos (carnitas, pastor and chilorio) were delicious as well as my spicy margarita. Will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsXGR7l3CzDv1GXMYyJ69xwJViU23JxZ_9zZz6&fid=0x0:0xa7058c9abc9572bf"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Celeste BB","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJsW8oOi_oc28H1wHHfNLrSam7bOOC47E_fadEuhGUrDLkNAws=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Having some Mexican background, I am always curious to try Mexican restaurants to see where is the most authentic / closest in taste and ability to what I am used to.

The service was very good. Originally a bit of a wait since we didn’t have a reservation, but the host walked out 5 minutes later and knocked on our car door in the rain to let us know they had a cancellation and could seat us right away. Our server was very attentive, though it did start to feel like we were rushed (maybe they had other reservations coming in and didn’t want us to overstay).

We ordered the Spicy Margarita and the Mexican Mule to start since the drink reviews were strong. Was very nice to see the tequila options were good and they weren’t just using Sauza. We both asked for Maestro Dobel tequila with our drinks and they didn’t disappoint.

We started with chips and salsa because I always measure quality and authenticity based on the quality of the in-house salsa. The flavour was okay, but likely would be better if it had sat for a bit to allow the flavours to seep throughout. Most of the chips were stale, which didn’t help.

Then tried the queso fundido which was disappointing. Seemed to be mozzarella cheese with no added flavour and ok chorizo.

Then we shared the enchiladas with salsa verde. The shredded chicken lacked flavour and there was feta cheese on top (Greek cheese, not Mexican).

To anyone else’s standards this would be good quality, however I readily admit my standards are high. The best Mexican food I have found so far in BC is 4 hours away. I will continue to search the lower mainland, but would definitely return here for drinks!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP56Fe1o2wI0wG1gERPSfs_C9uK4ACw3P8kFDcy&fid=0x0:0xa7058c9abc9572bf"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Jessica Laug","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBe8Xx5xxN7BsOtdNIPEwa5FovlhSe5vAzpwuJr6-pkVqmPN4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went to this place on a whim. My mother is Mexican and has always made the best Mexican in my opinion. It's almost Christmas and growing up that meant Chile relleno , tamales and caldo. My Abuelo used to make the best Chile relleno and I've been really missing him lately.  He passed a few years ago. I saw it on the menu and had to try. Obviously it was different than my Abuelos. But it was damn good. The frijoles and arroz were the best I've had in a long time. The queso fresco on the frijoles 🤌🤌muy bueno. Instantly brought memories back. The presentation of the food was great. My friend had the carnitas platter. 10/10. It was 100% the real deal. I loved everything.  We will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOy_3lTmpU5mUHFQuJRJrc0WxpxzXRRzey6sWlJ&fid=0x0:0xa7058c9abc9572bf"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Mronissopwnage","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLCd89cujCDFfhK27cKjCCtJrv2dWwb5yxMmbDOl2pDd9DasK8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sabor a Mexico may truly be the best Mexican food ever. Source? Well I ate there 😅 The service is amazing and this is a family run restaurant with extremely authentic and fresh ingredients. We had the queso fundido to start and it was nothing short of amazing. I had the Carne Asada plate and everything was beyond delicious. We tried all 3 salsas and I bought the jar of the medium heat one to take home. I’m telling you COME EAT here. Do it now.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBGMcQJMrWH99SEu9bldtooPJ8EGuR7j9woa-t&fid=0x0:0xa7058c9abc9572bf"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Shion “Via”","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXejIlLvv5gNfGeBDQsdulH5uAqY5ozP3QD3jCfP-HXInhFPKVf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Me and a friend from Honduras went here together, and the food was amazing. He said it was quite authentic tasting. The quality of the meat was amazing. However, the prices compared to portion sizes just can't be justified, for 2 dishes, and 1 drink it was over $60 before tip.
It really comes down to how much you want to pay for good quality and authentic tasting Mexican food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPeRjMzQrr_Dik91kZ7FnlFCY8-xddkyC2cek0P&fid=0x0:0xa7058c9abc9572bf"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Jennifer Kleinsteuber","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWSdJKAEAGQkrdxmBZy-xMdSQn4mnDTUWZ_qKjGvjulVXF1Qm-zpg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Found a little jem in the heart of Port Moody. The food was amazing!!! So many flavors 😋
Servers were delightful and the meal arrived quickly. A treasure of a place ✨️
Thank you dinner ❤️💟💞💘❤️‍🔥","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSMi6_MUC3TxredQkTCNi4uZT3CxKZqaijvPEY&fid=0x0:0xa7058c9abc9572bf"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Denis Santos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXF32K7mKkPkKCpGUSEjmRXhqYloH84bwlSW6sQJ_X-vjOnAtXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We visited Sabor A Mexico for the first time, and without a reservation, so we had to wait about 30 minutes for a table, so be aware to make a reservation before, as the place is quite small.

The food we ordered was delicious, especially the burrito, one of the best I ever had. The chicken enchilada was amazing as well, however, the chicken inside was a bit cold. They ended up forgetting to bring our appetizer, which I really wanted to try. But I do understand they were busy and these things can happen, so not a big deal.

The churros with ice cream at the end of the meal was fantastic and left us with a good impression.

Overall, despite a few hiccups for a our first experience, I can say Sabor A Mexico offers a delicious authentic Mexican food and we will be coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSVkM9338yfbqQZoEwPrEc1CUj0FBn04hs3JVe&fid=0x0:0xa7058c9abc9572bf"],"When":"2024-6-11"}]

[{"Name":"Naveen Sivasankar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVD85c8-gPz6lah-8hC6Wc52PIW1l9gF6x2wQmy27iEI7TaAflN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This restaurant offers a large selection of Asian dishes at a reasonable price! I would recommend trying this place.

It was quite a trek to get here from Vancouver, but it was made easier by its proximity to a SkyTrain station. The restaurant itself is fairly plain but has some decorations and signage that add character.

Service was good but not exceptional, and I had no complaints. My order was taken promptly and the food arrived after an acceptable amount of time. Finally, I was able to pay once I asked for a bill and I left without much delay.

The food itself was delicious! I was concerned about the quality before visiting since I had doubts about the restaurant's ability to make so many different dishes, but I was soon proven wrong. The flavours were rich and the portions were large, so it was a challenge to finish it all.

Although it's not the fanciest location, it's definitely worth trying and I recommend this to anyone looking for a restaurant that can showcase the flavours of Asia!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOoJa6-6H2OZX-fJFbupITE6G2UjmCytTCROUn-&fid=0x0:0x6dc6d277978a22d7"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"Ruby E.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTXhvN-EpNac4Qr_mgdf5IDJLY8uKSuinXxuVkhfUtlVyIdrlu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Finally got a chance to check out their Asian cuisine and was really impressed with the quick service and delicious dishes.  Started with chicken wings and roti.  When I asked for an alternate dipping sauce for the roti, I was offered a side of dahl which was delicious! We also had the chicken wings, Sri Lankan noodles with chicken, and the Mongolian beef on crispy noodles.  Plan to share the entree with 2-3 others as the portions are very generous. Take out containers were offered for the leftovers. Our server has been working there for years and reports a lot of repeat customers.  We'll be returning as well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFgmLCZ4lKWv7bo54_OlriK7LfNmmrbjE6yQa5&fid=0x0:0x6dc6d277978a22d7"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Nick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGjptqH3FdoeLfdSjPWQygL5KEsM_ui4pClg77BekGUD0E-Q_8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Surprise the heck out of us. The Sri Lankan food that we ordered was top-notch. I would recommend this restaurant. Service was pretty fast and we didn't have to wait too long to get our food. Spice level was exactly how we like it. Portion sizes are decent on rates are not too crazy. It's a good place for any spicy food lover.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrq6rk3y3EijjVvx94RllL0dJAZzTyb32tUYfA&fid=0x0:0x6dc6d277978a22d7"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Chanelle D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCEGtGi_rnAXcez2UGfi8tPvkrtnC3uoCyaDz_NpX-tJAfWp2A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great selection of Asian and western food. Pretty affordable. Service was good. What I liked about the dishes: good portion size for sharing. You can feed 4 people with average appetite on 3 dishes family style (sharing dishes). Overall good value. What I didn't like about the dishes: I wasn't totally impressed by the flavour and taste. Perhaps it was because of the dishes we selected but generally we all felt 2 of the 3 dishes didn't quite hit the mark. On a positive note, there was ample parking and service was good. We did have to wait a while to get the bill - I mean over 30 minutes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwh_3fVT390H46Xr3O8KONPTIGyh-2v7EDV9XH&fid=0x0:0x6dc6d277978a22d7"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"James Pak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDGXkcLNvZrxRl-5qs3T2guPldawPqXL6Frf4RrCaW8N0E6q8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Currently little known, this restaurant is a hidden gem. Richard creates authentic South East Asian dishes. A little spicy for the average palate but taste is amazing. very reasonably priced menu offerings and fast friendly service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMi2CnoT_fMab_noq-C6A4QpME8422JCp871yj&fid=0x0:0x6dc6d277978a22d7"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"G Az (Joey)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9vWQ_Z44zr2y2Axw1PJrCvSjNgoFBEHJ_rrMAAvf0-82-kOK5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My Second time at this place as my 1st time with the Mrs was a hit. This time we bought our (under 10yrs)  kids. They loved it! Great food, pricing is competitive and owner is lovely, making sure you are satisfied with his cooking. We definitely like this place over other big name places like ChongQing. Even the kids ageed their chowmain tastes better. Dine in for the best experience, get some desert. They do take out too. No food delivery services though.  The drive over is worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNw-h28gQFea0Yc0yzeK8s5uN3gulQpuWmJQzvA&fid=0x0:0x6dc6d277978a22d7"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Michelle ROQUE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVD5Ft2yZYkozXs1swLhpIu0nnpqHjqQIX3ls8oMAIBKwcM8hbs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Five star for Nathaniel, Hazel & Sujwani’s service and five star for their chef who prepared our food!!! So delicious!
Prices are reasonable too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjr3mMGfKXpK1OU7c87uLUxZliBghUKwZVE8C5&fid=0x0:0x6dc6d277978a22d7"],"When":"2024-6-29"},{"Name":"Shreya Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXYyfchREZOt93jrLr4kvvBwB1jTepyfM6oQu2MU6JoB-ykQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Warm and cozy restaurant with super hospitable staff and authentic food. We tried the Sri Lankan fish, Mee Goreng, chicken chow mein, hot and sour soup and spring rolls. Everything tasted great and our host did not skip the spices!! Also appreciate that we could talk to each other and there was no music playing in the background. Will definitely come back to try more food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnRdP3AMe9sLJu8Ath0viPzmTwzU_eZaqRG6GA&fid=0x0:0x6dc6d277978a22d7"],"When":"2024-8-27"}]

[{"Name":"Madison G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtZsEld-Yz5a2Swm5LesjF83lo03ZXPGgujeQvQiLn6WLaIuGx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I recently stopped by here with my friend for dinner a few nights ago. We were so excited to try it out due to their high ratings online. The atmosphere and set up I found was super cute and a great addition to the take out food.

First thing we noticed was that even though we were the only ones there , it took them over 25 mins to prepare our burgers and fries. I ordered the bacon and Brie burger and the bacon was very tough to chew. I had to take it out of the burger completely. My friend ordered the Smokey bbq glaze burger. But I wouldn’t say it had any “Smokey”ness to it. Aswell our burger patties were dry and had zero taste. We were a little disappointed about both burgers ..it just didn’t seem very fresh or flavourful. Their signature sauce was very tasty though , and was a nice touch to both burgers.
We also ordered truffle fries which was probably the most disappointing. It barely had any cheese ( see photo below ) was cold, and barely had any truffle taste to it. For 12$ I would say it is absolutely not worth buying.

The service from the staff was great though, they were very nice and friendly.

One other thing which we thought was strange. They have these beautiful black take out bags. And we noticed a “scan for a surprise “ on the bag. Once scanned all it did was take us to their website to read more about them aha. Which is fine .. but we weren’t sure how much of a surprise that was. Was a bit misleading. Maybe it should say “ scan for more info about us “ instead. Just a thought.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_IFDgQ_JGQn9NsvEfPyyJ9Ky92Je5qdN_FTti&fid=0x0:0xca7f3f9b84c47ade"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Brian Bortolin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKbhq0GNavbT8429FkErVkTqQcAimBuCcEuu2JQyCOtAFPgDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nestled next to Rocky Point Park and right on Brewery Road, Blaze Gourmet Burgers is a burger lover's paradise!

The **classic burger** is to die for – seriously, I had to pinch myself to make sure I hadn't gone to burger heaven. Juicy, flavorful beef topped with the freshest ingredients, all tucked into a perfectly toasted bun. And let's talk about the **truffle fries**. These aren't just any fries – these are crispy-on-the-outside, soft-and-juicy-on-the-inside fries that taste like they've been kissed by a culinary angel. The oil they use is a mystery, but who needs Sherlock Holmes when you can just enjoy the best fries you've ever tasted?

If you find yourself near Rocky Point Park, do yourself a favor and swing by Blaze Gourmet Burgers for a meal that’s truly out of this world!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNflkiUqYE0tnYMtZr9OrS5gaH_gvWZ7hhonkOG&fid=0x0:0xca7f3f9b84c47ade"],"When":"2024-11-5"},{"Name":"Ricardo Reimão","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwZCbz-2kJAkR8bZlCUN9otwbedxrhMfiUKWwJAk8nmIXtmg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Outstanding burger and friendly service! The bacon and brie burger is absolutely delicious, specially with the grilled onions. The prices are reasonable and the fries are super fresh.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzgxhxmoLA1FZyppANWGfpg6wD4bkBb0Q8VOFT&fid=0x0:0xca7f3f9b84c47ade"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Kim Lishman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWoLip5cDVmyG9tqCTLI4iijakhf4W2VYZg3aEWyBWtOfnKc61HDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome spot with delicious burgers and curly fries. We had the BBQ burger combo which was divine and the fries were perfect. I also had the pumpkin cheesecake for dessert which was super tasty. This is the perfect spot to pick up takeaway for us and we will definitely be ordering again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMOvzFj2BsYP7rLrrT79vSaVDZnd19Zpr36wzp&fid=0x0:0xca7f3f9b84c47ade"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"30ishere","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxlQHdkaU0mIo0MOpMWZ5u-mgYOBPFxYPqwccBUz98Z30r0Bij=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best burgers and experiences we have in the area. Their burgers are so juicy, the chicken patty is moist and their curly fries are so crispy","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOb3Z3HhU40iP-fxRPSkkgi9TaMFtAh09pCC0RP&fid=0x0:0xca7f3f9b84c47ade"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Paulo Guedes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1w9iyRpc43PkW79-66dCb4m7AZ2R_uxaLNTUBYTVb0ZT7dAql=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Staff are very friendly and the burgers are high quality. The place is busy but it's worth the wait. Points for the curly seasoned fries.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNW0CNlQY2op-xIEwMfw0-o4dDxYY7hGHotpfIA&fid=0x0:0xca7f3f9b84c47ade"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Yagmur Nizam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwf2IbQ8vwH9f8TlCxksYnlgKDnU8o7pg68HA31DaZMMoxkw4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We tried Blaze’s truck burgers yesterday, and they were absolutely delicious! Both the classic and BBQ burgers were amazing. The chef who prepared them was not only skilled but also very helpful. [{"Name":"Yoshiko C.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKtcsZOlyd8taDwX9F7EkmkehI4-UW_WG9O9oyFRNdwVNmFnuw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Easily missed out restaurant. Service was ok but for some reason they served us everything with chicken even though we order tom yum gang. Anyways, food was averagely good except for the curry was a bit watering.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2IN3H7yzyw-CM7fi4wSKY3nl-3Lkox5rV4RmD&fid=0x0:0xdaf5f7cf4b327c09"],"When":"2024-6-29"},{"Name":"Antonina Tserk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLu51platMydr9nMXtSXXj2rBVQmDVJ5TeaoybWeTCMpMIhjw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had spring rolls, pad thai prawns, coconut rice with chicken and tasty fresh salad, tom yam (small). The food was amazing! I haven’t eaten such delicious Thai food since visiting Thailand! But another awesome thing about this place is portions! They are huge! We haven’t expected that and couldn’t finish everything, just took away leftovers. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP13Grs1fEdca9HTmz1pr48I9OXWgjvCW-ECoUB&fid=0x0:0xdaf5f7cf4b327c09"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"Jessey Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMb0JtXtWT6QIMbuh1r6Wjm_4pV4rOD6KtKkiVpLdwarlZMpha=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super awesome staff and owners, accommodated us even if they were closing in 30 minutes. Food is amazing, perfect balance of spice, creaminess and flavors. Heavily recommend if you are in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbOtqY_sgWFeitZTdZeullDn1JJ2qW0Ax1iFny&fid=0x0:0xdaf5f7cf4b327c09"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They serve authentic Pad Thai with generous portions of noodles and large prawns! I was impressed with the amount of prawns given for the dish too. I asked for a spice level of 3.5/5 and it was spicy but, still enjoyable. Complimentary green tea in a small tea kettle was cute.

Yes, the interior of the place has seen better days and its not anywhere you'd go for a nice night out but, the food was very good. Its a small restaurant with 6 tables. About 4 tables to fit 4 guests each and 2 smaller tables to fit 2 guests each. They have a small parking lot on the side of the restaurant. There were quite a few customers picking up.

The server was friendly and personable. The restaurant is family owned.

I would 100% come back here again.  If you like Pad Thai this place is worth trying out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmC3TAKLdjut8951Ymwzs0Qtl8YxrtCAEv3FLi&fid=0x0:0xdaf5f7cf4b327c09"],"When":"2023-4-15"},{"Name":"Kate Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInyjlu0qoqpRbLL17MOOScTvMcRZSg8bf0P1FK82u7DtRXfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The exterior and interior decor could use some improvements, but the food is fresh and flavourful (which is what really matters).  All the dishes we had were great.  The staff were very friendly and attentive.

Definitely one of the best Thai restaurants I've been to.  I'll be sure to return and recommend this little gem.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAIVQza-fLmRjI-HZgAxuoD0EQCW8czSxAxGUt&fid=0x0:0xdaf5f7cf4b327c09"],"When":"2017-5-7"},{"Name":"Julie Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9yyWG_Ieprgcllu4pZBMEeeD1AqtJanukSOIHygxTbVTzt-Mz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Originally, we wanted to try Henry Kitchen but it’s reservation only place. So we decided to try Little Bangkok which is located just across the street.
Just like the name, the restaurant is pretty small and super casual (too casual to my liking) it’s almost like you’re going to someone’s outdated house. Although the taste of the food were good but some of the texture of the noodle and meat weren’t perfect. I would not recommend this place if you’re looking for good vibes. But the food is quite good. The service was just ok, servers could dress up better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAJn4uXKv-ykUfK8atHK6EyobEuLqCYMcNKwpb&fid=0x0:0xdaf5f7cf4b327c09"],"When":"2020-2-15"},{"Name":"Shreya Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXYyfchREZOt93jrLr4kvvBwB1jTepyfM6oQu2MU6JoB-ykQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The pad Thai and shrimp salad were brilliant.  We also got their homemade rice cakes and loved them! Will definitely return for the warm food and cozy dining experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dane Jo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKD24zpseh3Az4iZl5wtWhIBdG-ztskVB8kEN6CN0Jxlv5-JA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great authentic food. One of the best pad Thais. Big portion sizes and came quick and the service as well. The place is very old and lowkey but worth it for a relaxed quick dinner","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Kevin Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLyYLnZgxMkUqzHBHzA2QrRbdqyipTuzteJV6wMuexKoyPmtg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have been ordering from Kokomo for a couple years and have always been extremely happy with the food, price and service. However I recently ordered the holiday bowl and there was hardly anything in my container. It was more like a snack. I was still hungry afterwards. I hope this isn't the regular portion size and they made a mistake on my order as it was extremely expensive for the small amount of food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7gB2vnjumXPgr7fkrweFQgSSjrHmYHppjfRYs&fid=0x0:0x7f65a7f6352e1e35"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been here a couple times now, both pleasant visits. 1st time trying an Acai Bowl, got "The Works" and I loved it! The desserts they carry made by Turf were excellent.
Can't wait to try the other dishes.
Very friendly and informative staff.
Need to change the happy hour pricing as it is inaccurate.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1skL3AectG6DLZZiPpCEnw0BSfEnSgp01WIjE&fid=0x0:0x7f65a7f6352e1e35"],"When":"2024-6-26"},{"Name":"Zaena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0uL5_BX81jM9l56vBhJlVZo9GPHZpZOUMAV-UObxVeXamgoUc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Kokomo is a great plant-bases option tucked away in suter brook. The food is decent, not exceptional. I usually feel like the meal could’ve been better - for instance, the Korean bowl’s use of extra firm tofu isnt great.
Staff have always been kind.
Atmosphere is very cute. Very modern, nice windows. The stools do leave a bit to be desired, back-support wise.
All in all, 4/5 stars","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPo5ykSUWIshpDOqhDHRbvU-CdYAK-5BaWS00_M&fid=0x0:0x7f65a7f6352e1e35"],"When":"2024-10-4"},{"Name":"Katia Albert","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL5bmwoiVXSH4CqdEhBAsB79iP_3oHFTzTK9PSwIUYDbhkd1g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Some of the bowls are decent - harvest, shawarma and caesar - but others like the holiday bowl I thought was terribly bland and salty for barely any food. Quantity is very inconsistent. At the high price point, it’s becoming harder to justify…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMa--t8f5pqexAF1CSaZTnY8td0X7nmm_cfwyVi&fid=0x0:0x7f65a7f6352e1e35"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Maraschino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhS3dYMThrWsdQxVJVk7bvap7Ye0aWDZ1e3W4Ta6TU9YM0Dnk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered from Uber eats and was pleasantly surprised I could find something healthy yet so delicious. I will definitely order again!

Update! I stopped in for an açai bowl. It’s soooo good! The coffee here is amazing too 🩷","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOS5OeoVZhqA5686KjKIYdzbdc3RZRQPBF5Sxzz&fid=0x0:0x7f65a7f6352e1e35"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were so happy to find Kokomo and their açai bowls! We both got the Kokomo bowl (they had a few others) and it was delicious and filling. The mint was a nice touch. We had an oat milk latte and an almond milk latte and both were tasty.

Quick and friendly service. We also got a $3 discount off both bowls for coming before 11am.

They are a vegan shop with a few grocery ingredients and some tasty-looking treats that we will have to try on another day, but only after I try one or two of their bowls because they looked amazing too. We’re looking forward to our next visit.

Edit: we’ve been back many times for the açai bowls. Today I had the Kokomo burger and the chocolate orange latte and both were really good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYZj1_sxL5pBQ1_1GHfWKfjgYmAluKLwC2CYhX&fid=0x0:0x7f65a7f6352e1e35"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"Natali Katz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEphl1x5ru8xPB5YBR8eIEi9UOQbxLLF-DuvTa8Jnf25GtP7qLDA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An instant favourite. Absolutely blown away by how delicious the bowls are. I tried the Shawarma Macro bowl and cannot recommend it enough!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbwXfFEYqFSsiu8ibYKENX98i999CUocnVvEWQ&fid=0x0:0x7f65a7f6352e1e35"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Nena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXail0hFaAr6UWwh19nZb5xdJGv0KAVLSD1VnM8OXnts_-tYe0Nrw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow I was pleasantly surprised by this cute little restaurant when in the area. The ambience is cozy and comfortable, and really aesthetic. The iced mocha was probably one of the best I've ever tried, and the laksa bowl was delicious with unique bursts and textures of flavors in each bite. I'll definitely be back to try the other menu items!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4XylIqh-IXIwKqTJ6NRb945YJ5yAaV5oqvI_f&fid=0x0:0x7f65a7f6352e1e35"],"When":"2024-4-11"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Parm Poustchi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUzuL6uQgOVPirf2JhL5jowm8hzjHya32BsOdNPYYmPw5Whog8oA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went there for the first time today and was pretty happy overall. We tried heaven’s garden roll, and it was very interesting and fresh. Also tried deep fried California which was really good. Spicy salmon roll was okay, and we liked their miso soup. The only thing that was a downer was their calamari. I found it very greasy, and not so pleasant.
Staff were super sweet, polite and attentive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_Y6_f8uJcbKZg0ayE_Z6lUwcg5XceB7OpQuDB&fid=0x0:0x8174c9b61f42bbfc"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Chang Wun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXinnRETbtdmwq0G3dzHpocXq4c0y1kT8tCLTmXT5-MPrsCx3WH9g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered two people set and also a beef don. The food is average. I visited a couple of Japanese restaurants, and they are all higher quality with cheaper price. The interior is good with ipad in every table. They have a couple of promotions such as we can choose either miso soup or soda drink if we leave fill out the survey. After we done the survey, they said the survey is optional, we should leave the google review in order to get the free soup/ drink. The most offensive behavior was that when we paid the bill, they only gave us two candies, however we have three people. We not only ordered two people set but also beef teriyaki. We did not care about the candy but the behavior is totally not acceptable. Definitely won’t revisit any of the franchise anymore.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9yrOaqriGrOH1fK6-arYygX1K48gp48wVb_Kh&fid=0x0:0x8174c9b61f42bbfc"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"Maggie Lo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGW29ON88ICUA4mr7enhvuFI7FILuznS3AnqusBIEeINpfEis=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service and food! Appreciate the self ordering which makes it easy. Spicy tuna combo is delicious!

There's a promo to get a kids meal for free for spending $50. Love it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOThFc0Yuonggiuq2tAMmDdTIjEYIYNzDp8NhAj&fid=0x0:0x8174c9b61f42bbfc"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Kwangshin Oh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmURrBfjvjbZeNZTSmNIKU-nwFBIWBf2lmnVvv2AIbeff8kDp9xg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sushi Mura is a fantastic spot for sushi lovers, and their “Salmon Blossom” is a standout dish. The presentation is stunning, with delicately sliced salmon arranged like a beautiful flower, making it almost too pretty to eat.

The restaurant has a relaxed atmosphere, perfect for enjoying a casual sushi night or celebrating a special occasion. The staff are friendly and attentive, ensuring you have a great dining experience from start to finish. If you’re a fan of salmon or just love beautifully crafted sushi, the “Salmon Blossom” at Sushi Mura is a must-try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDPKv2F-4yU3Dq4843vhUvOwLI9l9ETrtxmMX9&fid=0x0:0x8174c9b61f42bbfc"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Franklin Ribeiro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KD-iw_Q54cn9nHFc0kiuGUSaa4ZPRQtsq2yQBLbkLdyNpL-2yg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came to a sushi restaurant in the same address, and our experience was… OK. Today, we thought about having sushi for lunch, and we were a bit hesitant to come here again but we did. To our surprise, everything changed! Everything is different! And it is a lot, I mean A LOT, better! It’s now called Sushi Mura. I can’t wait to come here again! Awesome food, service and atmosphere! 👏🏻","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4MEAAUD0ebO735_dU6_digWAf1S9nF45Zz_fc&fid=0x0:0x8174c9b61f42bbfc"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Christina Cho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLF2rKdtcW_fhZcpHTpin00nVPOF5fQkt8bTLshsOzNo1k_xg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sushi Mura is an absolute gem for anyone looking to enjoy fresh, high-quality sushi in a warm and inviting atmosphere. From the moment you step inside, the modern yet cozy decor sets the tone for a fantastic dining experience. The staff are friendly and attentive, greeting you with a smile.

I tried their deluxe sashimi, assorted nigiri, takoyaki, and spicy salmon. The portion sizes were generous, and the prices were reasonable for the quality. I’ll certainly be back soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBp68AYYOohdG8Uv0TfQ3sS4c3um98F54ASqZs&fid=0x0:0x8174c9b61f42bbfc"],"When":"2024-11-27"},{"Name":"Evangeline Reymundo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJI1Nlu3hdQyr4eln6VfUWQFA-CRztL9qvZigMJlicalVY3cw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food and serving size were okay. I liked that they served the tempura separate from the udon to keep its crispness. It was a very cold day when we went thus getting room temperature tea, when we looked forward to hot tea, was disappointing. It was free so I can't complain. The ambiance was good. Overall a pretty good experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPL_6fiBiCkQh1MtB8tlr_SOc1mSLz9KDWD92CP&fid=0x0:0x8174c9b61f42bbfc"],"When":"2024-11-7"},{"Name":"Jeen Yi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhcwyBv1_WETXqkoDdBBZ2oH9-Ur5OEeJ60ai298Pb3yCKIWY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We stopped by this spot after visiting Rocky Point park not thinking too much before going in; to my surprise, the interior was spotless and super clean (didn't have the fishy smell that you might experience at some other sushi restaurants!). You can order your food comfortably by the tablet installed at your table or by the server, and they are still very prompt regardless with food and drinks. The quality of the food was outstanding, all extremely fresh and just right. I high recommend you stop by if you are in Port Moody or a resident around the restaurant. The rolls are good and the kitchen entrees are very good as well. Lots of options!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQT0g2LpKj9Z26TIOua4IuCCaI6WtugzyIkDHs&fid=0x0:0x8174c9b61f42bbfc"],"When":"2024-6-25"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Stan “The Anti-Slip Guy” Schaefer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzqltE5LGtJImuoUpVJ_NYvhJbn49XC-SYegXTLH-CfeoTWoA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This restaurant serves wonderful Thai food. Unfortunately, since covid, it is no longer a dine-in place. The food is always excellent, and the owners are always glad to see you. They take great pride in their work and deliver a great meal to go.\nI highly recommend Aroy Thai kitchen for your Thai food cravings !!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Martin Matahari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAn1gLSlBMeGXZBHUnKkSJRx9LUQmHP9VKEpiPVA6PU8EOwPbl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Very disappointing food. Zero authenticity to Thai food. Just a whole bunch of vegetables with a small amount of protein. I ordered kee mao noodles but they used pad Thai noodles. The gap row tasted identical to the kee mao. Just like soy sauce and fish sauce. Nothing else. Worst Thai food I have ever eaten and not cheap. 2 dishes $50 for take out. Will not be returning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvKEzDoI8Lw5Pgrsj-MstnUrX1QovUlrM6XZcs\u0026fid=0x0:0xc100037309cfd3cf"],"When":"2023-9-18"},{"Name":"Gavin Hainsworth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLfrIVmrjyKGivMcZWeOPAIpUZMWPQw3OboqH_fkm716KvG3g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Was very disappointed by the quality of the food. It looked much better than it tasted.  The coconut rice was mushy, the satay was covered in a curry sauce and the peanut sauce was meh. The Phad Thai was awful. I may not even finish my leftovers","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrMK_eB7JSMDCSKs0gU3YQN8CHS6qRnQV4-mcS\u0026fid=0x0:0xc100037309cfd3cf"],"When":"2023-1-1"},{"Name":"David Royer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUlrzPUrsbaR5f9zXqUTdwB3PDm0rBKS2PUmLGKqqCt7U9cSd4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Welcoming and clean space, very helpful personnel. Not sure the price reflects the level of cuisine ingredients. Overall nice but will not come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTDrZYnWo_y0EqbGVlhYkAgdDbSuXvGTjFUcTT\u0026fid=0x0:0xc100037309cfd3cf"],"When":"2017-11-22"},{"Name":"Lesley Evans Ogden","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSvA12PSvW75OqmIsnZCbdVRZhSg-JfZUlJc_vG9Cu60EkD7UK=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a Port Moody culinary hidden gem. Family run, top quality delicious Thai food with the freshest and most flavourful spices and ingredients that will leave your tastebuds longing for more.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Oliver Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXb7YjHQxpAKhHYdI5aVhvehEVs8wdOwgNd26ERX0zFocfg8Rg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This is someone’s business, no one likes low ratings. With that said , we had to get take out for 2 because there were no dine in option. After we started eating, I said to my wife, I feel angry with each bite, the food just had no love or taste. All I could taste is the msg, salt, spice and anger for what ever the chef is angry at. I hope more love and respect for the cuisine can be focused on. Will come back to try in a while to see if comments actually mean anything to this establishment.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Holly Becker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLtkPj0i4UnDaWPksDveMRMXoY8Op1jg8CaTkBVYRUij35bIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good, tasty Thai food. Default is quite spicy, but they can make mild. Chairs are weird.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTB7Karlcod0PFGzKg4d82ymRE5MMq0QHH_9N3\u0026fid=0x0:0xc100037309cfd3cf"],"When":"2017-2-12"},{"Name":"lasdiabless","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJZBwh57kp6-1iQ1V4M3EODxcohHzfa6NB9OQj8FEJn-SUhV5D=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I don't know if they used to make good pad Thai at some point but this tasted nothing like Pad Thai and I've been to Thailand. Didn't even taste like a basic Canadian version, no tamarind taste no sweetness to it or acidity. Had to have been one of the worst I've ever tried in Canada. Very sad....and I never bother to write reviews. Please do better to represent Thai food.","Images":null,"When":""}]
