[{"Name":"Daniel Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ0pxg4i-TtYyI_KJB77O-97mUJ6f5A9DX0AG3A02P0CkLx2Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sergio's Pizza in Port Moody is perfect for those who love a thick, hearty crust. The crust is satisfying and pairs well with the fresh, generous toppings. Each slice feels like a full meal, making it a great option for when you’re really hungry.

The pizzas are consistently good, and it’s a solid choice for takeout. Definitely worth a try if you’re in the area and craving something filling!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris Hanley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbM3d7s4Aq6JN2ZhoS9MNKeIo2eaMG5mOqj_ZOXzJz7sWsVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ordered beef on my pizza. Little tiny crumbles like parmesan cheese dehydrated beef crap.What a joke. This place has gone downhill since original owners. Its so sad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmu2prD2RvvAa4M_cvYnpxptoaZws1fNAcqzV-&fid=0x0:0xa5e5acaf585c32be"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Sarah Murray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUewUWwG-c558BS5ADbBaqHJLRhAySg2ndftNcc4ZL7C8AW9Qxg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It had been quite some time since I had ordered from Sergio's, probably about 8 months. I missed their pizza so I gave it a go. I was amazed at how excellent the pizza was, just like I remembered but better...so much toppings. I will be putting Sergio's back on regular rotation.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Clayton Robertson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYYtsoZ4f2Mdi2szTOUXeCSLehGEr4GPUM3FgZQ2wnJ9rbVB9i=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious pizza with a crispy thick crust!

Sergio’s loaded it with toppings and the pizza had delicious flavour. I order delivery and they were on time with their quoted time. It arrived hot even though I lived 15 min away from the restaurant.

I highly recommend if you are looking for a fresh and tasty pizza restaurant!

Thanks for the amazing food and service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOA3XP7NTTHr9S-YRXdUjfx3Ht2mJc0ILvy7mSJ&fid=0x0:0xa5e5acaf585c32be"],"When":"2023-6-28"},{"Name":"Lisa C.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLzvbBjCs3B94OVibVGv4uVuD0c6d5EG7QEM4xGkD1GHxH-VA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Don't know if there was a change in ownership. Sergio's used to be good, but then started going down hill w the quality of their pizza ie the cheese definitely tastes cheaper, and the dough just feels more soggy.
Recently ordered for pick up to then discover when we got home that they completely burnt our pizza.
Sad to say, but I think that will be the last time we order from them.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXgHTq9Y2T2yk0d10ukRVRtb3kOXyJTpAvYf_L&fid=0x0:0xa5e5acaf585c32be"],"When":"2023-5-9"},{"Name":"Andrew Storey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHMIkmeNQ1qv9p5Gjftg7GvYIs9B2hl62_YGuwug5IglfM2K4E=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"DISGUSTING. Walked in there to grab a quick slice of pizza, the two staff acknowledged me and just kept on cleaning in the back. It wasn’t even remotely close to closing time. After a few minutes I said “hello?” and one of them reluctantly came to get my order. Already annoyed, I was curious if they were going to bother to wash their hands or put on gloves after being in the back cleaning, and I think you can guess the answer to that. No. If you are at all conscious about health and safety standards or general customer service, don’t go here. Will never go here again which is too bad because the pizza is decent.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex Zamora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNKWfobpaRhPSUqenbcNSr93AGpOp0zhiMmlx_-HBaE_jK9U05=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Flavourless, doughy, and disappointing. What was once a spot for a solid slice of pizza has slipped severely over the last few months. There are much better places in the area to go to, don’t waste your time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Luis Enrique Carrillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVn-opF4cAeVj-rPJG9VnbLnDSTqySrW0W5Ps_4TqPy_RtDJ8v2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Thick pizza slices. Great to pick a pair and go.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"ladan ghafouri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQKWEx_YV_Uj80v-xctgsLSGRY6V78hw5KMb4aNvRdZAaXJWti=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I just ordered a salmon sashimi to go. They still gave me a tea while I was waiting which it was so nice . The place was clean and cute. The staff was supper friendly . I have to come back for dine in and try sushi’s .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7GWo-gOrH8uM63b_B_F68bH9-YniYVWntxRQl&fid=0x0:0xbb09970b356e8bd1"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Jillian Cooke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXoVfvJseO-GDVyhUvIYpYrM3gIEu4XOG85NMAPmMxfGgxUPF74=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my go-to sushi place! I used to come here because it was close to my apartment but the more I ate at other sushi restaurants the more I genuinely wanted to return and eat here  instead. They are very affordable, but have nice  rolls, great special rolls and delicious sashimi. Best price for a split tuna and salmon sashimi ever, and it tastes great, super fresh. The only thing I've enjoyed more at other restaurants are the California rolls and agedashi tofu. Both are still good here but I've had a bit better.

I almost always get my food to go because it's a small restaurant and I live nearby but you can eat inside. They have an enclosed patio for extra space. Everyone working there are genuinely so nice and my food is ready in no time, usually 15 mins or less. The combos come with miso soup, which is always a nice surprise. I have been eating here at least once a month for years and I have zero complaints. I would like to try their all you can eat sushi one day!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtcorbRSzgNzlHlqlKDdVNWvUBJ99Ya4qaCEK6&fid=0x0:0xbb09970b356e8bd1"],"When":"2024-8-27"},{"Name":"Izmet Barranco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiQo1jy483UmDOGk0DLpOPmwFqDxOxzKBlrj-9MTXzn_Zhoww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We discovered this place by chance. It is kind of hidden in a mall but is is really good. They have both regular menu and all you can eat menu. For the second one they make sure you understand their policy and serve the order in stages, to be sure there are no waste.

Everything was fresh and tasty. Specially mention to the Alaska roll. We absolutely love it as well as the special spicy rolls. A place worth of visiting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVp9Mau4dS68ktoXdSXV7xz-zFjCacsMXDt2pA&fid=0x0:0xbb09970b356e8bd1"],"When":"2023-9-10"},{"Name":"Joanne Antoniak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTQwhPcO13h_HhVjJVUrwpHjU5MeesKhPrxV5pA1ymdZ1edFkY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time visit.
We chose all you can eat sushi lunch. It is expensive ($30/person); and there are some restrictions - but it was SO YuMMy!!
We ate all we could eat 😂
Service was outstanding!!  Our server was attentive and very polite.
Decor was OK; for a very tiny place - but the open storage shelves with boxes on display - affected the atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKlNAzbrATLvfGInUXjueg-i3Q3ErnrlLYtWfg&fid=0x0:0xbb09970b356e8bd1"],"When":"2023-7-8"},{"Name":"D A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJdDPdKx70IF8qinpqf4kBE0d__A91KC9IDnKHhcfzU8QrgaQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Not bad food, however, not a place you would go back. Bento bix chicken teriyaki,. Sauce was pre made container sauce,  spring roll was all roll no spring   tempura was 3 x as thick as should be . Temp prawn was sliced to create 2 pcs. If your hungry go but don't expect much. Clean and polite.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dan Peterson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbNeFUlLkRmjcX25zxpAW7H_0IDjY0P_SfdPGvxnigSNv-OQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Sakeya appears to do extensive takeout sushi business and I can see why, I tried the oshi aburi negitoro sushi and the Victoria roll (yam tempura and avocado) and both were very good. The bento box dinner was a good value but the teriyaki chicken was just ok, same for the tofu teriyaki.
We ate in and the service was terrific, our waitress was very friendly and efficient. The atmosphere is casual.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhJaTCegoSjLy_9kfGuFOwBpg3pn0p14-Uk5o7&fid=0x0:0xbb09970b356e8bd1"],"When":"2023-7-1"},{"Name":"Amelia M. [{"Name":"Michael Taylor (Battleship Cobra)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqj0B3uXJEI4-ToxfQ2z9_jzbT_Ue49f5Zh-XFyFN013RMY27V=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great atmosphere, awesome local beer selection (Yellow Dog, Parkside, Phillips...) and an amazing menu. The yorkies with the horseradish mayo are my favourite (nachos too with house-made chips). Grab a beer here with friends when the breweries close!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJA36R5ySOUBseh08jwYaauoI6WbHMcuq6cwEM&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"duane r neufeld","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhhlb1lcJQnDlyAPy1R2d_GOddZm-jMhyJJsiO9YhD02HRj38=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow a bit of a time/space warp.  If someone blindfolded you 10 minutes before arrival you could be thinking you are in remote Ireland ( though I've never been). Love the seats, decor, dark woods.  Ready for a fiddle and Fife to start any time.  Delightful pub offerings, wide bar choices.  Keen to revisit!   Consider parking in the nearby  underground.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Delany Bramley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIK2uPQopfYgNbDujVOD83GTVPgHurczGu-am82p4W8WqARQOg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The chef actually made a shrimp wrap rather than chicken for me whereas at a pub on Coast and Praire in PoCo refuses! The Well didn't even charge extra! Well done! Service was great too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyNfcHzYO_EJe8y8qrUyXb0YJemgmOi9TBsut2&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Grant M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRWL_i5cZiVpXExK1H8xMkwx4_6CHC_xRkP2HoYZIVJehiW1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's been a few years since I've stopped in at the Well.  I decided to walk from the Eagle Ridge Hospital as my brother was getting some tests done. So rather than sitting there and waiting I decided to go to the Well.

It was a beautiful day out so I just sat outside and enjoyed a couple Phillips Blue Bucks. The beer was nice and cold, and definitely nice and enjoyable on a nice day.

I grew up in Port Moody ( Born and raised ) and when my server came out with my second Beer I told her I can't believe where I'm sitting right now, that it used to be farm land and Horses running around and so on. I used to feed the horses at times with a carrot on my way to Hockey practices as I lived and grew up right behind the Esso Gas Station just up the road from the Well. My server couldn't believe it actually.

It's always great to come back home, and enjoy and reminisce the days of growing up in Port Moody 😀","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPv3oJO4DpTTTLZeliGYdyfWDrnkEZCqhuceeSF&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2024-6-20"},{"Name":"Ebrahim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPIKcLlYsRXzj_NU-cKrILAfiV6rHoottOnSl1Co3QI6YN1537=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Let me tell you about this gem of a local restaurant! The food? Absolutely amazing. Hands down, I had the best burger ever in Vancouver there. And guess what? If it's your birthday, they'll hook you up with a free shot as a little celebration gesture.

But it's not just about the food; the vibe is just so darn lovely. And then there's Megan, our server extraordinaire. She took care of us like nobody's business. You can just tell she adores spending time with customers and making sure they leave with smiles on their faces. Her kindness and professionalism are off the charts. We were asking for this and that, and she was more than happy to help us out every step of the way.

And get this – despite being a local spot, they're rocking a solid 4.3 review. Can you believe it? That's on par with big names like Cactus Club or Earls. But honestly, with people like Megan on their team, it's no wonder they're killing it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvo0dNJ8HHPdioG2-C9fSqlxrS1i8lXecWQHVT&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2024-2-17"},{"Name":"Chris “WolfmanMac” MacLeod","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk7iYkhOaOdtR5BVdCsDim4y9lHdV_5Fftj-CQxRzae_zANkHr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"4 stars for food only because this is not really your typical pub fare.....so don't be disappointed with potato chips as nachos instead of tortilla. Be absolutely thrilled you can get baby Yorkshire puddings stuffed with beef so you can have it all in your mouth at once instead of knife-and-forking a nice meal at Grandma's!
Typical burgers as well, but their salads are awesome and different as well. A couple of beers while you choose which game to watch on numerous TV's and a working fireplace. This place rocks for a beer or a sit-down for a couple hours.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kyle Desjarlais","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrRBEamWMJl4icWTFU6lImngzC0ND5A_dzd32uf-Z4ExMBsyw-Kg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow.
Beautiful Irish pub !
I lived in Port Moody way too long before I found this place. It's a real hidden gem.
Of course I had a Guinness on tap and then a Jameson on the rocks, proper drinks for an Irish pub. It was busy. Very loud, and very busy. Definitely a very lively and popular place.
Service did not lack at all despite the full house.
Props to the top notch bartender killing behind the counter. Really enjoyed my drinks at this pub.
Cheers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8UXOiylz8Pos0QiZelUGmaw9Ik0WSZC46yT4d&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2024-3-6"},{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The fried pickles and potato skins were absolutely delicious, a true delight. The price for happy hour was incredibly reasonable, making it even more enjoyable. However, I found the beef in the sliders to be a bit smelly, which was a bit disappointing. Nonetheless, the overall experience was great and I would definitely recommend visiting for the tasty treats and excellent happy hour deals!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPobWxLhOj-eqFVY9uuXuOOAVwOHIGg8p3L0sK_&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2023-8-27"}]

It tastes like they took a half eaten footlong and threw it on a Costco Pizza crust. Mamma Said Pizza is doing it up right - long live the mamma.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoaSwNfsWaTEZXjdcWE8-SN8KBVHupPGsSh2bt\u0026fid=0x0:0x1139f763070a03ff"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Brenda Bodnar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXip0tnc2MAYTd_t7flKkNJ49zhhPh5jcpiZ2opIuOQ4PhmwTrIbw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Saw this place in passing and Googled the reviews before deciding to order a pizza.  It was a 20-minute drive home so it was only lukewarm by the time I got in the door.  Regardless, this was the tastiest pizza I have had in several years.  I was surprised to see a thin crust which is always my preference.  I went for a simple pepperoni and mushroom with green peppers.  What I noticed right away was that all of the toppings were intact large pieces of pepperoni, green peppers and mushrooms (nothing minced on this pizza).  What a unique idea to drizzle honey on the crust.  It was really delicious.  This place is no where near my home but I wish it was.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP16gbvSTOqTrP4dk_LMPnSBdkqjfuRrJp8GMql\u0026fid=0x0:0x1139f763070a03ff"],"When":"2024-3-23"},{"Name":"dididodido dido","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLUvYQ6xK6svVdEg35LPnw6_RTbAl1bXcHiT4cUWLK4iYa_WA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent pizza.  Crust is thin, crunchy, without being too hard.  Firm and holds everything together. Easy to fold to stuff your face.  Had the Montreal Special and it had the perfect balance of ingredients and flavours.  Will definitely go back again for more.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marissa McKinnon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVY68LF-WJ3XLlkLB3mmSI9NIX-eNSB4BF4a47z33JIFfXjKyxv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best pizza I’ve had in a while! We chose the BBQ Chicken Pizza (with arugula instead of bacon) and the Fungi Pizza. Employee was very nice, and the pizza was made in a very timely manner. It was made beautifully, hot, delicious and evenly distributed toppings. They also had super cute, festive, halloween decorations up!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQwxkNkBXjxxMK1RNiHCF_YsEAhhxOKbp9Iuw6\u0026fid=0x0:0x1139f763070a03ff"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Derek Carr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXs5_9YoepHwXwJWgv8UG_Z7CMlP5ieqzu0oxCf6nhH4MEO-iM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"While most pizza places that we’ve bought from have become more expensive and less toppings and flavour, this place has absolutely perfect and tasty NY style pizza. The honey butter basted crust is crispy and delicious. Very fresh toppings. Super clean, but not really an “eat in” type of pizza joint. Friendly staff as well. My new “go to” local pizza place for sure.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Toscanny Pandu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL2gApUU6OqcgWej11WkI-IMAGjyAEo0RtxkVpTLkvbOK8AwZY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Definitely brought nostalgia back to being in Manhattan New York. We came an hour before closing and all the by-the-slice were cold..but with a bit of time in the oven, was brought back to life. I was pleasantly surprised how good the crust was, it was thin yet crispy and reminded me of what you expect from a New York slice. The cheese was the perfect amount, however the slice could have used a bit of more sauce. Great family atmosphere, and the owner was super friendly.\n\nWill definitely be coming back to get a fresh slice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFYzeyJXcJ64tV9fo1AYX-OLMluTy4a9jkmvdK\u0026fid=0x0:0x1139f763070a03ff"],"When":"2021-9-6"},{"Name":"Jeff Downer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXl3HQ-1C4N-_a7ykvhIi5aM883AB-cDQVYb1xeenCY7zekayvZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered the Godfather of all pizzas. Wanted to try this place for years. Blown away. We were starving and this hit so many spots. It’s exactly what I would put on top of a pizza, only they make it taste better. The crust was a great surprise and the pizza ooozed in all the right ways. Staff totally ruled. We chose to eat in the alley on our folding chairs because it was a nice evening. Would order from here daily if I lived in PoMo!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfgMn1cxZVer8R8f6Qph68H9VTRFTpJJovv-Wr\u0026fid=0x0:0x1139f763070a03ff"],"When":"2024-8-11"}]

We will not spend money on food due to policy.]

We came to this Legion to attend a Saturday night salsa dance event.  We regularly attend Legion dance events in Vernon, Enderby, and Salmon Arm.  Ar these smaller events, water and coffee is freely available. With the same entry fee, and four times the attendees, one would think the Port Moody Legion would be supportive of the event.

On arrival, before the event start, I went to the bar to order two beverages, along with glasses of water. I was informed that management had just instigated a policy of only selling bottled water. I have run across this policy before, when one is only requesting water. I have never been refused water with a meal or a beverage order before.

To reinforce a poor management decision, the manager chose not to be available for the inauguration of this policy.  This is unfair to the employees, who must face the sour customers. Luckily, the bartender had good customer service skills dealing with the unfortunate position he was placed in.  I guess the bartender will either find a better establishment for employment or become the manager at this Legion.

We will definitely not be recommending that our Legion friends drop into this branch.  It will just be a story of how good we have it at home!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shannon Craig","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKkcCTiYPJx6mTtL4cFio0D_2WqDJBVB2_sRqMM-Qko3xx7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed my experience at the Port Moody Legion. Server was very friendly. Food and drinks were not only delicious but VERY well priced. The chef even came over to check that we were enjoying the food. Great experience all around and will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBedwV8VWdv3pw4wwLVfcwKiN0yMnFkRS4VXA&fid=0x0:0x77f071911dfe4c2f"],"When":"2023-2-25"},{"Name":"Kalwant Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWKjft0leBsdm_kFX5OSZ15NI1FCR9f_lQ0muJx87U2uNDsgSRfA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very nice location to drink and dine. Awesome prices, food and service. A great people place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnnrLznU1ggjGvjX4bJdCVV9s0Vu-yuDGQGMZN&fid=0x0:0x77f071911dfe4c2f"],"When":"2022-5-28"}]

[{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It's a pretty typical dim sum restaurant with decent food and service. I appreciate the speed of the service and the value for all the food. It can get pretty busy, especially during weekends so be prepared to wait if you didn't make a reservation.

We got the lotus leaf wrapped sticky rice with pork, some steamed pea shoots, vegetable porridge (congee) and good selection of dumplings. It's not anything to write home about, but it's hardy and gets the job done. Solid experience overall and I would give them the thumbs up.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNldHIuVK-fsR57KEsIFq08_KeBGOEZKK1j8FvJ&fid=0x0:0xe8960ddf73ad1704"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Grace Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJv2Qb5BK8BlHD8B-fNqpMIiwBP96of3n6s7qsHpu4xPXVSJg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious and cute dim sum! Food was fresh and fast. We made reservations as it can get busy. Staff were friendly and attentive. I do speak Chinese as well. The kids love the food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOqxd3kLGHCrMQedJ1T0fOAbSmVa-M_lHRR3aR-&fid=0x0:0xe8960ddf73ad1704"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"Celina Wright","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXh2wmxFC5Utlekpzdr2MpXFcBCcrOSjcqSIoXPM9bCTR9ROXAVjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was fantastic and the staff were polite.  We visited for dim sum on a weekend. Seating took some time (10-15 minutes) even with a reservation, but I find that to be normal at most dim sum restaurants.

For those unfamiliar with a dim sum restaurant: just make sure you flag down the wait staff if you need anything and they'll head over to you quickly - don't wait for them to check in on you.

We had about 6 dishes among 4 people and were very satisfied with all of them 😌

We had an overall great experience and will visit again soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEjZuQIZKRlmVGxE6oDTnZ2lj9iQ_fe2zH2aWD&fid=0x0:0xe8960ddf73ad1704"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Annia Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLCmNf-6kVgoV3z2v1rhLUKPIXQtdwZxPsOxdlb6pZhbXP-BQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Enjoying some yummy 😋 dim sum for brunch.

A culinary tradition that has captured the hearts and palates. The term “dim sum” translates to “touch the heart,” a phrase that encapsulates the essence of these bite-sized delights.  So many different varieties of special Chinese dishes, served in small portions for all to share.
Dim sum has always been a symphony of colors, textures, and flavors in each dish to share amounst friends.

Food was fresh and fast service provided. Staff was attentive.  They were busy today luckily made reservations.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBhObly0gYODvg08E6vPpciOoSHEghCgOJz5-x&fid=0x0:0xe8960ddf73ad1704"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"K 2","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCr90XQEGh_XW_dogXGAOrNDNdWl4oto2DcQXyO8hGv5A6DKrVWQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently had an incredibly disappointing lunch here. We ordered four dishes, but after waiting for more than an hour, only three arrived. The last dish never came despite us repeatedly asking about it. When we requested to cancel the order after an hour, the server responded with an attitude, insisting it was coming. After waiting an additional 20 minutes with no sign of the dish, we had no choice but to cancel it for good.

To make matters worse, the food that we did receive was subpar, tasting like frozen dim sum from T&T rather than freshly made. Seafood roll was.. speechless.. since when the imitation crab became seafood????
The entire experience—from the long wait times to the poor service and bland food—was awful. After spending an hour and a half there and only eating three dishes, I was left feeling frustrated and dissatisfied.

I definitely won’t be returning, and I would not recommend this place to anyone looking for quality dim sum or good service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO797XW5ANvImlqxiyC1g_s4CcDzQenFyWjxZsG&fid=0x0:0xe8960ddf73ad1704"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Another Neptune afternoon…

I think this is the only Neptune I haven’t been to yet? Anyways, in the area taking care of some business so decided to try this location out.

It’s located on the front side of Coquitlam Center and facing the new Cactus Club, plentiful of parking is available up front in the malls parking lot.

Inside is separated into to section; Neptune Wonton for fast casual dishes and Neptune Seafood for more of a formal dining. It’s kind of a smaller place and pretty basic to me.

Anyways, here were the dim sum I ordered;

1. Seafood dumpling in soup. The imitation crab being used made the broth a bit overly sweet, was too unpleasant to finish it.
2. Steamed spicy beef tripe. It wasn’t tender enough, needed to steam it a bit longer.
3. Steamed chicken feet with special sauce. It wasn’t tender enough for the skin to fall off the bone, needed to run through the deep fryer a bit longer during the prep process.
4. Turnip cake with XO sauce. It’s almost a joke, my 10 year old nephew could’ve done better with this dish especially its presentation. Failed!
5. Baked preserved egg and ginger pastry. Absolutely horrible, the preserved egg was rubbery and the whole pastry crumbled along with its ginger paste. Failed!
6. Fried vegetables with shrimp paste. An alternate version of the deep fried eggplant with shrimp paste. It was so so.
7. Baked bbq pork buns. It was okay, the bbq pork could be less sweet.
8. Purple rice roll with fish paste. It was okay, the super jumbo size was unexpected.
9. Stir fry udon with live lobster. Surprisingly it was pretty good, enough wok hay to really bring out the flavours.
10. Little white rabbit pudding. Not bad, cute little treats.

Overall, I wasn’t too impressed with the layout and atmosphere of the restaurant. It portray itself as a mid class Chinese seafood restaurant, but felt l like a simple family restaurant with mid level prices.

The service was okay, enough to satisfy the basics, don’t expect anything more than that.

As for the food, honestly it was probably one of the most disappointing experience I had so far out of all the Neptunes I’ve been to.

Not a repeat or recommendation from me anytime soon… 1.5 stars","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQR35TFh2sABn6mWQv4-F7inIjdWxHkqeXqX1w&fid=0x0:0xe8960ddf73ad1704"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"Danny Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8eoyUE6az-FmQo7i2mVq5z64Ow48sgKu1EmLZc0zWWN6DMy5asw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came for dimsum. The portions here are pretty big and taste fresh. Lots of menu items to choose from. We had a larger party (11 people) and they had our table ready on time. However they forgot 3 of our items which we ended up cancelling. Overall good food and friendly service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2zar_Z9-rBEtiUz29w_-7yCkOfWbkH7rr9FO8&fid=0x0:0xe8960ddf73ad1704"],"When":"2023-10-9"},{"Name":"CY","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIyAWoVXS2wSYA_X8YaMHwhMb74Th2juKHatcW6zvf48kBI0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Been here twice, once in July 2024, once in Nov 2024. Quality difference between a couple months was huge. (Much better food quality and taste now).

Clean and spacious environment.

Food was served a bit slowly though.

Dim Sum dish variety is quite limited on the menu.

Price is a bit higher than mid tier

Over it is decent","Images":null,"When":""}]

Salad was all lettuce  and two sad looking turnips.
I’m super disappointed. I have passed the truck outside my work downtown several times and have been anticipating trying it. Did not expect it to be so, so bad. Bad enough to compel me to leave this review.

My family went through the drive-thru and we were immediately put off by the attitude of the lady taking our order. I ordered 3 3-piece chicken strip combos all with honey mustard and sprite, immediately after that she asked me \"Is that all?\" I said no and continued to order 1 chicken BLT combo with sprite. She then asks if we wanted honey mustard with both of the combos and I stated that it was only one chicken BLT burger, that's when she confirmed that we had ordered the 3 chicken strip combos. At the end of that she asks again \"Is that all?\" again I say no and order 1 double teen combo with root beer. After we paid, we only recieved three drinks instead of FIVE, we brought it up with the woman who was attending to us and she argued back and forth with us, we thought it was only the drinks so we just told her to leave it and drove off. When we got home we realized that it wasn't just the drinks but also we were missing the entirety of the 2 chicken strip combos. We went back to the A\u0026W just to realize that the lady had just conveniently gotten off her shift. Unfortunately, there was now a new staff member who had to deal with our anger. All we wanted was our money back and we said this quite a few times, this was a whole ordeal as well as he tried to offer us the chicken strips that we were missing. We finally got our money back and it's safe to say that we will NOT be coming back. All of this, not even to mention that the QR code on the window to let them know how they did was expired, as a result, this is the review you get, and the review that you deserve.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bachir Abba","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUm96VLPvjcmyOyqeAhQsyNGSJRyHGcLK49B2JWG8W3Q-Kg7wS6Ew=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice place to eat if you are in the neighborhood. Team is really good. Service is fast and amazing. One thing I have to mention is the cleanliness of the restaurant .highly recommended.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cruz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwy8Uwa7-GhYRQ_QjH7hvTpVzk1UcK5M-CVWt5B_hQ5ljtWFBA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"When I visited the neighbourhood last week, it was a pretty laid-back place. So tasty they didn't even need ketchup!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOupzXR9Znz2moILexerkTwqsTjirx2aPiO1shv&fid=0x0:0x16abda2984fa5eca"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Roozegar Mohammadi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrQru4VExe7pdnc_LNPc1yA4v-RaJaPJWbL5u-B9MOm7dojm-4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"1- Thank you and a quick question  regarding your meat shop,  Is there any Halal certification accredited by Halal Canada?
2- Your answer: "Response from the owner
Thank you for your inquiry! We’re proud to share that our supplier is one of the best Halal meat providers in the entire country, ensuring the highest quality and adherence to Halal standards.
Regarding your question, yes, our supplier is accredited by Halal Canada, so you can shop with confidence.
By the way, if you’ve enjoyed our services, would you consider giving us a 5-star review instead of 3? Your support means a lot to us, and we’d love to hear what more we can do to earn that extra star from you!"

3- my reply to your reply:"Thank you for your reply. Unfortunately, i have to change the mark to 1 star because of the following objective evidences:
"Although you mentioned that your supplier has an accredited halal certificate, based on my observations during everyday shopping and watching your Deli and Meatshop employees, it seems that you are not adhering to halal provider rules. Specifically, you are selling halal and non-halal meat together and using the same knives and surfaces to cut them. The regulations in this regard are similar to those for allergen and non-allergen items, where cross-contamination is strictly prohibited. Rather than this, open packages of halal and non-halal meat inside the freezer or fridge should be completely separated. I recommend that you read the Halal International Standard requirements for retail stores. Until you are able to meet these standards, please remove all halal signage from your store, as it is misleading to Muslim customers in this regard"","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ali Fasihizadeh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeEgxRiuCQGGcgBhaC0R0-E7HN9SKaiGfOrL8NTnYlp6WMk2xa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently ordered a birthday cake to Suzan at the bakery and I couldn’t be happier with the result! Special thanks to Ms. Afsane, who always provides excellent service.
Ms. Afsane is a professional barista and her coffees are wonderful ❤️👌🏻","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1xMqJRElD_1t8Z-23lkvD_JcHAGaeFjua0Wpn&fid=0x0:0x16abda2984fa5eca"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"meow meow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKrJ-mhNYyKJeNAeH6NNi0zZynSPeNyTmmob3-hI4azgkbLWA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is always delicious and price is always good! We had a server named Sareh who is very friendly and attentive. She’s also recommended and offered sampling authentic food we’ve never tried before and they taste really good and we all love it! It’sone of the best places to have really good quality food and customer service. In addition the atmosphere is very comfortable and inviting.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fuzzley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuQBLG7TksG6wDxiaXxGD7Hm142h_aQxwM9_mE25IYjf3jo0BguA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"As a long-term customer I was very disappointed with my recent experience at Urban Gate. I brought to the attention of the cashier that I had purchased some barbari bread a few days ago, and that I was told these were baked the night before.
Unfortunately when I took the bread home and opened it on the same day, I found both to be rotten and stale. I did not want to drive all the way back for a little refund that. The following week while shopping at the store, I informed the cashier. All I sought was a simple acknowledgment of my concern and an apology for the inconvenience. Instead, what followed was a lengthy justification about how fresh bread can spoil overnight due to moisture. Additionally, the cashier explained their return policy, stating that I should have brought back the receipt and the rotten bread for a refund.
I felt that the response lacked empathy and a proper understanding of customer service. The interaction came off as arrogant, and it left me feeling undervalued as a customer. It is disappointing to know that, as a loyal customer, my concerns were not taken seriously. I hope Urban Gate can improve its customer service training to better handle situations like this in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marjan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJi5kZ8SK7DmiaOMIRuV-4Ttne1NBXp-Dh_P2EIrXoD-QM7Hw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This store has a good selection of products from my home country , especially in the meat department, where the staff are polite and helpful.
However, the customer service at checkout is very disappointing and rude, especially from the cashier ladies. They rarely greet  and often have a negative attitude. For example, one cashier today threw the receipt on the counter, slammed her hand on it, and walked away without saying anything. I even said hello and thank you, but she didn’t respond. When I asked the others if they had the same experience, they said they did.
These interactions make shopping feel unwelcoming. I hope the staff realizes that everyone deserves respect and that good service is important.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lina Huine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTc90UClGdW5-vlLdRudv0nYQ1eUmIsZfcJ8sj-8pxZav3xZGO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A nice restaurant and very welcoming. It was our first time here, and we were ready to try all you can eat!! They had quite a few items in the salad bar. Hot paella, salads, veggies, rice, mashed potato’s and beans. There was lots of choices for the grilled meats, pork, chicken, sausages, chicken hearts and lamb. Although some meats I tried felt a little too rare they were ok, I prefer my steaks medium well. You can ask for certain cuts while they cut the meats for you. They are brought by the server to every table. My favourite was the pork ribs. So much flavour and so tender.  The grilled pineapple with cinnamon was also so delicious. This is the perfect place for meat lovers. The buffet price is $49.00 per adult and you have a 2-hour dining limit.
All Drinks cocktails, beer and wine and are not included with the price per person. Service is efficient our server was quite attentive.  The dining area has a nice open touch and the Samba dancers were lovely! Parking can be hard to find and it’s a tight squeeze . Reservations are recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkJM-iflMuGBgRbrRP5gP9QpmkbJa6mzraUFe9&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-6-29"},{"Name":"Peter Au","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwBxrbZVtlTM1OV2SDGm3NwMn7yUHEw1MaS3fh_B2utP_W4kON=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my second time coming here. With my family of 4 this time. The salad bar was vastly improved. Good variety. The meat was excellently prepared. The servers were very attentive. Everyone were having a good experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNY1ZKhYQV1ilQvIAxUYreDVvtD35cj39Sf8BQG&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-10-24"},{"Name":"Hassan Makhlouf","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYREoqUkazVJoJhrGCrjS5g1lIMahzFkhsZA1Ir7O3A-YofJyb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time to be there and it was Friday night , the week night of the show.
Staff were friendly and helpful and guided us through how the process work for all you can eat meat.
Salad buffet included some famous Brazilian choices.
Different types of meat come to your table to cut slices if you want. The only thing is that they should provide more well done options, although they bring some when we requested.
Don’t miss their brisket, grilled shrimp and their lamp . They are amazing.
Show reflect Brazilian Samba and it was nice.
Just to know it is for added cost as it appears as a separate item in your bill .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBj2bT_NRXD8W3R_E0mCSNY-FPlWJIquWOJxEz&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"Charles Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnyXkcgy3RAI1654HPbt1rZ6zUisia7pCqDlJbMaDIITSvFO3w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Atmosphere is great! We went in a nice weather afternoon. 4/5
Service is excellent, from servers to bartenders. 5/5
Food is average 2/5. It has a good range but no premium meats.
It has sausage, pork belly, lamb leg, beef flank, beef flank steak, beef strip loin, chicken heart, bacon wrapped chicken, but no premium parts like short ribs or tenderloin. So I would only want to go again if it’s $35 per person. I don’t eat much and I don’t feel it’s cost worthy. It could be great for young adults who eats a lot.
The good part about their food and services is that they would cut the cooked portion off and go back to cook again, measuring the best time.
I enjoy the top sirloin (which I cannot cook so well at home) which is very soft and smooth. Chicken heart is tender and good as well. Another recommendation is flank steak, so tasty.
I normally enjoy strip loin (New York steak) but I don’t like theirs because the center is too chewy and the outside is well done already. They cut such a thick portion and I cannot cut or chew the size they gave me.
Another thing I wouldn’t recommend is the chickens wrapped by bacon, because the chicken breast is dry and flavorless.
Forgot to mention, my wife enjoyed the deep fried banana and pineapple, and she had to order the second basket.

Overall, great place to hangout with friends because they don’t kick people away, you can take your time to enjoy the night; but not very worthy of going with young child because you cannot take your time. It can be ideal for young adults but it can be heavy on stomach for some people.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO71AVG9xBwG2lHo8QZdN5fg_LmksBW0S3Fg_cp&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Patrik Balian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkRyDf2r0GCbtZlv3fAL2_00qnr8ZzvdLDimiVoG484QU7TX1agw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Steaks! BBQ! Chicken! Tasty Salads! Oh so fresh oh so good place for birthday's and celebrations 🍾 ✨️ 😍 💕 The culture is alive at RIO BBQ! The staff were super helpful and friendly. The value on the drink variety alone was very exotic.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfqY43TYpGYjPwCt12r_wzhCPFfbtGR57abtzP&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-10-2"},{"Name":"Bernie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPXTBFQGy4UZogf6r0hGxUGZ8fvtwePPN5iicbAtQksaWtpwOP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Festive and welcoming restaurant ambiance. As a first-timer, curiosity brings me from their ads.  It’s an amazing dining experience to enjoy an ‘Eat All You Can’ of side dishes and sizzling meat on parade brought by the server at every table. Steaks, chicken, lamb, sausage, liver etc are perfectly roasted and deliciously complemented by a buffet of a whole array of South American starters of seafood paella, salads, rice, beans, soup and a whole lot more.  My favourites are the grilled bacon-wrapped chicken and prime rib steak.  This is the perfect place for meat lovers. The day buffet price of $49/per adult is reasonable for a 2-hour dining limit.

Drinks choices include cocktails, beer and wine and are billed separately. Service is wonderful, servers are efficient and friendly.  The dining area has a nostalgic touch, well-maintained and clean.  Designated parking places are available.  Reservation is a must.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGEwxGO_TrBQEBohiMCpR8Ge6Ct3bHPznCpk6i&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-6-7"},{"Name":"Jo ?","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIH6ejfn1zBGZNLGyX14NChaJTKE5bREgcEhd70QYQAvcdrmO5=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went there on a Friday night! My friend bailed on me, so I’m all by myself.  It’s recommended by my friend, I didn’t  want to cancel.
Seated beside the window, had good view of kitchen door where foods are came out. Variety of meat I tasted : beef with different cuts are roasted to almost perfection, juicy and with  flavor! Roasted pork, sausages, chicken drum stick, shrimps!  Lamb was lacking that special flavor which lamb should have, maybe it was done to please most customers? It’s all you can eat meat with a 2-hr time frame. I saw no one exactly put a timer on you or kick you out when times up😅🤣
Self serve salad bar is great, lots of different ways to fill up a plate to your liking. There’s white rice and a big container of Paella? It was the only disappointing food for the night: was mushy and only few shrimps and mussels. It was very salty too. In contrast to what shown in their website (which was very attractive)!🥲
Kudos to all staff there, always big smiles, helpful, ready to chat if you want and leave you to your food if you prefer👍🏼
Especially great appreciation to the host Daisy, very friendly, full of energy and big smile! Can see that she was on her feet all day but still kept the vibe! 👏👏👏","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEhI2u_fl7DmTCHMgfMIYQlhsa0jA4MF3it6AV&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Paulo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJLcA_plm7bkWjnqTJrnEsHhDOSAcI0Thh-Pnw_Wtq2KxuMbiQFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Last time I went to a Brazilian all you can eat steak place was maybe 15 years ago (Samba in Vancouver).

We've seen/passed this place so many times and finally went here for my birthday today with the family.

It was good. Food was delicious, service was amazing, our server (her name was desea?) was lovely and amazing.

No complaints from us. Definitely will come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-rXlJWcW9GXrwGqkZtRBMlKPFmnmqCCpPXvD2&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-2-3"}]

It’s located within the plaza with a free indoor parking lot, albeit parking spaces are a bit narrow. Having had Mary’s Brown’s many times while in Halifax, the taste here is a little bit different. I ordered the original Big Mary sandwich and it was really lacking in flavour. The tater poutine was also sub par. The interior is nice and newly renovated.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDVt-iZIdnr_XdIZ3kvnLmSIoDT6-5l7dzsL0C&fid=0x0:0xe8c3e8868bd857ea"],"When":"2023-12-22"},{"Name":"Ali Mirzaie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8Wv-MOFd4Glu3QaeeratzZCjIe1AFnCd67BUIJJKEwhQ_KFs8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best fast food chicken sandwiches I have ever had.
No oil is dripping in a disgusting way like some other chains. I can say for sure chicken quality is much better than other chain fast foods.

Very friendly staff and spotless tables and floor

This is a new location, so I hope it stays like this.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJZPmgoLxR15F6070JG-Fg_s8KoLH0Hq4c9whm&fid=0x0:0xe8c3e8868bd857ea"],"When":"2022-3-29"},{"Name":"Joshua (ThickBurger_Bites)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbIhhMlbxk7OIMpcaP-aSx2m75kt8-mqmXoXAJQ5K99gnxiff1zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious chicken that’s done right. Ordered the the Spicy and limited time only honey BBQ chicken combo, as well as a Big Mary.

Loved the chicken. Very well coated and fried chicken, with just enough crisp and juiciness to it. Wedges were huge and delicious. We couldn’t finish it. The Big Mary was a disappointment. Slightly dry and buns were meh.

Service was okay, took about 5-10 mins for the meal to come out, but the counter staff was friendly which made the experience better.

Highly recommended. Place was very clean as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfZrrwGCkgPX4R59C5xmn1_XSp-a3uYXRAFZ9o&fid=0x0:0xe8c3e8868bd857ea"],"When":"2022-11-24"},{"Name":"Brian Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVP9Yjc0dsBKsrjvO3c6aI8GrCpYcfpgbH0b0bg7NuNHsMSIVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"To start off this review, we drove 18 kilometres just to get some chicken to eat. We were very hungry when we got there, we ordered a 13 piece combo but when we got home, we realized they gave us 12 pieces. Some people might say its not a lot but to keep into consideration we spent 58 dollars. That one piece lost us 5-6 dollars. Not very happy about the service but food tasted ok. I am going to churches or kfc next time.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Peter Ryu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIA1mPJxqbAq3sA5Yx2oELWcSP1BdJp83hRCQqxHH8j4y2zYQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for breakfast on Tuesday.
Service was good.
The food was so good. We had rice noodle w/ minced beef and parsley. Soup was hitting the spot.
Creamy seafood was good. Added some white pepper for seasoning.
The chicken steak sandwich is so good. Their chicken steak is a must try.
Great price, less than $30 for 3 items.
My gf and I left very full.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4icTkTUUv9JDkn2JtXGDZMAMx_I3hwCSyteyy&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing customer service—quick and friendly! We ordered the BBQ pork, shrimp fried rice, noodles, and meat poutine, and the generous servings lasted for days. Loved the ambiance and the extensive menu selection. Will definitely come back to try more items!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMv9VLbM7Eayn1Tn58vlSESqVHJeByNmFCEMrlt&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Johnny C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMH8aFZIGB5a7CFStbNQ6JGT0sYgxOttD7xMtIebcz8N9tnSzq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Typical Hong Kong style cafe.  Sometimes difficult to find parking because lot is share with other businesses.  Food is OK but prices have gone up a bit since the pandemic.  Food and drink arrive quickly.  There are some elbow room between tables unlike other restaurants that’s elbow to elbow.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPP9Yp6b7U-wMOA3h89pt4AgqSR2112vjBXwLXE&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Copa (cup) of disappointment…

Picking up something in the Poco area and was deciding on some Korean food or this place. In the end, decided on this place since it’s been decade or longer since I have been to this place.

Upon entering, it seems like the interior went through a bit of change and renovation. The place was pretty empty except for 3 booths seated with customers, maybe it was near closing time (1.5hrs before closing). Everything appeared to be clean throughout the restaurant with a comfortable spacing between the tables and booths.

The service was subpar from the server, maybe she was more focused on cleaning and getting off work. When the owner/ manager took over, it was a lot better and she was more polite.

Here were the food I ordered;

1. Sizzling Hot plate combo B+B (chicken steak & sausages) with borscht soup, spaghetti , cold lemon tea. The chicken was a little dry and the soup was a bit off and warm only. And the hot plate didn’t sizzle at all, maybe a 3 second frisk sound?
2. Sizzling hot place combo A+B (filet mignon & deep fried oysters) with lobster bisque, steamed rice, add lobster tail $23 extra. The filet mignon was horrible, first time ever struggling to chew a filet mignon, it was dry and didn’t taste fresh. The oysters were little midgets. The steamed rice was more like overnight rice just added a bit of water and a quick heat up by the microwave, it was dry and hard. And lastly the lobster tail was horrible; it had that bad fishy taste to it, one tiny bite from that and had to stop cause not worth food poisoning myself from it. And once again the sizzling plate wasn’t even warm!! (Facepalm) The only thing okay was the lobster bisque.

Overall, I was quite disappointed with the food. I don’t remember it being this bad? What happened? Closer to closing time and whoever the cook in the kitchen was didn’t give 2 cents about the food being served? Is it really that hard to hire a decent cook nowadays after the pandemic? And for crying out loud, it only takes 30 seconds to heat up the iron plates and how can one pawn off such a bad bowl of rice in a Chinese restaurant? I honestly would send this cook packing for retirement if working for me, definitely wouldn’t tolerate this kind of bs jeopardizing my business.

I guess I retained my good nature and composure by taking into consideration that the owner/manager was very polite and friendly; very poise and elegant with the services. I guess that’s the only good part of this experience and kept my positivity inlined. Just enjoyed a quick instant noodle when back home lol","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMcEYpyZUuanHEcQL55fa0WprgsuAX0S3V4h87&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-1-25"},{"Name":"Chang Wun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXinnRETbtdmwq0G3dzHpocXq4c0y1kT8tCLTmXT5-MPrsCx3WH9g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went back for the breakfast. There are a lots of people in the breakfast timing, the breakfast set is cost effective! Will revisit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPglBpXDu8S3-D1K1Vx9zNGj1s7HzGBk70B8aKE&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-1-4"},{"Name":"Angie L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwNm9A8ohrfnu_XFwYhP8N-ACXPuzjT8lHAp_d40ZyvMetcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is Hong Kong style fusion restaurant. The selection is quite good for anything from appetizers, steak and fries, to noodles, rice, soup, combos and beverages.

There's Western style combo that comes with soup, main and drink & Asian style combo comes with Chinese soup, main and rice, no drink. You may think the price is on the high side but you won't disappoint by the portion.

Service is not bad but when is not busy. They are not dial in.

They charge $0.50 per take out container that I have no complaint to support the environmental recycling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDjOVajotJjtkKeh90GhichQoqjYaMOeW4VKP9&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2022-1-2"},{"Name":"Nathan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6aOctokU9KmE5fwo6-6THfOky0imQyJSKP9b0jCAM3iXNSZtK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Low price, good food. What more can I say? I love Hong Kong food. Copa Cafe has good service, the waiters are attentive, friendly, and efficient.

One time, we came here late at night and they still received us and were patient despite us staying beyond their closing time. I’ll always remember the staff’s patience and hospitality.

As you can tell, I really like their noodles 😂🍜","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmD0avsIDuv7S0oR3k1m2RCOwZwtXixWPr-ed3&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2022-12-15"},{"Name":"Bespoke Happier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_JY_sOUqfgLP_sU_CBSIZzGgEmarbG08tg34uKbeN8ljU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Copa Cafe, a popular Hong Kong-style restaurant in Vancouver, is a hidden gem that I frequent when I'm in the mood for a hearty meal. Although there are only two other Hong Kong-style restaurants in Coquitlam, I prefer Copa Cafe for its extensive menu options and exceptional service compared to its competitors. If you become a member, which costs $15 per year, you can enjoy a 10% discount on all orders, which is a great deal.

One of the highlights of Copa Cafe is their breakfast menu, which boasts generous portions that won't hurt your wallet despite the current high prices. On my recent visit, I opted for the satay beef noodle and shared the cheese, spinach, and bacon omelette with my husband. We also ordered two cups of their famous Hong Kong-style milk tea. After applying the 10% membership discount, our bill was a reasonable $23 with the tip included.

Overall, we were pleased with both the quality and quantity of our breakfast. The flavors were satisfactory, and the portions were generous. Copa Cafe is a must-visit spot for anyone who loves Hong Kong-style cuisine and wants to try something new. The ambiance is cozy, and the service is top-notch, making it an ideal spot for a date or a casual gathering with friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSzLi3djIKGAYOhylqv9qdoGJbTHEE6Sfx7hU&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2023-6-17"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dahee Sim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUX9xskvqrMlPhfaEjei8fHc2AKp7yd0SfCkRSHV-khbg0nQPk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you’re into Korean food and seafood, you’ve got to check out “Bambada”! The food is super fresh, delicious, and the portions are really generous. I went there for a family gathering, and it was awesome—they’ve got menu options for both adults and kids. The staff were super friendly, and every table has a call button, so you can get service right away. They even prepped and served the lobster for us! The place is pretty spacious too, so it’s perfect if you’re dining with a group. I’m definitely going back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrT2-09aoOderpUIuvuSh-mnAyWNJrCX3VHSE8&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-12-27"},{"Name":"Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJcSTrvAkETp5GS3z8RhAHVaYouKSaPeknm0ZxbLuelbq-2-0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a great place to try Korean food in various styles. The seafood is fresh, and the food is delicious. Definitely worth a try. The service is good as well. The only thing to note is that we felt really thirsty after the meal. 😂","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTZPvyF2Tj-s66US3VDJ-XiHdiAW02TVEMXv5r&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-10-17"},{"Name":"Uucky L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVU-arllP44rVa-XSyXWrd0b-hNq7ECu4284KMlWJ8XxeidF78qg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food taste needs improvement.

Don’t come if you can’t eat spicy at all.
I ordered Beef tartar bibimbap, seafood on rice. Both of them comes with a red sauce, claimed to be non-spicy, but they are actually a little-little spicy.

The beef in Beef tartar bibimbap has some tendon (?) in it, not as soft as I think, so you need to chew a bit more than just swallow it.

Seafood on rice, even added the red sauce, is kinda bland. The rice is a pretty wet/sticky.

Fried oyster & fries only have 5 pieces of oysters.

The server is kind and nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOD199c5zDxdMM7Ds_dRLkXLpgJnCeuNirilncm&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"C L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFSCt_t74XiqlEdz6jDYOHmtwc4pgb3Fve6nsF3wEBwwz9hl0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was my first time dining at this restaurant after a strong recommendation from friends who live in the neighbourhood. The experience and food did not disappoint! We held a birthday party for 13 people, which was tricky for the layout of the tables. However, the staff were beyond accommodating and made it work. They could have used a few more servers on a busy Saturday night, but the staff were very friendly and immediately responsive whenever we asked.

We ordered a variety of dishes, including the seafood hot pot, fishcake soup and fried fish. Amazing flavours and textures, with generous portions that are ample for sharing! The fried items were light & crispy. The steaming umami soups had just the right amount of spicy kick. You won't find traditional bibimbap, japchae or pancakes because their menu heavily features innovative takes on fresh seafood - not for those with shellfish allergies! Plenty of Korean spirits to test out & quench your thirst! At first glance the prices seem high but considering that the plates can be shared, the restaurant offers great value. Will definitely be returning to try the other menu items!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7rbCmBk0xQzNEDNpQI0kMl_DuMnV3myDZBA-X&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Hyebin Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjDtbZAwmClVNZWe8in7iKPeuWFpJk3xV63n3oUYqAkU_8FufJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had seafood ttukbaegi and clam bibimbap a few weeks ago. It was a good combination with the soup and the bibimbap. Not that spicy and had perfect level of spiciness for both.
The restaurant was cozy with booths and looked good for having meal + drinking.
The service was also good. I enjoyed their tea comes with a tea pot. I will definitely visit again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAW_pwiNbZD2uo1clqF1wwWNE4bFs3c-7MXZAm&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Kwang s Koo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJFo3VGQh4dEQHrPSivYNI5XIEy1BykoaCVmEDpxsBAeHTAFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"From entering to getting our food…was about 1 hour…

The small seafood hotpot…was 90% clams and mussels…maybe 3-4 prawns couple of abalone and a few other things…I do wish there was less clams and mussels…and has some kind of fish…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzs80B65n9dqKlhGLZj9jkiEpWUFk5mHNnEtfR&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Toshiyuki Enzo Shirosaki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUD_24CqvwnpZ272t1lMbFqdPq5Yicn0-6hmHLPLDbUePqw_ASerw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had dinner at a Korean resto bambad the seafood plate was a huge portion for us four people. I like their beef tartare, very soft and tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTthRBMCpezgjbQIAqo9FQZcioh045Rh5XizB7&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came away from the restaurant with a great first impression. The food was solid, especially for the price, and the customer service was decent.

I highly recommend that you get their signature steamed seafood pot. We got a small and it was enough for the family of four. They really pack in a ton of high quality seafood in the small pot. The broth at the end is almost like a bonus and it's absolutely killer if you pair it with a shot of soju.

We also got the Korean beef tartar and they give a lot of extra things to eat with the beef like wasabi, and seaweed.

I will definitely be coming back with a designated driver next time so that I can drink.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_ntt397jhPBf8nD0ABEKZBcIgPksxdsnfOV5G&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-1-23"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Adrienne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvS1YiBi1kAYmplCTkzo9NqyjbLMViYayHxaEQA-dKyQUyyA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The atmosphere was warm and inviting, and the staff were very friendly. The food is good but we found it was a bit pricier than other places. While the staff were very kind, we didn’t get a tea refill for quite some time. Overall, the sushi was delicious and fresh, we’d come back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSzWTq2_v-EqwSj-7vY-r0yB1_p1ayedksfr-j\u0026fid=0x0:0xe5eec69b0a8befe5"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a lovely dinner at Sushi Mori. The rolls are quite big and everyone left feeling full. The atmosphere is lovely and would be nice for a romantic dinner, but three kids will take the romance out of any restaurant experience. Staff were friendly and prompt. [{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fantastic park with beautiful scenery and well-maintained grounds! There’s so much to do here — a public pool, a variety of food stalls, breweries, and excellent walking and running paths. The children will love the water park, which is a fun addition. Whether you’re looking to relax or get some exercise, this park is perfect.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOJZ6HYlwh7jIsOX-J7q9T8AOZTgs63m6QkRz_&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Mucahit Mert Alagoz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlZFzlr8OmJ6ReNSeqILjiXkPYOR-Wi6HlJhjaTTE_xGsRl7kohA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's a nice place for a walk and to get some fresh air. Even though there wasn't an event, it was hard to find parking, so we had to park along the roadside and paid 3 dollars for 1.5 hours. There was an incredibly long line for ice cream, so we decided to skip it. The coffee at the café was really good. It was a bit windy, but the smell of the ocean makes you forget everything. However, I’m giving it a minus point because drones aren’t allowed—it's a park with a drone ban","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQl3HQHOMWg2HVXbk-lGIKNaHx8k2QuhZOlz2N&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"Sathiyaseelan Suhashini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGCDhZwAvUF3Q8iMEpEx8TQCvKbwiXzYFJN0uOrenEt7v0wxGX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Breathtaking view from the dock and tranquility at its best when you walk through.

Such a great picnic spot with children and mind relaxing jogging trails.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMg_NZ675GRRHcqLBaMeyjOOsYi-AUxrsz1-8Uk&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-7-26"},{"Name":"Amy Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvtm7hBqZHDYxXgP_oxkelx2FGhwfW-EuwTv9rdyjxo-_-_8Nq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Huge park that’s great for families and going kayaking or paddle boarding. It has a nice kids’ water park and the public washrooms are clean. It lacks shaded areas and needs more parking!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhiI6LZ94pnToYVpCOBM3e65iW2XDRjjOoEWaE&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Ahsaan Rizvi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVs2v-63PhGkwL4KAVyaXYhU-lYSiC0m4y-b-I-LmqV4c_0Pmnr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Rocky Point Park in Port Moody, BC, is a delightful waterfront destination offering a variety of activities for all ages. The park features a scenic boardwalk with breathtaking views of Burrard Inlet, perfect for leisurely strolls. Families can enjoy the large playground, splash pad, and picnic areas, while fitness enthusiasts take advantage of the cycling and walking trails. The park is also home to a pier for fishing and boating, adding to its recreational appeal. On-site amenities include a skate park and an outdoor pool, enhancing its appeal for youth. Rocky Point's seasonal events and festivals create a vibrant community atmosphere. With ample parking and nearby eateries, it’s a convenient and enjoyable spot for a day out. Overall, Rocky Point Park is a versatile and vibrant destination for relaxation and recreation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3Sk3tp3LG7WznI8Cf2tN4HIdmP5fz0BEvdUt-&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A really nice park with lots to offer. There were a bunch of shady areas, a playground, a spray park, and a trail. Rocky Point Park is a great location to check out with kids, especially the spray park.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHDTrTU1duTOQHATqYGqJPWdTvY5tbWA1OEIwQ&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"wah chi yip","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKKBykHMUbkrtJ4cwRRXsjOnAzAcOzwrpq-XVjovUt6A3trFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A great park all year round but summer is the best. The breathtaking views of Burrard Inlet.
There were a long broad walk along the shore.  But I didn't go to a walk for a long time.  It's a good broad walk.
A big water park and a pool in summer. It's good for whole family spending a day there. A big long picnic shelter is at the park.
We go to the Golden Spike Days on Canada Day.  It's a really nice day for the summer concerts.  Happy see a lots of people enjoying the day with family and friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1oVa-lqvcUlLJYY8kAR8_wmyinU4Z32oA5Lx1&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Kateryna Konova","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKXpZ9gT59r8N5Phg4dth6giQHB5KWWU7de2wMWT2rICTrc-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Rocky Point Park is a fantastic spot for a day out! With beautiful views of the water, scenic walking trails, and plenty of open space, it’s perfect for all ages. There are picnic areas, a playground, and even a splash pad for kids. The pier offers a lovely view of Burrard Inlet, and you can often spot people kayaking or paddleboarding. There are also some great food options nearby, including ice cream and seafood. Highly recommended for a relaxing day in nature!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9NmXmfBtNavUi8nXnrcvzoUwUfDqtyklLFyAL&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-11-3"}]
