[{"Name":"A.J. Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I usually enjoy my visits to Mariner Brewery in Coquitlam. They offer good tasting craft beer and food. Comfortable seating with TV screens playing sports. Patio seating as well. Free parking lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZOep9PY3X_UZZI0gHiWKfkD3_Rwg7S6IlxOXy&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"shotavi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNMh1hfEFIJYaCTSLthIdHQ3TANUnSyqWujpD58h8MinLMJyw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for a casual place to grab a drink and found this spot on Google Maps.

The atmosphere was really nice and relaxing, and I thought it would be great to come here on a sunny day.

This time, I only ordered a drink without food, but next time I want to come back for some food and beer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8MebbW-WnQTRvvxKA_I0ZvOyBNH4FxfomcuPu&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"jasonbenj","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXesObwVr-MYoNivn747YIQhYO4b8Vn-9xP5t36MuM6wxR0MRI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"First time back since the renovation. Sadly, it looks like a lot of re-branding of the same old product is 90% of it. Also, they took all the good items off the menu. RIP beer cheese dip, you will be missed. Sorry to say but it's not for me anymore. Also, $13 25 flight before tax !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOql9qRevUlia8U9C-dRW3PT6r5a5AmKlZ5qwHk&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Marisa Lenarduzzi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIbCzpGYeIKBI2SunoaFci_IoZvVVnbxBDnsfb3PLewJQAy3A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great beers and great food for a brewery as well. We got the fries with mango chipotle and it was delicious! There’s also a great atmosphere inside - not too loud, good lighting and very clean. Would go again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7VsLepap0KHEDl1zc5eEsDCQ9ndL4l7M2shto&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Christina Faminoff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX12CPz5calL7TtQ0KnMyeMWTusgq3nB56xjWsl60LKS9agnIFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just had the burger of the month, the Fall Forage smash with the falafel patty, and a stout. Both were awesome. Falafel was super fresh and tasty. I've tried most of their beers, and kombucha, and I appreciate that they are all really different, and don't all just taste like hops. Love that they added a food menu! Nice to be able to get good hot food instead of just snacks, like a lot of breweries. This is one of my favourite places. Would recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi9KQYgc3UAPTrvyVhcEulEHKDPEevANrCc4rQ&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Came to this brewery with a meetup group and it was an on experience. There were limited non-alcoholic drinks on the menu, but they had four different craft sodas. I tried the cherry cola craft soda, the taste was interesting, but it wasn’t great, a bit flat. I also tried the pretzel and they were very generous with the mustard, but it was overall still very bland and got too cold too quickly. It’s a nice space to hang out and it can get busy even on weekday evenings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5hAZODlvyOhf9B5lJi8jBxhRFGkFm5uo_rePD&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2023-12-21"},{"Name":"Lauren St John","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWi3pWsd_jh8y8V1Pl7XbMiNRgCVHq-YYCdAOx_KkkOFRnXREk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Pass on this one. Unless you're a beer and ale aficionado, keep going. Sorely disappointed in the food. We heard it had improved with new owners but it's obvious that more changes are needed. They charge $17 (plus tax and tip) for 8 chicken wings. That's outrageous. We tried the Jamaican patties and they were ok. The venue is cozy with more outside seating than inside. The service is "meh." The beer was average. There's not a lot for non-alcoholic beverages. The whole experience left us nonplussed. We will not go back or recommend it.  We spent $65 for 2 beers, 8 wings, a can of ginger ale and 2 Jamaican patties. And the pressure to tip 20% even though there's no table service, left us perplexed!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_Ekb1Paet7mkMRPuwFGpkIuDRB9sqyDH14sUc&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2023-9-8"},{"Name":"E. C Arteaga G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxwN6PAknbpzp4-FRd4QkWYRhq1QUPT2iG2_oEOzRgEc5F0GVH1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I was waiting for the perfect opportunity to go try this local brewery and today was the day. We were greeted by our server who was kind and knowledgeable about their beers.  They recommended the Blonde Ale ( Low Gravity Mango) super delicious. But, the food was not what we expected. The fries tasted bland and raw. It tasted like everything was made in an air fryer. The sliders we had were bland and the buns were not toasted. The chicken wings were a hit and miss. Some where nice and fell off the bone and others where hard as a rock. I would definitely try this place again because the beer is their saving grace but I will double think about ordering food again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPN8xjotriAojNGVe5wIIRD29aZaMWIHah5pNDd&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2022-3-30"}]

[{"Name":"Andy Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWooGSzw1FKhky_mrftz_qLp6fsBzAqJ7JcjT2pde1tUMh4Y9hx8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Shrinkflation and inflation.

Dishes taste fine but the prices are going up and the portion seems shrinking as well.
I ordered to pick up some dishes. $6.25 for 6 pieces of small spicy salmon roles.
Maybe I’m out of touch these days. $32.25 for takeouts does not go very far these days I guess.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHN74PVQXn88pZBDO_WRQkASFUILQKLltLDqPH&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Mohammad Tabesh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjokXICqa-0DdrHKHh0Wt3GGaHTAC4RDuOqk22M3flRzjmqoKo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good quality food for the price with a nice variety, really quick service and convenient location inside the mall. It's a budget place with disposable plates and chopsticks. Miso soup was plain but tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPL_iRBW2adsUvuZctF90SuqpluYd65jND4m7dv&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My partner works in the mall and grabs lunch here three times a week, especially loving the teriyaki. I had the chance to try the unagi oshi sushi, and it was delicious! The creamy prawn tempura was a fantastic bonus, making the meal even more delightful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6on5Y08KZ9VAGnb-Q10oavACH62ly3bxzrkNn&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Armin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVKfPvn-jqW8hTOlU1VeElw6vFvjre9PTWSba_96soEJn4hAFVjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good Sushi for being in the mall! Lots of options to pick and you can order online so you don't have to wait!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5ux3twBDePDGec0k-4hwPkab1Rd92kFjUs18y&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"I D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJePVcTLvMpAzx-nv1Jiy6G3BSAT8AXC96M8bp3iDt95AnsQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I wish Coquitlam Centre has better eateries. I ordered the Beef Bento. Price was okay, but the portions were not big. For $15, I only got 4 pieces of California roll instead the standard 6 pieces. I was surprised by the quantity of the beef. It was more than I expected but the beef quality was quite poor. There was also not a lot of rice. Salad was fresh. Service was quick and friendly. It's a small place, and I couldn't find a place to sit, so I had the food to go. I forgot to ask for napkins :(","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexis Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4lll3FSw4DuoAXTTSQfNVd2BMOvLsNf0gg2O5LBY3etPVgQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love the prawn tempura and miso soup. For mall sushi, this place is consistently great! I enjoy eating here and will always return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEOr8Ou4QsT2tC4bIAmYmBwtpMCrNDvv-oKLq1&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-1-14"},{"Name":"K S H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUpfuZFJ8RwqNTmsEi_Ve_L99RruCBycZdik5Nf-7YZZhK-hRF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the Best Sushi places in Coquitlam and very conveniently located in the mall.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtjlH9F0FcLxhh45QyYB26pLJ8aF_QRpWZxyIU&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"Johnny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvkqlZ5wz-o7qQiMAPvxq4Uq26umX4_opBke6CDrVfkbGhCeuLaA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My first time at Togo Sushi was excellent. With exceptional service by the lady employee, I ordered the teriyaki bento box, and I opted for chicken rather than beef. The teriyaki bento box comes with California rolls, salad, gyoza, and miso soup. The teriyaki chicken was, to be honest, disappointing, which I was not expecting. I also ordered yam rolls, which I loved since I love sweet potatoes. Would I go back? Likely not.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We finally discovered the best KBBQ in Coquitlam at Galbi! After trying several spots, this is the only place that truly got my partner excited about KBBQ. What sets Galbi apart is their focus on the quality of the meat rather than just the side dishes—a huge plus in our book.

They handled our reservation quickly, and we were fortunate to snag a table before it got really busy. While the space is a bit cozy, the meal was absolutely fantastic. The marinated beef short ribs were so irresistible that we ended up ordering extra.

We were expecting the bill to be around $200, but were pleasantly surprised when it came out $60 cheaper—even with the tip included. I’m definitely bringing my friends here next time. Can’t wait to come back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtXU7g1Mdshu7JLv6kgKpUYZu5LSk1yfwe--bA&fid=0x0:0x3acdae584ead321a"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Suzanne Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVA92S6YKukSMnbRa5H7tG8jeNNTYeIVRPnSfmNiCXXXyAauEzN0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here on a Thursday evening and thankfully we came early! The place filled up pretty quickly around 7pm. We ordered the fresh beef ribs, pork jowl, and pork belly with skin on (thick cut). Prices are reasonable for the quality of meat and quantity (each portion is by weight). I found the soybean paste soup very salty, but once diluted it was quite tasty! Enjoyed the salad and sides, but they charge for extra side dishes and restrict you to 3 pieces of romaine lettuce per meat order (which seems a bit stingy for a small side item). There was also dirt on the lettuce, which they washed off and returned to us... Rice is ordered on the side for $2 each.

Overall a clean storefront with friendly staff, fresh quality ingredients, and a fun no-frills kbbq experience! We spent around $100 for 3 people.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMolYBIiES1jj5IW8KrAnPCgFR-qT5oYoTiMa20&fid=0x0:0x3acdae584ead321a"],"When":"2023-11-3"},{"Name":"MAY 매이 Elford","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxJVIiA7BVVmzUGqT6sRzP7-hCdYJttIOnYMeIvWOWZPmq7cr7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A Saturday evening out with my friends. 4 of us ended up at Galbi. We ordered the pork belly with skin on, Galbi, and the cold noodle. Everything was delicious… the bean paste soup was so yummy.
They gave us side dishes, but to add more, there is an extra fee.
Service was great and there have a lot of parking. Definitely worth going!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOiNt4K-oH50HrFkg3LuUdGSxwY6y2kJMYXzNyD&fid=0x0:0x3acdae584ead321a"],"When":"2023-4-28"},{"Name":"Ananda Enkhtur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkkmVVa6j0bCuttopPInRikVrpr7LXYSHoZtWk3dhng__J_lZi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tried this place the other day and it was pretty good! Not many items on the menu that you can choose from but overall the taste was delicious. Especially the red bean soup and the corn cheese was so good. Like many Korean restaurants there are variety of side dishes that come with the meal and the portions for each one was generous too! Would recommend to come as a big group tho!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJ-sZtMzSf8pafLObOPwMYuYYoPalr6VIO6Vud&fid=0x0:0x3acdae584ead321a"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Tried this place out for the first time. We had the marinated beef and pork short ribs. The beef was tasty but the pork was just okay. I had a few pieces of the beef that were hard and fatty. The portion size for the meat was average. The soup appetizer, kimchi, and pickled raddish were good. They provided a pitcher of water, no complimentary tea offered.

The selection on the menu is minimal.

Service was average. We had to wave over to the waiters every time we needed something. They did not come up to us and ask how things were after they gave us our food.

Overall, the food was decent but I wouldn't come back when there are other Korean BBQ restaurants with more selection.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPb8x1RQYXa6xENsHZCT5yvKAqEx9VI05wYGrBK&fid=0x0:0x3acdae584ead321a"],"When":"2022-12-11"},{"Name":"Molly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLxkBBeHfwDYZEHKteGzubNOwVdGJVg2Kn4pysUcR2QBA2w0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Jessi was my server tonight she was very friendly and attentive. 5 stars for my experience. Food was great. The free soup was so good I purchased another one! They didn't seem to have the salt soya sauce dip tray that you get in other places. Maybe you have to ask for it? I don't care for it I don't add extra stuff to my meat. I got the short ribs and the prime beef so good!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"S C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVumoVlQ2Nr7knqW9lb01ghVZite-FLKkjhE2dVSofQsuYeSfVW=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Galbi is my best place for Korean BBQ in Vancouver. The meats were fresh, tender and nicely marbled also marinated short ribs were well seasoned. Excellent service and reasonable price. I usually visit 1-2times a week. Try this place if you are meat lover!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4RXzzsu5isoPwissTXgbEx26fjigui8uk6uai&fid=0x0:0x3acdae584ead321a"],"When":"2023-2-28"},{"Name":"Hwa D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwQyjGi41SNIX6tVkw-8BfQdSHpbL_wDTFcZShwlM2dHZ3e1AW_w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited this restaurant and was thoroughly impressed. The marinated beef short ribs were absolutely delicious.
What made the experience even more enjoyable was the exceptional service. The staff were incredibly friendly and attentive, ensuring that our dining experience was delightful from start to finish. I highly recommend this restaurant","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOklX-zzm88iNsKQfia31-tC_DHWRFqVfVdVqKY&fid=0x0:0x3acdae584ead321a"],"When":"2024-3-17"}]

[{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I ordered buffalo, cheddar, and salt and pepper wings. They were decent, but nothing out of the ordinary. However, I really enjoyed the cheddar flavor—it was new to me and definitely stood out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTWIC6VC49TZUu9GZ3GYVoFbCoWrxDwMHlARnl&fid=0x0:0xb5bfb1a4bfbe095a"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Sam wins Wells","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNKFEGfgiabHv5G1ZHjQRt6ipm1Q83CrIF-CqaqVVHOkCl5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down, these are the BEST chicken wings I’ve ever had. From the moment I took my first bite, I knew I was experiencing something special. The wings were perfectly crispy on the outside, juicy and tender on the inside, and packed with flavor in every bite. The seasoning was spot-on—bold, balanced, and absolutely mouthwatering. I’ve had wings at a lot of places, but nothing even comes close to the perfection of these. If you're looking for the best wings, stop searching. This place is IT. Simply the best!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXoz-baxNsPwu7qynyE9dLI-RMCVYrLt2nqwVE&fid=0x0:0xb5bfb1a4bfbe095a"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Kim Cuenca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjaWn84n5WkNIiuTVVUDNGG11BZFZ9bDL7ozRG9Qhg3XlrHg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is so good. The wings are amazing it makes me crave more. The burger that I ordered is perfect for my taste!

Our server, Ange, was so accommodating, attentive and friendly. She helped us with everything and helped us with everything we need. We were satisfied and happy with our visit here at Wings Port Moody because of the food, the service and the place was clean and cozy.

Thank you, Ange for the amazing service!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGjptqH3FdoeLfdSjPWQygL5KEsM_ui4pClg77BekGUD0E-Q_8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food took a while to reach our table. Except for Buffalo and Jamaican wings, all the other options in wings are just dull, but I'd recommend Buffalo and Jamaican wings. Tacos were the highlight of the day. They were out of a few drinks and dips on Saturday. Would still recommend it for Bobby Wings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDaEmmsxSYTd0KqHG1GGK0aJGND6mrDEPlEcUP&fid=0x0:0xb5bfb1a4bfbe095a"],"When":"2024-4-25"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's surprisingly spacious once you're inside and they have everything you can ask for in a restaurant with a bar, dance floor, live music, and multiple TVs for your favourite game.

The servers are all very friendly and accommodating and the food is about what you would expect from Wings. It's nothing to write home about, but you don't always go in for the food.

I love their beers on tap, cheap wings on Wednesdays, and the electrifying atmosphere on important game nights with friends and family! It's a place that I will be coming back to every now and then.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbZhiNL7Ym7AJ4ZwM2Khlle_b114KNn5wnJGGb&fid=0x0:0xb5bfb1a4bfbe095a"],"When":"2024-1-22"},{"Name":"Heather Bain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGP_U6RMLGGjNkwmYwdhJeH4dP9HKVXM2EwtwgIA4QjU4ZDIk2Yw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I would like to give them a better review but I am not.  Was a last minute change in a freinds bday party. Glad they could accommodate on short notice that is the one positive thing. But it was a Saturday night and busy of course, and they were short staffed. Drinks were mediocre which is a personal opinion. Food was good.  As in short staffed they service was a bit slower than usual. When I am comparing to other Wings locations I've been to before.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marge F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLj5_g_9SDwBb15hkYb6s_LfRvp-45OrDfymdcrjkixQvwaBw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So nice to come to a place with the friendliest server I’ve ever had! Lizzie was exceptionally attentive and was extremely helpful as we tried to decide on our dishes and drinks. We tend to take a while before choosing, and she was really patient. The food was great! We had the Texas fries, and they were yummy and filling. The bartender had a smile on his face the whole time we were there, too. Great job all around to the server, bartender, and kitchen!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shane Mccardle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9o-BfnrXqKRNH6NQDfADrksnTzHWsbz6WF8sXz3aqRfIeh0Fp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great flavour choices of wings.
The wings were average, though. I would hope that a place known for wings would have different wings other than the standard kind found elsewhere $18.5  per order for average is tough to swallow.  Service was great for our party of 25 to 30 people, and the server hustled and did great and was very pleasant and same as the food runner.","Images":null,"When":""}]

The chicken burrito had tons of meat and full of flavour with decent portions and price. The server was also very friendly!

I recommend this place if you're looking for a good burrito/taco restaurant in Port Moody area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYLbd8uuN-9MGU07dEVD0rf3wYj7ttpeGaHC0S&fid=0x0:0x3576f9f5b5a0f06c"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Herbert Camat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKXSkcN5npL56jCqrImwFWlxlBsiSCmQ0Pl7fUB01TSYknRkt_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best Mexican food in the greater Vancouver area, in Port Moody! I had the guac and salsa with chips, so good! The tacos were divine and delicious!!! But for me, the highlight is definitely was the pork belly bowl! The flavours came together for a great blend into a delicious circus!!! And the margaritas and cocktails they have were also extremely good!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmkU41lBpiL-0cbvA0PS4ROXJFJWzPXMq0N4Qi&fid=0x0:0x3576f9f5b5a0f06c"],"When":"2024-5-11"},{"Name":"liberty facundo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNBp5rH1To4BVHWq1Mfj3iKJNDPtZ8CbWa3yq0RypDCjJicJtkRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried this place for some quick take out tacos and the place was so nice. The tacos that we ordered tasted really good, the fave is the Korean bbq pork taco. Will definitely come back to eat in next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAM89PY2rckTvUkNSWLpXt6Vk2FR_ssdYMX1hc&fid=0x0:0x3576f9f5b5a0f06c"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"George Says","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXohTUDS1Hme-40_fBadV_6ZJOt8nYejw_acqYyifv5Fy1T5nx77A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food!

I am for Mexico and I can honestly say that the way they play with the fusion of flavors in this kitchen is amazing.

Super tasty tacos
Great Torta
The sauces are delicious

The service is good although sometimes I think they are short staff for the amount of customers there are.

I would just like to mention one thing, I have been to this place about 10 times, my experience has always been good, but this last time as we had no reservation they put us on the waiting list (which is completely fair) but they made us wait almost 50 minutes, and they seated us at the table that was available when I arrived to ask.  In fact there were a total of 5 tables available, I never understood why they couldn't seat us from the beginning.

We waited 50 minutes in front of the door and the tables I saw were never used 🤪.

Greetings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwUKZ3pbZedCpK1bDRuB7p_smLnp3LxxZgdw-7&fid=0x0:0x3576f9f5b5a0f06c"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Colton Wilson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9J-0Vx6x8cF5YVvJZsNgZ_ehNWjBzDwqwuFlN_lt9-EfdsJIu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hard to find a critique about Taps and Tacos. Service was amazing and fast. Food came out quick and was fresh and full of flavour. The menu has lots of mouthwatering options that makes you want to order it all.. the drink menu has great local beers from surrounding brewery’s and a very impressive cocktail menu with lots of Mexican inspired drinks. My favourite Mexican street taco restaurant and my favourite restaurant in Port Moody.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPC1xxxC5kQhrk4Y6iodn9J5QJTzJbEi_zlfm62&fid=0x0:0x3576f9f5b5a0f06c"],"When":"2023-6-5"},{"Name":"Ava Quinn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMU8VO2fB7cXmNzEfci_rgw-GMvyqSUc989asfRnFG0burVgIH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Got the tacos here one day and the bowls another. Everything we ordered was amazing.

Atmosphere was upbeat and cool with all the glass. The music was insanely loud both days we got dinner though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOe5mxP_vYLi5Nmvc_pUWu7JOVUdEKAsEpW_2UW&fid=0x0:0x3576f9f5b5a0f06c"],"When":"2024-5-14"}]

[{"Name":"Avis Woo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXh4Pb-SJt2DTMUggN2-tIRxEo8pAErRU5SI_TxM4gC-gvdVBym=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great movements my daughter and I spent here with great coffee, great hot chocolate, yummy coffee cake, wheat-free brownie and banana cake while waiting for doctor's call nearby from Port Moody Emergency Care Centre with 5 minutes walking distance! ❤️❤️👍👍🎄🎄","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFgWyPt5lRnzUcbw2ll9HyCR5HS5p4CRG77Ucm&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute cozy cafe for drinks and tiny bites. It wasn’t busy when we went on a Friday afternoon so luckily we were able to get seats and sit for a while. The interior is woody and there is a clear area to stand for ordering and waiting on your orders. There were signs posted that says it is a laptop free environment on weekends as well as 90 minute seating during busy times which are reasonable. Drinks are tasty but I don’t believe the hot chocolate was made with real chocolate. Street parking only.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFwCsN9D9Rwioy9lI2Tv-iUgM1vRQ3eyakyzJa&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Line Rejmers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0T1dg6KY3grV8k0ZQ4Ky-7ZoPCjPwiJ6glB3_yFoGHY2ex87HvQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely lovely. The coffee is some of the best I’ve ever tasted (highly recommend a ‘Spanish latte with a hint of orange’ or a ‘Sam Jackson’). Furthermore, the ‘Divano breakfast sandwich’ is super delicious. The location is in a lovely quiet area, and the atmosphere is super cozy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOABKnA-dMKT-TcN2BnYx_cgmIF_gKL8ztvTJ0U&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2024-8-11"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Love the coffee, food and service. Get the peanut butter cookie if you can. Would be even better with some comfortable seating, I’m not a fan of hard wooden chairs. Decent selection of vegetarian options, and lots for breakfast, lunch, or snack. Great espresso and interesting seasonal drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP778HgN8KVCPWAjlok8Bp_2AfVL6wnYIbSACCu&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2023-12-2"},{"Name":"Sunflower T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIxJjMmucwwDA4tlzDMS42ioEJCCaNp6pZeLU1uC3v2pVpwoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Since they close quite early (5p.m., which is a pity for no outdoor coffee in summer late afternoons!), we were politely asked if we would take paper cups when we arrived at around 4:30p.m. Although it would be nicer to use mugs, we had no choice but to forget environmental concerns for once! The cappucino was good though, so was the banana cake!

Next time we would arrive earlier to enjoy the atmosphere, the decor and relax more! (lap-top free on weekends!! And 90 min slot on busy hours!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfwJ8AOg1d5gQzOmY5tl7hMIeNZXllNvqtGMwf&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2024-5-2"},{"Name":"Arjun Tyagi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWopm7CB27Brsn2nZf_ZcGMYA1rC2xZn0gFS2Ev_B4zUk8mX8MoIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Honestly one of the best latte’s I’ve had in ages in BC. This took me back to my recent trip to Melbourne, Australia and their world famous coffee culture. Grabbed a to go latte in a rush this morning so no opportunity to take pics (beyond the cup with me) of the establishment but it was well laid out with a great coffee house feel and plenty of seating both inside and out. They also had a wide assortment of pastries and food items in general which all looked delicious, I will definitely be back and update the review with more pictures accordingly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_bV1SFQwNmBHl5YL-hQ4034IJLDttEoYYbnnX&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2024-4-18"},{"Name":"Pradyumna Gujjar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVHYwZPoeWTWb_r-Pj3URXZmwvjMuE8IJLkPSR4xqAVv86CR0HjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The ambience is great! The staff are warm and welcoming! They pride themselves on their coffee and I can see why because they taste good.
The let down for me was the chicken wrap. It was a bit undercooked and the sausage wasn’t that great!
I had a Spanish coffee and a spiced pumpkin latte, both of which were great!
The balance of the spices and the flavors were great and the pricing was reasonable.
All in all, would definitely recommend it for the coffee but might have to visit again to speak for the food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTJ1TZNjysDMIbZ18szw3LHfxb-VHSbGsxZzhZ&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2023-9-18"},{"Name":"Jay P (JP)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWelLAg3J6-KSk1lMcsa257JZB2pUVD6ykaC4OdY8owoc_MOJyN0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Divano offers a charming and relaxed environment that’s perfect for working or unwinding. The decor is modern yet cozy, with plenty of plants and comfortable chairs. I tried their iced latte, and it was wonderfully refreshing and well-balanced. The shop also offers a variety of specialty teas and vegan options, which is a nice touch. The only downside is that the Wi-Fi can be a bit spotty, which might be a concern if you plan to work here for an extended period. Otherwise, it’s a delightful place to enjoy a cup of coffee.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"A.J. Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of Port Moody's Donair shops. Mega Donair has been here for years and I like that they actually make fresh bread (pita) for the donairs by order. Fresh and tasty every time I visit. Air conditioned and comfortable seating inside.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYOnB6DnVivYV3LB4cEUVUQQCClxRazx0z9dRK&fid=0x0:0x5e0681c0310f59d8"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Negin Modir","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJIxLrD9MaLLUXrRzDgC04oGs7WW9wweZNAc7nLEJ1sx6y-ew=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this place!! the food is always so delicious and the lamb is super tender. Portions are huge and I believe its the best donair in the city with tons of flavor. The customer service is  also TOP notch! you must try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNO3FnCInyJErXqJ_oaqlbcexkhaLFcFzxlbDvP&fid=0x0:0x5e0681c0310f59d8"],"When":"2024-12-3"},{"Name":"Al So","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLumQHIv-5W9wXPr4ZbA1zWCVnPk2w1Kc3bjsO93-VMG-v7JQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you haven’t been to Mega Donair  in Port Moody, you’re missing out! This place is like the Aladdin's cave of donairs, filled with treasures of flavor and freshness. Very yellowly inside...

First off, the pita bread here is so fresh, you’d think they had a team of genies in the back, flattening and heating it up right before your eyes. Seriously, watching them work the dough in the machine and then heating up on the stove like watching an ancient Middle Eastern cooking show – mesmerizing!

Now, let's talk about the donairs themselves. These bad boys are stuffed with ingredients so fresh, they might as well have been plucked from the Garden of Eden. Each bite is a flavor explosion that’ll have you saying, “Open sesame!” for more. And the size? Let’s just say, Ali Baba would need more than 40 thieves to finish one of these beasts! We got the chicken 🍗 one, and was pleasantly satisfied after.

Sure, Mega Donair might not be the cheapest eatery in the souk, but with the quality and freshness of their ingredients, plus the friendliness of the staff, it’s worth every dinar. The service is as warm as a Middle Eastern bazaar, and the flavors will take your taste buds on a magic carpet ride.

So, if you’re in Port Moody and craving a donair that’s fit for a king, head over to Mega Donair.  Your taste buds will be belly dancing with joy!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgrkhj5xVUjAfVjhzyVEHRmpAEg6bBJIxdkiZD&fid=0x0:0x5e0681c0310f59d8"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"James Tasker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9NiNIaLm_vJXAOyrHHjnqFvKsK-Y4c4_NtjLMC68D0-TJQg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Honestly, I’ve had loads of Donairs from everywhere in the province. The freshness, friendly customer service, and inviting atmosphere make Mega Donair an All-Star Donair. This family run business provides great portion sizes while yielding affordable prices. Would recommend to anybody in Metro Vancouver to come try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPG0C_Tt8T2WntUVhQQVgPq1svg_98gWMqeYBnL&fid=0x0:0x5e0681c0310f59d8"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Robert Horne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWjh3uBuk3kJPg-hc-U_wrcI93lKxaVucpTodap5gNstb2Dhe87Uw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best donairs I've had in Canada 🇨🇦. Great flavor and fresh ingredients.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWRunvmCf7c7N3nqd-amQ-qJNq4kYsHSI1bcpG&fid=0x0:0x5e0681c0310f59d8"],"When":"2022-11-29"},{"Name":"Aydean Mehri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK7vsez26Z2HmbRPWHEjpz0jN2LhiuT-gyNLWVk7RTpbV3-1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I heard so much and I never tried it until today while at work

It was so authentic so good so homie, home made bread, Baklava.

Absolutely love it can’t wait to go back","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Luke Lindenbach","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAnciz0S6b-f06TL37KstoBSdDYL6OxSrD4eSrdLWrj3F3qg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We tried the Lebanese Mega Donair. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Mussaab M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6kTvFP9CF7bDxCUlKrtsJlOeaqA94_Z43EBsk5pA3jn_VnAM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My Favorite Kimbap Spot in Vancouver!

I’ve been coming to Illo Kimbap Cafe since they opened earlier this year, and it’s quickly become one of my go-to spots. We’ve also had Illo cater two events at university for around 50 people, and they were amazing both times. The kimbap platters were fresh, beautifully presented, and a hit with everyone. I also love how they introduce seasonal items—recently, they added a Lobster Kimbap, which was unique and absolutely delicious.

Illo offers a wide variety of kimbap, with plenty of meat and non-meat options to accommodate different dietary preferences. Some of my personal favorites are the Illo/Skinny Elephant Kimbap, Natto Roo, and Soy Salmon Kimbap, but honestly, you can’t go wrong with anything. They even include estimated calories and feature healthy ingredients (plus keto options), making it easy to enjoy without straying from your diet.

Outside of kimbap, their Tteokbokki, sandwiches, and tiramisu desserts are also worth trying. The Egg Sandwich, in particular, is super filling and uniquely prepared.

It’s a takeout-only spot, and the portions are very generous for the price, making it both convenient and great value. On top of that, the family and employees who run Illo are incredibly nice—they’re always welcoming and happy to explain menu items or recommend new things to try.

I highly recommend giving this a try if you’re in the area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0HmzBxFauXPgT48gHe6W5gga3TTaAChqUUAk&fid=0x0:0x851307994e80a3c"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Susy S.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOXFRmPNhvtrh6EsN703ph8OLmY1L5EksqjupPcRZsoEiF39uMiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently ordered a catering order from Illo and was so happy with my experience. They were able to provide me with suggestions for what Kimbap would be best for my event and was able to keep vegetarian options separate. I highly recommend the Doo-Chi Kimbap. It's fantastic. I love the white kimchi.

I'll definitely be back, just for single orders!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTTt9FR4cSRTSDodx0xsn-dO-7gfwU1C29LZSZ&fid=0x0:0x851307994e80a3c"],"When":"2024-12-23"},{"Name":"jihee jeong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHxb2sdK9_X6jNUfswbQw-TBkmnv9CBuQknOyBW1iSxkg7Ng=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We heard many good things about illo kimbap cafe, so my husband and I visited over the weekend. We tried kimbap (Chichi kimbap, Spicy pork kimbap), sandwiches (Egg salad, Strawberry & mango) and juices (Mango, Blueberry). Illo Kimbap cafe is now our new favourite Kimbap place to go. Here is why:

1. Kimbap
It was one of the best kimbaps I've ever had, including the ones I had in Korea. Spicy pork kimbap is full of flavour. I highly recommend drizzling a bit of ssamjang sauce as it enhances the flavour even more. Then the Chichi kimbap was a refreshing change. Its light and crisp flavours were a welcome addition to the meal. Perfect combination.

Kimbap is usually heavy on carbs. But Illo's kimbap is nutritionally well-balanced. Every piece was so big and filling, yet I didn't feel heavy or bloated afterwards. They do not save on great ingredients nor compromise quality. 200% recommended.

2. Sando (sandwich)
As soon as my husband and I had our first bite of the Strawberry and mango sando, we were like, wow. First, the cream was pleasantly sweet. I didn't know cream could be so refreshing and light! It is not overly sweet, not greasy, and has no artificial flavour. Also, fruits are all the way from the top to the bottom of the sandwich. The egg sandwich was creamy and flavorful. It tastes like a healthy homemade sandwich, full of flavour without being heavy on mayonnaise. I loved the egg in the middle.

3. Service
From the server to the kitchen team, everyone was welcoming and friendly. They kindly explain the ingredients and share recommendations if you are not familiar with the menus.

4. Price
Some people say it is pricey for kimbap. But I think it is super reasonable. Once you see the size & quality of Illo Kimbap and taste them, it is totally worth it and not expensive at all.

5. Overall
I could feel the Illo team was dedicated to serving a healthy and tasty meal. They chose fresh ingredients, and I could taste the difference. I am definitely coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAgBYqh9ljnXRrca5jRn5dJtlk3ltsr9BbbJEx&fid=0x0:0x851307994e80a3c"],"When":"2024-6-19"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Each kimbap roll only has 5 kimbaps but don’t let that fool you! There is plenty of kimbap considering how much filling they cramp in the seaweed. We liked the Illo kimbap and the soy salmon kimbap.

The restaurant itself is quite small so I think people generally get them to go. But the interior is still very clean and cute.

I highly recommend if you want to try some Korean style kimbap with a twist!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7OOC9IsKtU5L_Gqcf5p9ajMknGBFMsEIakcNH&fid=0x0:0x851307994e80a3c"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Victoria Moon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI7IdGSmon5miLT6es0cCEjVXddJnr6Xmq4XEJ41ZRqQbDFlr8F=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pro-tip: if you have kids or prefer smaller bite-size kimbaps, you can request that when you order. I just learnt that today so the pictures don’t show the mini sizes, but I will be requesting that in the future.

The new soba kimbap with the wasabi mayo sauce it comes with is a new favourite in my family. The sauce is made with real wasabi and the kimbap is such a refreshing summer treat! The chi chi kimbap with the white kimchi is also divineeee.

I love how versatile these kimbaps are for whichever meal you want to eat it for. Also, speaking as a Korean who grew up eating homemade kimbap, this is hands down, my favourite kimbap spot in all of Metro Vancouver.

It’s not your typical kimbap rolls, but you can tell each roll was thoughtfully crafted. I personally love how there are sauce pairings, keto options, and various menu items to choose from. All fresh and delicious ingredients that make your body actually feel fueled and good afterwards.

I’ve gone in multiple times for takeout and ordered off uber eats, and I recommend going in person if you can to check out the cute space and to say hi to the lovely owner.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBYdPb-e9LyW0JKGuhxVoAMl567e2BXe7xnbms&fid=0x0:0x851307994e80a3c"],"When":"2024-6-28"},{"Name":"Sue K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJdh-K_Uu9TqAPplulx4NcxEW7aCsRZEDC_u-73Uvc9VOCXgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Decided to write the review while we're craving for their kimbap already. We stumbled upon this place yesterday while en route out of town and decided to give it a try — and we’re so glad we did! The kimbap here is absolutely delicious, made with super fresh ingredients, and the place seemed spotless, which really stood out to us.

We ordered Tteokbokki, Natto Roo kimbap, Chichi kimbap, and Skinny Elephant kimbap. Every kimbap was bursting with flavor, and the quality of the ingredients really made a difference. The Skinny Elephant kimbap was so refreshing — my personal favorite (if you love salad, you haveeee to try!). My husband couldn't get enough of the Chichi kimbap. We also tried their kimchi soup, and immediately thought this is perfect for cold days.

Although there's no dining area, this is the ideal spot for takeout. We're already countjng down the days until we're back in Vancouver to grab more.

--
Additionally tried their Lobster kimbap, Lemon Basil Chicken kimbap, Spicy Beef soup, and Miso soup. Fresh, Tasty, and Excelllleeeeent as ever!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyGKQcuAUnsdCHEDyUVIpbnxwWmRa2eOJqRrgn&fid=0x0:0x851307994e80a3c"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"candy L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgq2OgnXFRsC1icGye-CTgUf_6kEV0cPoOgzI7ANMes5eDT-Xz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I discovered this place on Instagram and became very interested in trying their creative sushi made with healthier ingredients. However, the location is really far, but I finally had the chance to check it out today. The store is very small and mainly offers takeout. The colorful sushi and sandwiches displayed inside were so appealing that I didn’t know what to choose. In the end, I decided to get the SKINNY ELEPHANT KIMBAP, SOBA KIMBAP, ANGRY MOM’s Kimbap and illo egg mania sandwic and We took our food to the park to enjoy, and each item was light, fresh, and satisfying. I really hope they open a store in Vancouver so I can eat there more often.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOC_IxqsdewRBrncTxhHrq9ETtzEZOZXjFUERA0&fid=0x0:0x851307994e80a3c"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I'm thrilled to see a new food spot stir up some excitement in the Burquitlam neighborhood, and I'm jumping right in with their top-notch kimbap offerings. With its ingenious kimchi wrap, the Chichi kimbap is a brilliant twist on a classic and is my absolute favorite. Frankly, I'd be happy if they wrapped all their kimbap in kimchi! The lemon basil chicken sandwich also scored high for being delicious and hearty. However, the mango-strawberry sandwich didn't quite make the mark. It lacked both in taste and seemed a tad pricey for what it offered. Maybe a flakier pastry, like a croissant, could have saved it. Despite this, I'm eager to see this place thrive, and you can bet I'll be back for more of that kimbap.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGjOMRynIvjHhgUcNWW4MskfDzJ4K3nd7Hiazm&fid=0x0:0x851307994e80a3c"],"When":"2024-7-7"}]

They are quite well established in pubs and liquor stores across the Lower Mainland. Although availability varies, most of the time, you can find brews on tap that are on the stronger side when it comes to flavor and alcohol content, which is absolutely fine with me. Space Armadillo DIPA and Juice+Cintra IPA are my all-time favorites. Their taproom is of a decent size, but not too big, and the staff is friendly and helpful. Also, there is always some sort of a food truck right in front of the brewery, so food is not a problem.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQsS4yvRNopVpxl8xx1LsYXer_yFGhILuRBa0A&fid=0x0:0xb1d5a4cd24e4928"],"When":"2021-3-10"},{"Name":"Steve Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmgrmzSyB3CC_qWamR3pXmaZna6-RxfqDluiFzTGNrypDReGc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Best beer in the area. But, again, beer here is the best of Port Moody (and among the best in all of YVR).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMu3i0ptHa9GvV2f11IR60rttJUXvOHTaXGGlY&fid=0x0:0xb1d5a4cd24e4928"],"When":"2017-8-27"},{"Name":"Todd M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU67_ZmetWQLLuz1KRqYHOntfV6qmBZzVG6Cd0a8DGs8auDO9km=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My girlfriend and I loved our experience at Twin Sails. Cheers!

Ps. Nice merch too","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"TheWanderingFire (TheWanderingFire)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX20kihjd5sHOQU_2dQCv9tQRbMj0dIQPKVelHkQyk5bmlgoU3-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This have been my fav brewery for 5+ years. Great pizza truck out front.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8i5eEdX_oDSoguZdL3RaJF_H05WzY7L1AaUmb&fid=0x0:0xb1d5a4cd24e4928"],"When":"2020-10-15"},{"Name":"Alan Lensink","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiUwCeCmUetf71kEfPgC6rH5900gBIDxe7g76jUiL6IDj623SV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Twin Sails has an impressive line-up of delicious beers: IPAs, sours, stouts, lagers, ales, etc. I think they have a delish beer for everyone's taste.

But in first we entered by mistake in a lounge just next door, but somehow we figured out it’s not the recommended place by our friends. [{"Name":"SOMAYEH KADKHODAEIELYADERANI","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeT4rSCdV1n5Ln9gW9Ums0ibH02kt7_6Ugxp50LKa_XE-SEF8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you’re looking for an exceptional experience in a warm and inviting atmosphere, this café is a must-visit. The owner and staff are incredibly polite and attentive, making you feel truly welcomed from the moment you step in. Their hospitality is remarkable, and they go above and beyond to make every guest feel at home.

The tea and hookah service here is outstanding. The tea is perfectly brewed, with a rich aroma and delicious taste, while the hookahs are of the highest quality. The café itself offers a beautifully designed space, combining comfort and style to create a relaxing environment.

For anyone who enjoys a great atmosphere, friendly service, and top-notch beverages, this café is the ideal spot. It’s an experience you won’t want to miss and will definitely want to revisit.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Seyed hassan Vaezi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGXsYVnfOteXBonVmKqUu7JuRO_r1d-d31RrvqGFZ-gU_gOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you’re looking for an exceptional experience in a cozy and inviting atmosphere, this café is a perfect choice. The owner and staff are incredibly polite and welcoming, making you feel at home from the moment you walk in. Their hospitality is truly remarkable and sets the tone for a wonderful visit.

The tea and hookah service here is top-notch. The tea is served with an amazing aroma and taste, and the hookahs are of great quality, ensuring satisfaction for every guest. The café’s environment is beautifully designed, offering a mix of comfort and elegance.

If you’re seeking a place where both the quality of service and the warmth of the staff stand out, this café is a must-visit. [{"Name":"Chinonso Obeta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0yfV5kjQ-Xq9KAUs_4HZeSU_qZxQQ-j4kdZVPxgkKv14HMtX3qg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The doughnuts are so awesome. I would recommend the lemon meringue doughnut for a more savory taste.

The team is so kind and so wonderful. Whenever we come, we love talking to them. And sometimes they even give samples! I’m from Vancouver and I would make the journey any day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOnD07tbCog4k6Z7_LCOaA79-k5AxP773sTP6W&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Tyler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5pgqDcV4jXxCDs44gFpKqBE7-kpDe9pqH0qySpykt9h70rZWn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If heaven had a breakfast club, Doughnut Love in Coquitlam would be the founding member. Let me tell you, this place knows how to make your taste buds do the cha-cha. I waddled in expecting a quick sugar rush and left with a full-on breakfast love affair. Here’s the scoop:

First off, the chocolate chip cookie dough doughnut. It’s like someone took my childhood dreams of sneaking cookie dough out of the fridge and deep-fried them into a perfectly golden doughnut. Absolute perfection. Then there was the apple crumble doughnut—crispy, sweet, with that lovely crumbly topping that made me think of Grandma’s kitchen (if Grandma was a Michelin-star chef in disguise). Together, they were like the dynamic duo of dessert—Batman and Robin, but covered in sugar and far tastier.

Now, let me talk about the cheesy smoky breakfast sandwich. My friends, I have had a lot of breakfast sandwiches in my day. I’ve been around the eggy block, had my share of bacon-stacked bagels, and yes, even tangoed with the occasional McMuffin. But this one? It was life-altering. Like, call-your-mom-and-tell-her-you-found-the-one kind of good. I’m not even joking when I say this was the best breakfast sandwich I’ve ever had. Hands down, no debate. The cheese was melty, the smokiness was spot on, and the bread hugged the filling like it knew I needed that kind of emotional support that morning. Bravo, Doughnut Love, bravo.

And then there was the pistachio latte. I thought it was pretty good—creamy with that distinct pistachio nuttiness. But my girlfriend? She took one sip, wrinkled her nose, and gave me that look like I had just offered her a cup of blended brussels sprouts. So yeah, it’s a bit of a polarizing beverage. I was happy, she wasn’t, and I ended up with two lattes. Win-win for me, honestly.

Overall, Doughnut Love is definitely worth the visit. Whether you’re after doughnuts that’ll make you reconsider what you know about dessert or a breakfast sandwich that might just change your life, this is the spot. Plus, it’s always fun to take your taste buds on an adventure—even if it means having to finish your partner’s drink. Check it out. Trust me, your stomach will thank you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBicJQNVZ3eHQ0mQVOJAQIJgDpPzUg6SHE_QzI&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Sunny Bui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKMzWAiXdng0rCtZP9l45dHvlvYqeLHGoUweyd_OjqtW7kL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing Donut Place! Service was GREAT! The vibe was enjoyable!

HUGE SELECTION! Gluten free, vegan, regular donuts and some that are definitely out of the ordinary.

We’ve been here a few times for these delicacies and have ordered batches for catering. These guys DO NOT DISAPPOINT! They are delicious and have something for everyone (and their diet).

Their staff always greets us with a smile, are considerate with handling of the donuts and make sure we are in and out/got what we need. The inside is very cozy too if you decide to stay a bit!

Great work!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtvlbuizmioa0vN8NfQOqkDtC3FpnlSyy1DFQ&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-1-11"},{"Name":"Maria M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmuhUB-INQ3XCbE2M9HT-MdzILSuqxW6ls6tLvy0JgUoxl1f3wCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m not a donuts person but I sure love hot chocolate. I tried the Tiramisu edition for the hot chocolate festival and it was sensational, it came with a mini tiramisu dessert that also tasted very rich. My husband tried the Mexican special and he liked it but I didn’t dig it hehe, don’t like spicy drinks. His came with churros which were very yummy. Nice spot, lovely service :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXKqm4O7z3Xnll-ng94h2kwwU17u1W4jXTh2U_&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-1-24"},{"Name":"Ayesha S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIRN1jDxm-GbV9f53B-tJsf5liCDSU1wXPfJ8zXkEZajwAAmKs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down the best so it’s I’ve ever had! My entire family agrees. I’ve had many donuts but the flavours here are phenomenal. The donuts aren’t overly sweet which I appreciate. Crispy on the outside but soft on the inside! 100/10!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sogolika","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUzHybtFBRJfBv53jgPRRojyPQpndAKmXiSDkdl1E8GHCzNky1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was my first time going there and really loved it.
The doughnuts are amazing and also the staff are so friendly,even they gave me a free bag of doughnuts as a gift.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOHmieBrgmprydw9odbYU76hAb1iTyxWuyDjIGc&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Vegan donut haven! These beautiful light and fluffy rings of insanely yummy dough are one of the best in Coquitlam I have tasted and the perfect Friday treat to combo with your morning cup of Joe! Nicely dense with a light and uplifting texture, nicely moist and flawless
Super tasty, excellent bold and quirky, edgy flavors with zero animal-based ingredients.
These were a solid four, however a tad dry and stale and I imagine the fresh morning batch in the morning is legit phenomenal .Writing this review has already sent me into another dough-dream.
I really want to try The Homer (my favorite ultimate donut flavor of all time) and will give this a whirl if I manage to get there at a good time.
Support local businesses!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfcdDUDpiuADd3RnOCt_7OIHsckDzcPTScbc6Z&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2023-10-27"},{"Name":"Jess Golden","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNdoWBo5RTPsLB2umQOAwhHEXhhe_ZCgHopw1C7RPs6Tys=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down my favourite doughnut shop, so when my now husband and I eloped yesterday with just a couple friends, I ordered doughnuts for brunch on the big day!  I requested they put our initials on two of them and they threw those extra 2 doughnuts in for free!  They were such a hit and looked so cute plated with chocolate-dipped strawberries.  Thank you, Doughnut Love for being a part of our special day! 🍩🍾🥂","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZTVUKm5RpCf6zS7ueAcA7VyMG3iHkNz60dCs&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-5-16"}]

[{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and his boys are here regularly and always come home looking good. Today I tagged along to see the barbershop myself. They have a convenient online booking system. Today we popped in when we were walking by, and luckily they could get my husband a chair. There are a couple couches in the waiting area and we were in and out pretty quickly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUQUEWJlW0zR4zHYJWprbGnsxKlXHL9w76edKi&fid=0x0:0x682801dbfe0fb4fe"],"When":"2024-6-1"},{"Name":"Steve Wolfe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJ0vcu_0fjNPj75ypbIobgNbUpje_VlcPBfQezcNzXNuk8VA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always a good experience but had to finally leave a review after this last visit. My son got a great haircut as usual from Eric but I could tell something was wrong on the way back to the car. He looked great but I think he wanted more of a mid fade but told them low fade (I heard him). I think he was just too shy to "correct" an adult so he didn't say anything til we were back at the car. He asked to go back and get a bit more noticeable fade. They were super cool as always. Eric had someone in his chair so someone else stepped in to "touch it up", not "fix it" as there was nothing wrong with it. They gave him what he asked for, he was just too shy to let them know he meant to ask for something a little bit different. At any rate I just wanted to leave this review to let them know it was a positive experience as always.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vincent Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLQWxrXwCY9LsYygMKLq_UsjGsIDYE4uDAcjjbKwvuTA6XcNA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I tend to wait for a while for a haircut cause I usually get nervous when people touch my hair but, I had Eddie help me out and made the personal experience one of the best experiences I had. My hair was fairly long and Eddie was able to make it stylish and easy to maintain which was all I could ask for! I appreciate the customer service from Eddie and look forward to coming back in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kareem Ahmed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPPjqtVhVvIkBaija7isKp0_j4p6B2BLBkkSOt4K7XawdgHBQ1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I just moved to Port Moody recently and I always get nervous getting a haircut from a new Barber but I got a skin fade from Reza and wow I am very happy with my haircut Reza was very knowledgeable about cuts and did a great job. I am very happy that I found my go to barber in Port Moody. Reza is the one you have to see when you come here!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYzL32qyFiGnPATjxTfcoQzgZS7jBWuXFkFArPUfP70MYReQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am usually very meticulous about my hair and often get frustrated with other barber places when they don't deliver what I politely informed them to do.

Been here for the past 2-3 years. Just had a cut with Eddie an hour ago...
and Eddie did an incredible taper fade—exactly what I wanted. My hair length is exactly what I wanted it down too.

He listened carefully to what I wanted, and delivered perfectly. Nothing more to say, how can I complain??

I'll definitely be coming back with Eddie and is now on my list as my main barbers, thanks!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexander Tapora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2COOToirR-7oB3wbFqqluc4GquEPTfnG26gCcocsjuJOmZqlV=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mo's the guy that cut my hair and I can say with confidence that he has given me one of the best haircuts I've had in a long time. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Andy Leung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBfPzDHg9RmwaF6xT8BiwrCt06LiR0mWps8IZZP7KGtsdBbQne=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stepped into the restaurant not really looking to eat but found the place open amongst many closed restaurants. Staff greeted me at the door and I asked for a menu which was promptly provided. A staff member (tall young man with perm) provided a thorough explanation of the menu and what different food options was available and the restaurant was about. I opted to dine in after the thorough explanation and genuine service even before I sat. Once I settled on an order the staff loudly shouted to the kitchen staff and proceeded to hand me utensils/water. Moments later I could hear a meat mallet being slammed against what can be presumed to be my order (pork loin cutlet). Not long after I sat down another customer came in asking to look at the menu and explaining they're unfamiliar with the concept. the food came out quickly. The deep fried loin was pleasantly plated; light tasting; and juicy with flavour. 5/5 food. 5/5 service. 5/5 ambiance. Seems like cabbage salad sides are unlimited too! Beginning to end this was 5/5. Came on Tuesday Oct 22nd 3:30pm. Katsuya - Coquitlam if you're reading this please recognize your staff for such outstanding service and delicious food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqilRDdGE6NydQWz1wbHRJAZ10XC-zTFgOgoJS&fid=0x0:0xc180c2232f3f7e85"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Kristine Aizle Estrada","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYbQRMW0sa4F7v9y0xsCWOZxC721h53-90ZVy0Q0mpX6y_Og=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We are greeted by all staff as soon we entered the place and got seated right away. We ordered the special set and it did not disappoint (the katsu is crispy and not greasy 😋). The set was large portion and we end up taking the leftovers to go. Good place to eat variety of katsu. Will come back for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOY-fx02u_VLQCLdpnDytZZVO7vSsU3Eniy5syQ&fid=0x0:0xc180c2232f3f7e85"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"Jack Bi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZ4Bsv7wnjfj756aRVvVyi5fPfQhBIMCe6kqNdp4pTbIyytg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the pleasure of trying katsu in Burquitlam recently, and I really appreciated the wonderful service. The food was delicious, and it was lovely to have both a salad and a refill of rice included—such a thoughtful addition! That said, I did notice the music was a bit on the loud side, which made it a little hard to fully enjoy the experience. Overall, though, it was a nice outing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGrjvypMFCi2IrGkRiEDeUZr2eyCD4xHboYTPz&fid=0x0:0xc180c2232f3f7e85"],"When":"2024-12-11"},{"Name":"TS OS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrxJ8Fjd3bGSI8mWbF186RbFWyg_DW73VTS3OIkFaxPfXFBEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"DonKatsu was pretty good. Pricing is up there with its competitors. Quality of food is comparable too but cabbage salad and rice refills don’t seem to exist at this place at free of charge. We also really liked the pasta, which was surprisingly tasty especially the sauce. Place usually isn’t packed so you should be able to get seated fairly shortly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJbZSl1M1e8lL8ztqGh1BRqzbPMALyWsOjK81b&fid=0x0:0xc180c2232f3f7e85"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"Ben","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLUPgdSyWZ3aTWwwnESZaSRJf8t_y_oBRQlEfjK-SB4dJfKj64=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Katsu sauce had a unique taste, but overall it was the best tonkatsu place I've had in Vancouver. The taste was great, and the portion size was very enough for the price, which made it very satisfying. The restaurant had a small number of tables compared to the size of the space, which made it comfortable and pleasant. The staff's service was also excellent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtnMx8MZVn9g_Opb-r96C0P49aZ1kpq0KR6bq2&fid=0x0:0xc180c2232f3f7e85"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Karen Abary","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuR4UCsHnAPqLBeNDszrqXOmjrbOmLQnn5L3CErUSQyQJWrM8qqw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you’re cruising through North Road and craving something beyond the usual Korean fare, Katsuya is where you need to be! 😋 This place has all the mouthwatering options—from rich, savory udon to crispy, golden katsu. 🍛 And when I say the portions are huge, I mean HUGE! 🙌

I went for the Katsu Set, and it was an absolute game-changer. The katsu was perfectly crispy on the outside, tender on the inside, paired with a warm, flavorful bowl of udon, plus a variety of side dishes that kept me coming back for more. 🍜🍤 Every bite was better than the last!

But what really made the experience unforgettable? The service! 🙏 The staff is so friendly, super accommodating, and genuinely makes you feel like you’re right at home. 💖 And the best part? The prices are totally worth it for the big portions and top-notch food you get.

Katsuya is definitely a new favorite, and I’ll be back for sure! 🥳 So if you’re after a cozy, flavorful meal that’ll leave you stuffed and satisfied, this spot is a must-try! #KatsuyaCravings #FoodieHeaven #NorthRoadEats #WorthEveryBite","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNI92G2XWHYPDUt7OD1zn2lu0xp98OwnV25kSEQ&fid=0x0:0xc180c2232f3f7e85"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Cyril","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWK-_ySZg3bQEFmes-BY-8D2FucE-bUlde_oHJOB4IAApjGcLEN=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came on a date with my girlfriend, we were greeted as we stepped into the place and were seated right away, love the atmosphere lovely music that fits the season and also love the bread displays it shows that the breading is authentic. I was overwhelmed in a way in which the food had a excellent presentation and the portions were worth the pricing, also love the sesame seeds which you can grind by yourself it gives it a nice detail to add to the meal. Most importantly the Katsu is cooked just right, my girlfriend got the silver cheese katsu and the cheese was just right melting and not too hot, recommend this place for real, nice little hidden spot for a date or for a filling meal :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUvIHVBWOi-4eHV9Ift76vddqGCB1k7bOIVPwn&fid=0x0:0xc180c2232f3f7e85"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Anish Banik Arko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWI0KM6WKbnZVsLpZ9NMfdm_mhCSCv9FEUTS0DOwOV0D99wyYin4A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food has always been amazing here. Have been coming here for a long time. Their special set katsu menu comes with enough food for two and the variety of foods really adds to the dining experience. The presentation is also on point. Would highly recommend to try out their red carbonara katsu with your choice of protein.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPaP-aKaqJ3ToDeKrzL9oDtvbRVJxEmm8p4ZWAp&fid=0x0:0xc180c2232f3f7e85"],"When":"2024-7-23"}]
