We prefer to eat in home because the restaurant is really hot in this summer but we like the food. Finally, really good prices but the service is no good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi1YBxhAcQdMw7_Xi5ontWRu5FmdjkKadhBNXe&fid=0x0:0xc29909442b15211c"],"When":"2023-7-15"},{"Name":"Joshua (ThickBurger_Bites)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbIhhMlbxk7OIMpcaP-aSx2m75kt8-mqmXoXAJQ5K99gnxiff1zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Decided to grab some dinner. Donair looked good and this place had rather good ratings.

Food:
We ordered the chicken platter. I got the upsize (+$2), which meant, more meat 😍 I had all the vegetables and sauces on the platter. The chicken was marinated and roasted well, a little dry, but given that I went a little late, it was expected. Rice was delicious, savoury and filling, wasn't too sure what stock they cooked it in, but it was amazing. Two options of salads, Caesar and Greek. I had the Caesar, it was alright. Nothing special.

Service:
Friendly young dude. A little quiet. Quick prompt service.

Location:
Pretty empty at 9pm. Rather warm given that it's summer and there wasn't much ventilation/AC.

Price:
Approx ~$9/pax

Would I recommend?
Yes. Meat portions are generous (refer to pics for clarity), food is relatively filling. Get the set meal(+drink) for better value.

[{"Name":"Sarah Hong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKnboqN2ucap2810B74d4ezUYCyFoMSbI2XJPs7KKauWRgM5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is absolutely delicious! The noodles in the 짜장면 are perfectly balanced—not too thick or thin, and cooked just right. The 짬뽕 has just the right level of spice, full of rich flavor that melts away your stress. As for the sweet and sour pork, it's a perfect combination of textures—crispy on the outside, tender and juicy on the inside. 100% recommend! Definitely worth every penny.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOi-q_1NweNn4z2ThRTUFxzQExHPrQNJtVyh5QC&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"David 04 Make the World a Better Place","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXmkrAyRsAwad4uDl0EKEwpsCVMLq51IOxmbley55h_iwJzGo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"David's Overall Recommendation
★★★★★

● Taste ★★★★★
● Price ★★★★★
● Kindness ★★★★★
● Comfort ★★★★☆
● Cleanliness ★★★★★

I visited this restaurant around 4:30 pm, which is a bit early for dinner. A female server welcomed me, and she was very friendly.

I ordered the combo with Jajangmyeon (black bean noodles), Jjamppong (spicy seafood noodle soup), and Tangsuyuk (sweet and sour pork). About 10 minutes later, all three dishes arrived together. The Tangsuyuk seemed to be fried in clean oil, and both the meat and the batter were exceptional. (Having worked in the restaurant industry, I could tell the frying oil was fresh.)

The Jajangmyeon and Jjamppong were delicious too, but the Tangsuyuk was the highlight.

The portions were generous, with all the food being flavorful and filling.

There were a couple of minor downsides:

1.	After the food was served, although the restaurant wasn’t busy, no one came by to check on the food or refill the side dishes. But with food this tasty, it was easy to overlook.
2.	They were playing a Charlie Puth medley, which didn’t quite match the restaurant’s vibe. (Just a playful comment!)

●There’s parking available, though not a lot.

●The restrooms are separated for men and women.

I highly, highly recommend this restaurant.
The food is incredibly tasty and clean.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsoYUAAi-S_HgnQg7DpsMimB6vAJ-ixuB9las&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Paula Mari Calip","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDLGLcegymnTs4tKFxCUQkS77Gpb8Bcit9lJfvZ7dcPzKmO_Ci-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Home-y atmosphere, big servings, flavourful meal. My family enjoyed our time here. Will come back for sure!

PS: couldn’t take proper photos of our other food lol we were hungry and ready to chow down 😂","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-fmzFjkrXsDSuD70e4LWu0e4GepaXup02B7aI&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Y Man","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUB62F2-VitrTkpd3TexeBmDt6LJ-Ec6lzQvbbyCIp7HJAIiB3b=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Update:
We went for the second time and we are happy that the food is still great and tasty! Consistency is so important and glad it did not disappoint. We ordered the same dishes plus Jjamppong. The Jjamppong was delicious! The broth was spicy but flavourful.  We will come back and try more dishes.

What a great meal! The food was delicious and the portion is generous. The tangsuyuk coating was light and crispy its sauce in the bowl was sweet and flavourful. The fried chicken's batter was also light and crispy and it was coated with a nice sweet tangy sauce that has a nice kick to it.  The jjajangmyeon was delicious, noodles are nice and chewy, the sauce was good with seafood and waterchestnuts mixed in it. I look forward to try their jjamppong (spicy seafood soup noodles)! We saw another table had it and it looks great!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYGfyXK9P4bM98bWmhnS-0JPOB5QwstdK4zmYr&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-6-8"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's a pretty standard Korean-Chinese restaurant that I'm used to. Their black sauce noodle was pretty good, but what really impressed me was the sweet and sour chicken.

The spicy seafood noodle was also quite tasty and would recommend it if you are into spicy food. I recommend that you go with lots of people so that you can order different things to try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVNoe2LTQphTqu1MVyAj3B_wmaTn3z8kg7qon6&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-1-23"},{"Name":"marieXD21","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-Fu7lpV7ZXo_nlR8y9b6iJvHY1uEHpNZ4ShKlMM_rYkUiQkw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All food are delicious. We eat here once a month but every time we come back, we still can’t finish the big portions. Undefeated, highly recommend 💯!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAroCq__K1__QMaOgFHdj2TOTP2iR6IMqfnzCS&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-9-4"},{"Name":"Fanny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJf8QKhXtO_qInBc0jUDaCE3x1KtIHCwwl5Dp3ugGKzBjub0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We tried the Jjajangmyun and Jjam Bbong, and we're thrilled to have finally found a good Jjajangmyun! The portions were generous, and the service was excellent!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFNKr0BhTh7zPnf9l2KU0zrOOR5DhjvZAbQn6k&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"Kenny Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPZZirBvo0A4h9mBsQTblhWpjRI5s3b9jzZsDmMvuAnSg24xg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We don't often have Korean food but we wanted to try this place since they just opened where Kam Ding used to be. We also didn't know the portion sizes but it turned out to be really big so we ended up with enough leftovers for a second meal! The food was tasty so we enjoyed it. Most of the dishes are spicy but just right for us. A senior couple arrived and sat at the next table. They sounded like they are Italian and were also looking to try Korean food. We helped them choose a non-spicy dish!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhdTuRlDHKuJZqKozH-SA71Wk1X7IfundtlX5N&fid=0x0:0xada9b7037d05e7e9"],"When":"2023-12-27"}]

[{"Name":"Meghan Atkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpn_HJKLz67oWun2TqZ53LpPOuwDcgytLe9I7rJRW9gkR5zUDI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered take out tonight from Dinakis (through skip the dishes). Ordered my regular Greek dish, the chicken souvlaki. I often order from another restaurant but thought I would give Dinakis a try. Upon eating my chicken souvlaki skewer, I noticed the taste and texture of the chicken seemed off. To my surprise the chicken was raw in the middle. The restaurant was immediately called to inform them. They stated that we needed to contact skip for a refund (which is fine!) and said the chicken was raw due to how busy the restaurant was tonight. Unfortunately, I do not see this as a valid reason for serving undercooked meat. They offered to remake the meal and have me come and pick it up. Unfortunately with a baby in bed, leaving the house is not option which is why I ordered in.

I’ll no longer be order from Dinakis. Perhaps if the situation had been dealt with differently on their end I would. However, it’s all left a bad taste in my mouth - no pun intended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPamzWqtMSJD_2lXqeftQ04VTeQ-qet20_AUo7c&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Queenie Chao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZJZmSpZQRAFF9t6SoJ29KP7hdKen-l5gR8pgpgRf7-1s6aED9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went here for my dad's birthday. Service was excellent! Food was great - the roast lamb, chicken marsala, and moussaka were all amazing, especially the lamb! The only exception was the steak, which was over cooked and full of gristle. To make up for it, they offered us a tiramisu cake which worked out well and was tasty too. Would definitely come back for the lamb and try other items too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUkbQOcVFipathRk-dHPJeXSBTX5g93Ke5HcNA&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Jessica Tite","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDIMc556UvdeCdK2q0SIDelAc_HJzjyapBYqP0A0CPBdyeWUex=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best Mediterranean food I've had! It's no wonder they have so many awards/accolades at the entrance way.
The food is incredible: well priced, fresh and great portions.
The restaurant is neat and clean, including the washrooms. It has a very cozy feel inside.
Service was excellent!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2zKnmJCNiyvvJJiFSndVY5qI8Go-Dp0HU1Vdj&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2024-2-11"},{"Name":"Al So","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLumQHIv-5W9wXPr4ZbA1zWCVnPk2w1Kc3bjsO93-VMG-v7JQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you’re in the Shaughnessy area in Poco and craving some Mediterranean magic, look no further than Dinakis Mediterranean Grill. Let me just say, the portions here are generously sized, so come prepared to feast!

The tzatziki is a standout—nice and fresh, with a flavor that’ll make your taste buds do a happy dance. It's the perfect companion to their delicious offerings.

Speaking of which, the Souvlaki Combo is a real treat. It comes with beef, chicken, and prawn souvlaki, each one cooked to perfection. The beef is tender, the chicken is juicy, and the prawns are succulent. It's a delightful trio that hits all the right notes.

We also tried the roast lamb, which was cooked to perfection. It wasn't fatty, and the meat just came off the bone. We thoroughly enjoyed it.

For those dining with little ones, you'll be pleased to know they offer kids' portions. These come with one skewer instead of two at a reduced price, making it great value. It’s the perfect way to keep the kids happy without breaking the bank.

Overall, Dinakis Mediterranean Grill is a great spot for hearty portions, fresh flavors, and good value. Make sure to bring your appetite—you won’t be disappointed!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi-Vmmgslvmp-CsAb30_lQnluDK_dEqTU341G1&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"Patrick Laplante","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEQ6rmzYgqU18BgeUeFbN3j9UzTXOfNOAqOLvy-TwFRIxBth-Q7g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Firstly, the service and the staff are absolutely fantastic. Secondly, the food quality is great, it's really great value, huge portions, and always fresh. And thirdly, great drink selection, and I was happy to hear that they can accommodate large parties as well. Whether for a cute date, family dinner, birthday celebration or quick lunch, I'd highly recommend!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGEpDRCp2o6wFFn9ZB0lPz_oE8b1ckSu6JjaQG&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2024-1-8"},{"Name":"Julian Sara Joseph","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWofxVvuCZOl3BWxzMUTJPVosg-yW0WoAuPTsW6aFO5_K2yZycmSg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Greek food here was truly authentic and tasty. Souvlaki of all varieties was great. We had come back from a trek and all our tiredness was gone with the kind servers and their affordable but yummy food ❤️their portion sizes are quite large so it is filing. Loved the presentation too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJvrpsBh0Cgol4Hr9mDBGY6_JEDFnb7KJHbIEJ&fid=0x0:0x9aee5f46d48e0cd3"],"When":"2023-4-4"},{"Name":"Cheryl G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQZ5krFYmB32nSSVZRn_5-zzzmWzMyLr7fQFLOSOH_4NttzFie=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Overall good experience. We had regular entrees but also ordered happy hour appetizers, portions was a little small. I also found that an automatic 18% gratituity was surprising for 7 people dining. But we enjoyed the food with our dining guests and I would recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thom Slater","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNyquzT0Ty5ga2cGbYXqVQ4Zp1mr8dSG4EejGqH4R5Eqad_PSB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came in for an extended family dinner. Really generous portion sizes, the lamp chops were fantastic.
Other than the great food, what really made this a 5 star experience was the incredible service from Mariah.
She took our 12 person reservation last minute despite being solo, had such great energy the whole night, and really made it an enjoyable time for everyone. We'd come back just for her.","Images":null,"When":""}]

But as a big group, prepare to be hungry a little bit. Serving is not super fast but your stomach will be full for sure!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdARKT_83o7JGkz1gZt3M9u5asO5tb7xwpZ3CG&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"Christine W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKPsEE58m4l7C5YBEcOPLQtBTaYwdBFGzTSKEIraaLnCr6OYcs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We made it just before the lunch rush at noon and only waited about ten minutes for a table of 3.

The hostess asked me if I would like Jasmine tea, I said no and asked for Chrysanthemum tea.  She didn’t understand me and brought me jasmine anyway but it wasn’t a big deal.

We marked off the dim sum we wanted on the paper and the dishes came out relatively quickly considering how busy it was, one at a time.

The food was steaming hot and delicious.  We had the egg tarts, fried tofu, shrimp rice rolls, beef balls, pan fried prawn and chive dumplings, chicken feet and beef brisket rice rolls in a clay pot.

Everything was absolutely delicious, the shrimp rice roll was loaded with prawns!  The servers aren’t the friendliest and don’t hide that they’re annoyed when you ask for other things such as hot sauce or a drink.  I understand that they’re busy though and I’m there for the food so it’s not a big deal.

The hostess also missed one item that I checked off on our order but we were full anyway.

Bottom line, yes I would absolutely return for dim sum!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnaVG2kGThAKwI_-1GwALL1JRsn48bC2BI75fc&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"Ngoc Ha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBQDR7xuHV7zpmSmm8y3qArF6yv91O7Kuz_kGRJuYZ6FiARojF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a 3rd time I am here. There are long line up for brunch. I have never had to pay, so I can't tell about tipping thing. The service has room to improve certainly. For example, when we say today the food seem to be a little bit saltier than the last time we were here, and we ask if they have new chef or what; the server acts like we speak nonsense. I am attaching here the updated menu in case you need to know the increased price. Today is September 30, 2024. I recommend you to bring cash to pay and ask for promotion of cash payment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwhQqJazyjZJ780aB1nl5jFq0sJazfM_7PRRv9&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"---edit June 2024---
I tried different dim sum dishes.
Deep fried squid tentacles - really good. Portion is a bit small

Beef Rice rolls - good texture.

Shrimp paste on eggplant - came out piping hot

Shrimp patty with chives - this one came out cold... it was good but it probably sat there for a while

Deep fried glutinous rice balls with meat filling - the outside mochi was good but the filling was lacking in flavor and in portion

Beef brisket on chan chuen fan - love the noodles. Can't get this type of noodle in many places. Beef brisket was tough and not much flavor. Would try the pork riblets next time.

-------------
In terms of flavor, this has got to be one of the wosrt ones I have been to.

Century egg and pork congee - flavorless. No salt. No base whatsoever.

Hand shredded chicken salad - extremely small. Most places that give smaller portions have expensive jellyfish in the salad. This place is only chicken and preserved vegetables so there is no need for it to be half the size of the plate, smaller than other specialty chef items.

Deep fried chicken knees - giant pieces only to find out it is 80% batter. The garlic salt and spice just sat at the bottom and the chicken was never stirred with it.

Minced pork fried glutinous rice dumpling - the glutinous rice wasnt very sweetened. The insides were ok. The only good thing is that it came with 4 pieces instead of 3.

Overall, the dimsum dishes were not very good. The prices are high with poor quality dishes. Maybe their dinner menu makes up for it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRL0bQXOdXOmLCPckVyE40kKNkpOpokL1auaQZ&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2023-5-27"},{"Name":"Brayden M.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPBZNPVNqHW8dSCFike-NLUMkuCrsmT6ZW7ysivwMhyRbgUxkL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for lunch again, and it's always a great experience here! Arrived around 2p, so we were seated promptly (wait time ~20 minutes during peak hours).
We ordered the 蝦餃 shrimp dumplings, 牛筋肚 beef stomach tendon, 菠蘿叉燒包 BBQ bun with crispy topping, 鹹水角 'football' pork croquette, and 炸兩腸粉 fried rice roll.
The Pineapple BBQ bun was sold out, so we replaced it with a regular BBQ bun. However our order was not properly registered, and we had to wait around half an hour for it to come out, though our server handled the situation very well.
The shrimp dumplings were large and fresh, the pork bun serving was generous, the croquette was hot and fresh, and the rice roll was super quick to come out.
Overall, we had a great experience, save the minor hiccup with the pork bun, and I look forward to coming back!
Total cost for 5 dishes: $48+tip","Images":null,"When":""}]

Family run establishment.  Portion sizes are large and flavors are on point.  The only suggestion I would make is for the rice to be a bit warmer.  But the flavor and texture of the rice was perfect.  Appetizer of stewed Eggplant with fried onions was very tasty and a very large portion.  Texture of meats was juicy and perfectly cooked.  Prices very reasonable.  Would definitely return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkEt14ac299DDARyd-SgbrVvDagrTz-2sDL7kR&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Melissa Cabot","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIL0zOTwNlNjn9wGw7Rzo6ydbTGCYv0cdQl9NYnK3iWj33iaQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I've been a customer since the beginning, always good, fresh food. There are way too many options for good Persian food to be lowering your quality.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuk86eyrKzFCxN3fjC2Gh7WVgfPs4ac8RQel74iDY6fKVzQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"amex accepted.  Decent barg/beef steak with rice and shirazi salad. The food is not particularly flavourful but acceptable.  It's a fast food place, so service is minimum. The decoration/atmostphere is better than most middle eastern fast food joint. The old lady at the counter is very friendly. Might come back and try the ground beef kebob.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNs14IYo1pHdekx1j-K9eq221uq_FRoesZnYd7a&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2024-2-13"},{"Name":"Farid Entezari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV35QQyx2JmA30yOGa4kCXMTDZjBP0mMYjKzM0CL9HNh-FF7LAEEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The kebob house restaurant in poco is a small nice Persian restaurant. I tried their mix kebab dish which is one skewer of ground beef (Koobideh) and one skewer of steak( barg). Taste was good, portion size was good. Lots of parking in the plaza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONMghztr8XUKJnLI08J656NjDz94WXClWyIBRM&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2023-6-8"},{"Name":"Jason Shanks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqF_09LHcLQUBwa4sJj1J-2wuuUKxQADdaKcyJX3stv4lfuueH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Go check this place out!!!
What a great little place, we will definitely be back.
1.) Food was great, especially the yogurt for the pitta bread. It was light, fluffy, and had fresh chunks of cucumbers.
2.) Great service, although there was a hockey game on the TV good relaxing music for eating was playing at a conversational level.
3.) Meal for two, we were full upon leaving... just over $35.
3.) Clean kitchen, relatively new renovation making the inside comfortable, happily the renos extended into the washroom... some time these strip mall places can have not so great bathrooms... this was nice.
4.) Strip mall parking = short walk to the restaurant","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFxEqNuD7DW3qZGM5hzj53ap4gsScn4pVQDJj2&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2023-11-29"},{"Name":"Holly Hui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhQD6BQlcWfE694GJOqlMhXMwIQT-rKw4jcG8DlxP8gg2emzY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My favourite persian restaurant to order from on UberEats. I've been ordering since February 2024.

I always order the Vasiri combo with Mast-O-Mooseer (yogurt with shallots), and the Shirazi Salad. The perfect meal! The portions are great, skewers are cooked perfectly and not dry, flavourful. What I appreciate is the consistency, I order quite often from here.

This recent order, the restaurant had contacted me about not having Sprite in stock so I replaced it with Ice tea. When I received my order, they had packaged 2 cans of Ice tea. I really appreciate the complimentary drink. I do want to mention when the lady had picked up the phone, she sounded very pleasant and genuine. One day if I'm in the Port Coco area, I would love to dine-in at this restaurant. Thank you","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steven H.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXK62iJj1ZUFGa-U3A8AjtI1ckQk60_9MMp9OhTpvv0nDBllSzC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been here a couple times.

I've always enjoyed the food and experience here.

Fresh, reasonably priced and just plain good.

I live a bit far away from port coquitlum but whenever I come here, I always eat here.

I am a big fan of Persian cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpNJ3rXIwpVXFMcE37cha4yyJ0Xclp5IESBsYC&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2022-3-9"},{"Name":"Magic Eslami","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJo_ometNe5VFxyYN9EFz4qK_PQABq10iwnM8v3Yyyw57cviA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kebab House is a charming Persian family restaurant where I’ve been a regular for several years. The selection of kebabs is impressive, and the food is consistently delicious—all at a very reasonable price!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"james corbett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXORPNpjn99AmypwXC5L8gqaCK1buk43veXhtLSzHUK1ZItjmE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The atmosphere here is nothing special and does not need to be with the food they serve. This is some of the best food I have had since being in LA. I go to LA to see my Korean adopted fam and they take me for food I could not get in Vancouver. The chilled noodles brought me back the first time I tried. Kimchi pancake was crispy with a nice soft inside. I ordered way too much as the portions were large. We all enjoyed the meal and I have thanked the friend that suggested it multiple times for taking us here. Now I need to go again and just order less food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjnrBc83bnjesqd7a_A31XBSajmsoWJxCMyDlv&fid=0x0:0x5fe33e293525f560"],"When":"2024-11-26"},{"Name":"Ess November","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuPJ8X9jOZ2CtOO2jCad-r9UmiPcylLXs6WZsf1PzrAZBsBSHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you’re looking for authentic Korean soup and fresh ingredients, this is the place. I’ve been here 3 times so far and it just gets better. Authentic handmade mandu (steamed dumplings) and fall off the bone pork back bone soup with a deep flavourful broth- this soup is what Tongileo is known for so I highly recommend it - you’ll be hooked! The side dishes are fantastic as well…very fresh. Overall 5 stars and highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOew8gNH7gPRqP4Av9gCLhX8FzNkktx42Rwhml&fid=0x0:0x5fe33e293525f560"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Beatrice Gandu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-m69YxvoaMOoMimuj6-sA4-k4eYqu5MNiPHLVrevqzu-K2Gac=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I love our time there, and it was our first time there. We got want we were craving for and were satisfied. We'll be going back soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNb3TZRpKTHP5Y6aPV3mC_goLkNKC9KgXaB5Sdl&fid=0x0:0x5fe33e293525f560"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"Peter L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSG7FnL9eakxXRPAc9ls0ptr2FhkmSk4cro_gsE76Wu7JPcW0z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I had the bibimbap with beef, and the portion was on the small side. Besides a lot of large chunks of green onion and slices of onion, there were barely any vegetables.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipML6J-vTHvaqQ_JNrjMylk-3LVy9s6HAKBVAG8T&fid=0x0:0x5fe33e293525f560"],"When":"2024-11-1"},{"Name":"Yael","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2CedmibCs3GgALTk7vZt6eeRKcGkvp_k4R782jS2YY2IhPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"backbone soup is great and meaty! Squid bibimbap is sweet and spicy, my classmates think it is average, I prefer this taste. No more spicy kimchi soup, replaced with kimchi tofu soup, which is delicious. Free to give us three small dishes, sweet potatoes, seaweed is sour and sweet taste, delicious. If you happen to be in the area, you can come and try it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOf6we7xCuCK8euUNqwVxrvr5JmtA4jcG1ensk2&fid=0x0:0x5fe33e293525f560"],"When":"2023-7-23"},{"Name":"Eagleridge He","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyk6k_xeBUj_1KDLC2dilz6BOL-9JcNSoxnyXWuMM0QdJPvjOF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is always our family's favorite restaurant in Tri-city area. Whenever I want to skip cooking at home, we'd like to come here. For years, we stick with the same orders.: Pork bone soup, bulgogi in hot stone bowl and pork cutlet.
I noticed their prices have been keeping on going up, but still the most reasonable in our area. I like their sides too, which have been cut from 5  dishes down to 4, now 3. But still no complains since they were generous before and always gave refills if we asked for. Recently we started to like their bibimbap.
Their cooking is good and food is tasty and homey especially in the cold winter, very filling and satisfying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNFIZ_N0rsUyopk6JEQk92YOL6_V0b6MNsdlq8&fid=0x0:0x5fe33e293525f560"],"When":"2021-11-9"},{"Name":"Kat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9KU6JHMNV2dJVHVeBb2rvEzltNXWG-yaPrGGgPwOBW0ejMgGu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very delicious and well priced! Service was quick when we were there, we came before it got too busy (around 4pm) but soon after we got there people started rolling in. Obvious favourite in the community and I understand why. I got the tofu seafood soup and my bf got the dumpling kal gooksu. Was very good and the portions were generous.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNwF1mvva63r1fhCJLj6PNVklaEZ4rOa0yaxXW&fid=0x0:0x5fe33e293525f560"],"When":"2023-1-8"},{"Name":"yumi chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTtW8e1Rmf0_77OCHIl7oqCn3pXLHhqJBUZVfdHrPrImawFw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently dined at this restaurant with a pregnant friend, and the experience was beyond disappointing. To start, we were served spoiled squid, which is completely unacceptable, especially for someone who is pregnant.

After we told the server, they offered a discount as a form of compensation. However, when they got wind of our intention to report this incident to the health department, they shamefully retracted the discount. They said they are being generous and take our intention to report as a threat. Also, they emphasize that we have to be responsible for what we order, but we didn’t expect to get the spoiled food. To make matters worse, they even summoned the police to coerce us into paying the full amount. And they take away the dishes but never serve us a new one, so basically we paid full price for nothing.

This level of disregard for both customer well-being and basic ethics is inexcusable. It's disheartening to see such a blatant lack of responsibility and accountability from the management. I strongly advise anyone, especially those who are pregnant or have health concerns, to steer clear of this establishment.

The blatant disregard for food safety and the mistreatment of patrons is simply unacceptable. I have already reported this incident to the local health department, and I hope they take the necessary steps to rectify this situation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzXIc3umbyprD0wTKFcJVYCpFTVPYTWpqe5jaT&fid=0x0:0x5fe33e293525f560"],"When":"2023-10-4"}]

Just what I needed to regain my strength. But I got told "don't forget to eat the noodles!" - took two more soups for takeaway. Thank you!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joshua (ThickBurger_Bites)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbIhhMlbxk7OIMpcaP-aSx2m75kt8-mqmXoXAJQ5K99gnxiff1zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went there on impulse for a late dinner after reading the reviews.

Food:
Ordered the House Special Pho, large. Was pleasantly surprised to see a bowl that wasn't as big as Pho 99's large. Pho was good, soup was just right, neither too salty or too rich. Noodles came in a good amount. Meats in the House Special Pho left a lot to be desired though. Not as much as I'd expect, half a beef ball, about 2 slices of beef steak, 3 slices of beef flank, tiny bits of beef tendon (which was really soft and delicious to my surprise), and a few bits of tripe here and there. Kinda disappointed with the amount of meat but as it was still pretty delicious,  I'll overlook it.
It comes with tea, beansprouts, basil leaves and lime on the side.
Refer to pictures for more information!

Price:
$10.24++/person

Service:
Nothing special. The lady sounded angry but I guess it's just the way she speaks.

Would I recommend?
Yes, go with family/small groups of friends as the place is rather small. I have not tried the other dishes, but will do so in the future :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQm5L8nR0xCYWH_i_xK2j7rwq5AZRQ2MMi8XQj&fid=0x0:0x136fcd8e7d93f071"],"When":"2017-1-8"},{"Name":"Stan S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJDG5_awNL6dSqZYIF4Ack_45eiH9so1tVgUCK8vlfNcXo0LDN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Not my First time here, busy place seems to be lots on the go even though there's only a few of us sitting down there's plenty of takeout or to go orders and the people are quite friendly and the price is reasonable. With the back door open it is quite cool in here however you do warm up when you're eating your food. I highly recommend this place the food is good the people are friendly service is excellent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNVX0tlIkif75DPDxyhNi5Wvo2ID-r_1D3o98A6&fid=0x0:0x136fcd8e7d93f071"],"When":"2021-2-13"}]

[{"Name":"Deb PS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2JrjvxBJWPrjHCwBxV9NiRybb9V5GJpynDBuSW5sd6snYZiMa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This restaurant is a very unassuming place. I would have never guessed it looked like this inside based on the exterior. It was very clean and the staff was super friendly with a great sense of humour.  The food was also very flavourful.  We all enjoyed our meal very much for not being a high end restaurant. Prices were very reasonable as well. Will be back for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCVOc1V1GanW0vAfXOMHxUlD7OXgwln2QuHrH_&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-10-24"},{"Name":"Ton V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWb4h6oZDMjakZ7o0kpJmjp_i41AvhfJ62KCrl6wCnDvytBpv4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hadn’t been for a while. Food was really good and service super friendly. Good size portions. I would prefer a menu with pictures though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxcvuP86fZtjp3Yr1fSFBnF1sXV3XGZII_RYI&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Ricardo Amanda Paliotti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1-tWR3oImGXb1bh0eJaBkqqB4lKa--eRLaWv99DtP2gOoadI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellently executed every time we visit. Flavors are on point. Always fun times there ! ☆☆☆☆☆ / Dec. 15th Sun 2024","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFnUCp9_Bgr50_ywSBFmDWPht7MdMv6uwMz8wv&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This place has been here since I was a kid. Glad to see it's still here and I'm visiting again after 20+ years. All I remember was that I liked their hot and sour soup.

Not really an authentic Szechuan restaurant. 30 years ago, most chinese cuisines were cooked by hong kongers or south chinese people. So, most of these dishes are going to be a southern take on it.

Hot and sour soup - price is awesome. $11 enough for at least 6 bowls. Souo base is missing a bit of flavor but it is jam packed with ingredients.

Drunken chicken - it was ok. Little on the salty side.

Shanghainese pan fried pork buns - these were probably the worst I've had. Not made in house and not properly pan fried. No juice, super dry, no fried bottom crust.

Bean curd wrapped pork dim sum - surprisingly this came out last. At least 20 min has passed. This is a steamed dish but it came out with dried edges like it was sitting on a dry heater. Taste was ok.

Mapo tofu - asked for extra spicy and extra numbing. Numbing was there but nowhere near real szechuan numbing. Was not spicy at all. Sauce was more oily than saucey.

The price point reflects the quality. Things are either mediocre or a complete miss. Would come again to try only the better stuff. Staff was friendly. Came to try to refill the tea way more times than normal. The iron goddess tea tastes much better than a lot of dim sum places elsewhere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsyXtmZVjFTpSM7j5XHpsMqasJjiN51hrkn9sk&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Sarah Grace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0P_FT3n0HZdmLMDEJ6UcRFNPyHbE7QJ8GW3gOL-SGGTFh-sFdQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good Chinese food, some of the best we’ve tried! Brought my family of 18 there and everyone had a very positive review to leave. The restaurant is clean, nicely decorated and the service is phenomenal, on top of amazing Chinese food. 100% recommend. Accommodated us no problem and efficiently being a large group.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4Zm-hsHEcTAf_11Ju8D7ypxHDl4umZ6xffmp0&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-5-26"},{"Name":"Marie Amin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKR0qp3fose5GsYts0dtMeJqwXo1MWNFSPwo4SjCtJGEbgYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I have been craving for a good Chinese food. We have done take out here many times before,  it's our first time dining in actually.   I am so amazed on how good the service is at this restaurant. Food came out fast and it was delicious.  Did not disappoint 🙌.  Thank you wahwing, we will definitely dine in again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVB0fCOEp8ge2kh842Ux2XpFXVwgqLutUtBbEG&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2023-8-5"},{"Name":"Amy Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUamHxgbXpYwrJI1uE5cJUYfe1wmxOQk5ygeSabzKwSDEQZmU3C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is my first time to dine in at this restaurant. The service is good but the food need some improvement. I ordered a noodle but the soup base taste salty . Chef should put less salt or no salt since the veggie already taste salty and the Chinese broccoli taste not much flavour.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCpErihv2HeGr4hQralU6fnwyOSS6XRaqyldOu&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2023-11-15"},{"Name":"Julio Cipriano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdiL69VWk_HhrY9vvXJcaFkLa2z0igCrSjghxutPFMYl05ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been going or ordering from here for 20+ years. Can’t remember a less than great meal!  Same applies today for lunch ginger beef, pork buns, even something simple like spring rolls all 5 *.  Tried the fried banana balls  and mango ice cream.  So so good!  Staff went out of their way to make sure my mother (little older) was taken care of. Congrats on 30 years and hope your here for another 30 for my kids to keep coming to!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ricardo Esteves","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhLIO2qt-2RQR0_aQCihSuDY8549ydYAIf_Ebc863j0CC6irdH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow!🤩 Best pizza I ever ate, hands down. This place takes the cake! Not sure how they cram all those toppings on and still manage to keep such a light, airy crispy crust. I’m visiting from Ontario and I saw the flyer in my Mom’s mail. She never orders pizza any more because it always sucks. Mom had never ordered from here before, but I decided to try it any ways. We were both so pleasantly surprised at how beautiful and delicious the pizza was. I may not live here, but my mom does and she will definitely order from this place again. Try it. You won’t be disappointed! 🤤 (we had the Juliet 😋)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfcmZDOkXuXHHfApnVXrXSE03TOb8qP-MbB4q0&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were in a time crunch and asked if we could get our pizza in a rush - they said yes and they delivered on their promise! Our pizza was tasty, hot and fresh, and we had plenty of time to make it to our next appointment. Our server was friendly and prompt. We’ve been here a few times and will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLly5sdKZqb1_imp4OGBRs4Dhktp9UI7we_mRH&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Grant M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRWL_i5cZiVpXExK1H8xMkwx4_6CHC_xRkP2HoYZIVJehiW1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's been awhile since I've had Me N Ed's Pizza, and it certainly didn't disappoint at all. It's still fantastic after all these years.

We decided to order a few pies for the NFL US Thanksgiving games on Thursday for delivery. And they arrived at a decent time, and still fairly hot still.

It's a little pricey, BUT you definitely get what you pay for. ( They definitely don't "SKIMP" on the toppings ) as you can see from the pictures provided.

We made up our own Pies two of which were the personal ones with their Gluten Free Crust. Which friends said were excellent. I myself made one up of original crust and Tomato sauce with Capicollo, Salami, Pepperoni, and Bacon. And it was outstanding and loaded with toppings. And the Capicollo was some of the best I've definitely had in a long time.

Great Pies and I/We will be definitely ordering more often from Me N Ed's Pizza Parlor...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZ8c0Q2gaomnnrh8SVY4SW_UCMu_Uc0GDiZvLh&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"J wico","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKFLTpvMyLxVfHKit3ZJqPccY65Bl-YeNGA1wEu8pZSIRWpww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pros:
- Family and team friendly. Great family atmosphere, which is always a plus for me when dining with our toddler.
- Considering how busy it was, the food came out quick.
- Staff are friendly.

Cons:
- There are 6 other pizza places within walking distance and I'd put it towards the bottom. This doesn't mean the pizza is bad, there's just too much decent competition.
- Price. 2 smalls were $36 before tax and tip and it was today's special...

Would I go again? Maybe for a team party or a kid's bday.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1MNiIwxPsTfI_D1Gyey22Wh_Gy-8bxTa2Weij&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Lord Stanley (Lifepilot)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzQPaJP0C4QgYze9YWfcg4vOQGSlA7Fi1WI2IqpyzPqwuzcItLsg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We popped in for a quick pizza 🍕 before hockey 🥅 🏒 game as we really felt like pizza. Saw a few pizza shops and then came across Me-n-Ed’s which we knew from Burnaby.  We got a table right away. Staff were friendly and restaurant was clean. We saw the Salmon & Roasted Garlic pizza with goat cheese. Seemed interesting, so we ordered it. It was absolutely delicious 😋 couldn’t fault a single thing about it. Crust was perfect and very flavorful! Yum! Pricing is also fair!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXkyEI6QptUTCf1-w_s5__bZl3WIuNYKdP0VLm&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2023-12-16"},{"Name":"Al","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJke_H51lEVtqmQ6Mwhj0R5MqDW7L2xLlIdf0sg4kPFJFF0D9I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great location, very nice place with lots of room. Waitresses were welcoming and polite. The food was ok but had better Me & Ed's pizza. Chicken had a little bit of weird taste on BBQ chicken. Overall, it was ok. Place has a lot of free parking and good location. They have kids menu which comes with ice cream.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIEpEpFb1gDy7vAh00FHxcrupgV651s-LKiH6S&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2023-8-7"},{"Name":"Victoria M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4EhJg4Rc2VuzKf5_JHxexyjVp-afUrXeUpfgefDqByTw_eqXIfw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an amazing meal here on Remembrance Day. The food here is always great. We tried their Mighty Caesar pizza for the first time…definitely will recommend. So many toppings which all pair ridiculously good together. Only critique I have is that I would expect quite a bit more beef to be on the nachos for the $4.50 price tag.

BUT enough about the food, I just want to point out Izzy for being the best server I’ve seen in a long while. She was beyond swamped, legit had the entire room to herself. She needed bills paid, food cleared, food delivered and to make the drinks on top of that….and she did it all. If she wasn’t doing all that she was answering multiple phone calls in between. Heck I’m surprised she wasn’t in the back cooking the pizzas herself at the rate she was going. Plus she was personable and extremely kind within all the chaos. Total superstar. 10/10 will come again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSa86tUfJWBd2NRD4nRR1FBYS_U1NiczNltakJ&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2023-11-12"},{"Name":"Joanne Antoniak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTQwhPcO13h_HhVjJVUrwpHjU5MeesKhPrxV5pA1ymdZ1edFkY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"10/10.
Such a fun place for a father's day adventure.  The restaurant is large; nicely decorated; and very clean. Service was outstanding!
The pizza was so yummy!!  Not your regular pizza "dough"; more like a thin crust flakey cracker - so tasty.  The toppings were super generous and fresh. The  Nachos were HUGE; served on a large platter so there were toppings on every chip.
Really fantastic food.  We will definitely go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrwCYhvy5QqYykCBedXwx96v2e64SasZCSs-eB&fid=0x0:0x723248c50d21e55f"],"When":"2023-6-17"}]

[{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Conveniently located near the SkyTrain and Coquitlam Centre. The staff were super friendly, and the lobster dunk, ribs, and steak were absolutely delicious—highly recommended! The ambiance was cozy and inviting. Will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5lCB7UYXuKglJCHEcLCgizeN6zWPuTR_mKGf-&fid=0x0:0xa8c5636616493c53"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Parya Salehi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbh4w9SWNAXiJGP9wxzBZJLCCi91QA6ycLqmxcg8Loj48hcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Tonight, I had the worst dining experience of my life. Due to power outages, we decided to have dinner at Mr. Mike’s, a place we’ve been to before. Unfortunately, tonight was absolutely horrible.

First, we placed our orders, and it took an unusually long time for the food to arrive. When it finally did, my plate was completely cold. The staff took it back to warm it up, but that was just the beginning.

I ordered a medium-rare steak, as I always do, but it came out rare. The meat was incredibly tough, making it almost impossible to cut and chew. On my first bite, I nearly choked and had to be helped by a nearby table. Shockingly, the manager didn’t seem to care about the situation at all. They simply removed the cost of the meal from the bill, without offering any real apology or concern.

I was left struggling to breathe, and the only comment the manager made was, “You ordered a medium-rare steak.” I always order medium-rare, and I know the difference between rare, medium-rare, and medium. This steak was not only rare but also so tough that it was hard to cut in the first place!

I am deeply disappointed with the lack of care or professionalism shown during this experience. I will definitely think twice before returning.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pam Delfino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVou97WNj_X-lZ_I6WAUZr7ELzzqVVEd-LYy7ydp9dEDslErRA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fun place to enjoy a tasty meal and some brews! Very friendly service! ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2j1QY0G9zmTHxjbcYdSBuKt4DJPhlAhXMfv8Y&fid=0x0:0xa8c5636616493c53"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Haas Eskandanian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9IADx9YthZR1vOZb8_xNjKOZYe9q3dvXswpievCacAQi6Xm67=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I don’t know how this restaurant is still in business but I’m sure they will one of the next chains going out of business soon.
Ribeye steak was cold, chewy and very late on the table! Don’t waste your night and money here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvsQaKgpL9nNiQwP8NJZXjFXnjvxN3hLywRHA9&fid=0x0:0xa8c5636616493c53"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Fatemeh Mohammadnejad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_vxxy0DRS_-_0DEH_6td4t10kAYXF76jysJTuML9DO4CHIlU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My go to restaurant for any occasion! Great atmosphere, delicious food, and always a wonderful experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMciwfSqYoAS6jb1sLCwQDbHILVCq5VqSndNvfO&fid=0x0:0xa8c5636616493c53"],"When":"2024-11-1"},{"Name":"Richard Filgate","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqY0CH1XgGWiOwrSaofbVKHTYfrBSo2qLPtYgxiWh2x5oOWqQp=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Today I had lunch at Mr Mike's steak house in Coquitlam bc
Order the classic Mr Mike Burger by mistake and even though it was just meat and cheese and bun it was quite delicious our waitress was polite and caring and would recommend eating here for lunch 👍👍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzd8FS8nOKEA4BK9aYw7JL2wsCQzLe4hjBFH_c&fid=0x0:0xa8c5636616493c53"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"ZuffaLtdDanaWhite","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6gGe3NbbgwlJVAvgbTW4PyVUNZSvDx9TwIaijDSbPkD-WMrs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time to Mr. Mikes. Expectations going in was not what I experienced. If you’re in I suggest you try and order an 8oz striploin (medium rare) w/ chimichuri & the keto option. Salad was amazing in itself. Steak was on point! Soft and succulent & full of flavour. The waitress Cassidy was very attentive and came by our table 4x’s to check up and bring extra items. Very pleasant experience! Will definitely be returning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUPThP2riuEei0GIGcgF645Nxz2_aVP7UHJ817&fid=0x0:0xa8c5636616493c53"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Denny Hui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXuGFgsc9U61TCKDV21ZHXILH-aGrlI-hjZswBeAYg3LhKf97Y3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Went to Mr. Mike's after my sons soccer game last week. Restaurant is modern and spacious. Seats are comfortable.

Staff was friendly. Atmosphere was lively and welcoming.

Food on the other hand was ok. My son ordered the Sirloin and Lobster Mac. Sirloin was tough to cut and chew.  Lobster mac bland taste. Our burgers also bland.

I ordered the Nashville Hot Chicken sandwich. Flavour was good but chicken patty was very small.

Overall ok experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkhqoEFfTPptXrtv_oqjfXPOjpc-iRD4blLilS&fid=0x0:0xa8c5636616493c53"],"When":"2024-2-11"}]

[{"Name":"O T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNMZRDyPmCXOIYr2knffcKqnpyxzie7qHVjFWoC2-ZmJX5_do-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We visited this restaurant twice, and unfortunately, both experiences were disappointing. First, the portion sizes were shockingly small. We’re not big eaters, and we don’t expect massive portions, but we did expect enough food to feel satisfied given the prices. Both times, we left still feeling hungry.
On one visit, the server got our order wrong and brought pancakes instead of waffles. We decided to let it slide, but the pancakes turned out to be terrible, so we asked for them to be replaced. To our surprise, we were charged for both meals.
Overall, we were really let down by the food quality, service, and value for money. It’s not a place we’d return to.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwTnR0sk7n_ze7mP7n_f-jOtfF0efbBswqsPUQ&fid=0x0:0x7ea0a39de7ea97b3"],"When":"2024-11-21"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We took my mother-in-law out for a late lunch on a Friday afternoon. My husband enjoyed his blueberry milkshake and we had two different veggie burgers, both nice. Dated atmosphere. Server was friendly and prompt. Worth checking out if you want some comfort food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzyFOKm-V4IPKAvAN5BodO9u64aX-PhSOkmL_D&fid=0x0:0x7ea0a39de7ea97b3"],"When":"2024-6-29"},{"Name":"Kate Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIr0wyxbETF1OIwtaRI7q7gqmb4Gyi3lrLYLvt0zWijOigiOvk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Consistently delivers delectable dishes. My friend introduced me to the franchise’s blueberry milkshake and it is a delicious treat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuUI6nj548BZ1C4vgDjZOQjyjkUik-0PgfsNEv&fid=0x0:0x7ea0a39de7ea97b3"],"When":"2024-8-17"},{"Name":"Y Asr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUiVODPcX4RwOd_Ul80uRIkFuz2OcFSnrFGXThpJ_cRU33YGpqN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely outstanding service! Marco was attentive, friendly, and went above and beyond to ensure we had an exceptional dining experience. His recommendations were spot on, and he always seemed to anticipate our needs before we even had to ask. It’s rare to find such genuine hospitality, and he truly made our evening memorable. We’ll definitely be back – all thanks to his wonderful service!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ray Chow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnHoKzUHN2laU2bSp7bGdZulx8wlTrl7fcyIV2n_GmA8fi001AHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was good at this location the steak was cooked to perfection and tasted good the pasta was not bad either.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkkWX1s6vBv8MErdPfUPNiztR3S8TLwXV9QU6g&fid=0x0:0x7ea0a39de7ea97b3"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"Izmet Barranco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiQo1jy483UmDOGk0DLpOPmwFqDxOxzKBlrj-9MTXzn_Zhoww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for a late dinner with my sister. Service was quick and efficient as you would expect.  Served was attentive and courteous!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9oKhWjY86cmXTrWKTbI47nPnGHGbsDpa9ELzG&fid=0x0:0x66fc3602c0cc67ed"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Jessy J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHNRFw0Z_JgaU0TxGr1Pv5X-w9V6JzR0bnCuTDlGr_7pfsbx_k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Our first visit to this ramen noodle restaurant with the family was delightful! The atmosphere is spacious and welcoming, and even though we had to wait briefly, it was only about 5 minutes, which was very acceptable. The service was excellent, with the staff bringing out kids' utensils right away, which we appreciated.

The highlight of the meal was definitely the noodle soup. The broth was creamy with a distinct bonito fish flavor, making it a unique take on our ramen. We've never experienced a creamy base with shoyu before, so it was quite interesting.

Their Gomae was quite tasty. Instead of using spinach and peanut sauce, they used Choy Sum with sesame paste sauce.

The only minor drawback was the soft-boiled egg, which was slightly overcooked.

Overall, the service was up to par and we had a great experience. We'll definitely be back to try more of their dishes!" the family was delightful! The atmosphere is spacious and welcoming, and even though we had to wait briefly, it was only about 5 minutes, which was very acceptable. The service was excellent, with the staff bringing out kids' utensils right away, which we appreciated.

The highlight of the meal was definitely the noodle soup. The broth was creamy with a distinct bonito fish flavor, making it a unique take on shoyu ramen. We've never experienced a creamy base with shoyu before, so it was quite interesting. The only minor drawback was the soft-boiled egg, which was slightly overcooked.

Overall, the service was up to par and we had a great experience. We'll definitely be back to try more of their dishes!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPovmOXlxrn71FdseJvAjANGOudb6lv_Ph6vheL&fid=0x0:0x66fc3602c0cc67ed"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"melissa choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKPYCcnHjMsXKLjSAR5QRLFI-pwNjpHDAAO3nrNqEuOCcrf9A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I came alone. there were maybe 4 tables with people seated and already eating. One other guest came after me. It took forever them to ask for my order. They got the other table before i did. They never checked up on me after placing my food after me. They were not attentive. Food was okay. Wasn’t amazed by it though. Will not be returning. Overall atmosphere was clean and calming. I personally will not be returning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzaN_LsU9Kwak7qgzrRh5nUJIoBMK7KF226Z2f&fid=0x0:0x66fc3602c0cc67ed"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Chi Hsi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcBbxQUmUDBINWW8gpiVBRZkPGVAvZUVKaxZbYRVQUj9Y0ACg0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came here with our preschooler on a Thursday night at 6pm and was seated immediately. The service was great and quick in response when we raised our hand when we needed anything. They brought the kids utensils, scissors, bowl and cup right away.

I ordered the U. B. B. extra to share with my preschooler. Rich, flavourful, and creamy broth which I found a bit too salty for my liking. I was able to finish the end of the broth with the extra bowl of free rice. My husband doesn't finish the broth whenever we have ramen so it seemed a shame to dump it. We were able to get a to-go container for his remaining broth.

They also have an universal washroom for handicap and any gender so it was easier for my preschooler to reach the sink to wash her hands or go with my husband instead.

We'd recommend this place for families for sure!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMye_HMVe1iRiTuUeVDUU-tRMeahxBkdlzSUbA&fid=0x0:0x66fc3602c0cc67ed"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious ramen with splendid, rich and creamy broth. Tried the black tan tan men which came with a bowl of rice and the flavours were great. The black sesame ground pork was both sweet and salty and went very well with the rice. The U.B.B. Extra ramen came with thick noodles that had great texture and the broth was so rich and complex. The service was great and the place was clean. Solid and satisfying ramen place. There are also complimentary sesame seed and chili powder toppings on each table.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOZzYuriQu4IYkOTSb_x2nmC5vxcMD9MWz02sD&fid=0x0:0x66fc3602c0cc67ed"],"When":"2024-3-25"},{"Name":"Megan H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIku9KV44jqgA8L-HCiMZoBBhlSnQF2rqxPqsFbb_vW5iUOog=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Thank you for great experience! :D
Vegetarian ramen coconut soup is new to me it was good.
We loved salt and seaweed sause on table for changing it soup own flavor.
Garlic add on was bit over cooked taste was bitter.. more soft is better.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Fat Cook Papa (Fat Cook Papa)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJUpgi6nqSgMlDhQ45Yjl_gk21krVh2zgBl_CxlCp6gK1X_Jg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Coming from Toronto..

Love and enjoy great views from the patio.

Fish and Fries - both of their batter and fries were overpowdered and little salty. Also, I'm quite disappointed with the fries portion.
Unfortunately, two pieces of COD were first serving. Apparently, they looked like cooking with different preparation timing. One was great with thick cut crunchy exterior and soft interior, other piece hasn't fully fried to perfection. It's greasy and less crispy.

The Downtowner Pizza - pleasantly surprised by the amazing flavor honey drizzle on pizza. The heat of the pizza then warm the honey as it mixed with the sauce and toppings.

Wings - no impressed.  Originally ordered with Honey garlic sauce toppings style.
Unfortunately, wings were made with buffalo style and tasted like they half coated them with tobasco by mistaken.

We have to say they were by far some of the worst wings I have ever eaten. It's tasted like korean BBQ fried chicken wing.

A little bit pricey and service does need a lot of improvement.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0be5JHmIITlNBtCmwiDVXPzfNar9iOeCiuLah&fid=0x0:0xbbadd84419ac02a9"],"When":"2024-6-4"},{"Name":"Amy Adams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyVH38TT4RWGwG_4hraWZRuXvb1BELFJJQ_LmMrQJEwE8qxzQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Salted and pepper Wings are hard and dried, only drumette, no wingette. So disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOR5_ZcPVXhC0Wp4WEPzD8P0o66YgMQsBgVyxdG&fid=0x0:0xbbadd84419ac02a9"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Bekah French","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiYLh-7emQ9AthzE2N_CGxwmtRUdZguPeMRuVIWmhyOtllxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Views and location are amazing. Would love to visit again in the summer and sit out on their big patio we ordered the soup of the day (chicken and vegetable), it was okay. And we shared a meat lovers pizza. We requested half with no cheese (for me) but the pizza came out first time incorrect (it was half cheese only, half meat). They quickly remade the pizza and the base was very yummy. I’d rate the pizza as a whole 3/5. We found the service very friendly and welcoming.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwfumHC1VMOXhld8Vw1mT60IYGLKPdkLMIuntT&fid=0x0:0xbbadd84419ac02a9"],"When":"2022-11-16"},{"Name":"Ali Mehrizi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXWq9cg0fjpkngwNGme387YM4kRUdnI6Pf_Z33gzbG1mkoqze49=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Beautiful views of town (all the way to Burnaby) and good pub food. Fries were one of the best I have had. Drinks are good and beer flights are generous. A quick and good place if you’re in the more residential part of northern Coquitlam.

I just wish the service was more courteous. We had to wait quite a bit to get our server’s attention when we wanted to order extra food and drinks. When the food came (in reasonable time), she came to check on us only when we were almost done. On the bright side, I don’t think this is the service culture at Fairways; the two other persons who helped us sit and get a clean/sanitized table were very nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4yxOEC8MmM2niMejhmuf8tooer3a0pejf_8Sj&fid=0x0:0xbbadd84419ac02a9"],"When":"2020-10-22"},{"Name":"Janice Robinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwXAghB0kKeZJUcp8jSMN3IavGDPtUMtF57yQo1h9gD5800GlzTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The last time I dined at this restaurant, it was called Hazards, and we lived 5 minutes away. I had the blackened salmon tacos, which were very flavourful and expertly prepared. I will definitely be back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eun R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtFP78dUqzbrC3sUP2EUQ7OgKF-9eTaViByIOG1MgbwrrOyEABLw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food quality is good, portion is generous, and servers are friendly and attentive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYiB0HybsweJ0t28YswxQYL6q4xyemOS01_F9f&fid=0x0:0xbbadd84419ac02a9"],"When":"2024-7-23"},{"Name":"Ve7123","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI37Dp_jMOGKDkNZyR_8bRIASwIfCrsxmFZJBEVbUjSJ5H-kA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I am living nearby ,we're always coming here.

[{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We visited on a weeknight for dinner. There was only us and 1 other table, but the delivery pickups were constant. On a rainy night, I can understand why.

The food is fresh, hot and delicious. Super comforting flavours.

When delivery people arrived without their warming bag, staff would ask them to retrieve it. This ensured the food would stay warm.

I would highly recommend the seasonal specialty, Khao Soi. This was our first time trying it, and I'd definitely order it again. This dish comes with crispy and soft noodles. When you stir it into the sauce, the fried noodles stay crispy, giving you an amazing combination of textures. Beautifully balanced and satisfying dish.

We also enjoyed the crispy wraps, chicken satay and Pa-Nang Curry.

Very relaxing environment, and I'm glad we popped in. Chada Thai is a fantastic local Thai restaurant that has been in the community for many years.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgs6Rb5cfnF84J2qgMTdFMob8BlMuzG2vmaGLv&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Tiffany Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTMFXTr99Nvibpsf_X84FJETCu3bBQbDSclTYmi4Zeid_pQeVX=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely scrumptious authentic Thai food!!! It is a stable restaurant on our family’s go-to bi-weekly!! The air in this local mom-n-pops Thai restaurant is always filled with the most delicious-food-heavenly-aroma flowing from the kitchen :)
Top notch service, monthly and seasonal special menu items, always a good surprise, keeping the customers’ dine in and take out experience exciting!
Love it. Will be back again next week!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5i0hMWKO1NoxYJ1hz-r9q_LAgP16LoMW8IBlT&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Kareen Cadiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLw3OKuvTnvabIzBQ3y_Jc5m3vIpEHN-6lVpcIUOUmxioiQzg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of our go to places for Thai food in Tri-cities, can’t go wrong with either dine in or takeout. Their lunch specials are such a good deal (pictured here). And of course the food is consistently yummy, fresh ingredients and good portions.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-5cRjh_efXpw9-7c5P9WAgZ6JpuWrYyw4MPJE&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Charmaine Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMK-vcbBIxyt_pQwyKQmCk5dMi5qXNyvwWP-HdCaK4MzQ7dCIb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love the authentic Thai food here! The Tom yum soup is irresistible. Green curry fragrance is very good that I can finish the bowl of rice. So far this is one of the best Thai cuisine I have in Vancouver. The lunch menu is still very decent in price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTDJde8-gQXH92NluWv3gqrtQt309FXJTYEGFh&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Parichat B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3tpKxJcU4Lx_ecgrcufj6LfbAj_OdEqTtupyTak05ILPS6QkOMA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best thai food in town, really yummy authentic dishes in affordable prrice.
All staff was so nice, great in recommendation for a menu and spicy level.
The restaurant is clean and easy to access by walikng from Lincolne station.
I definately go there again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqEm0G5fpF7dbYNyoStcPpYC-5skgUuqbPXtJY&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Aidan Siu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWc1EBOVHC3agFY5CmQn_KE37Zb3iZR8UikBgzoOS_YFnx5fxiO=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hidden Thai Gem in Coquitlam! For a delightful Thai culinary experience, try Beef Pad Thai, a perfect balance of savory and sweet with tender beef, stir-fried rice noodles, and crunchy peanuts. Pineapple Fried Rice with Shrimp is another must-try, offering a vibrant mix of succulent shrimp, sweet pineapple chunks, and fragrant jasmine rice. Finally, savor the rich and aromatic Red Chicken Curry, where tender chicken pieces in a creamy, spicy coconut milk sauce infused with red chili. Each dish is a flavorful journey that will leave your taste buds tingling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuMZvozTcY-cgvXAYiOFiAAv451NQXKZubUuHV&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Dan Peterson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbNeFUlLkRmjcX25zxpAW7H_0IDjY0P_SfdPGvxnigSNv-OQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Met up for lunch with a friend and we shared two items-shrimp pad Thai ($15 off the lunch special menu) and chicken yellow curry (the sauce was sooo good)
Portions are generous, food was delicious and the service was terrific.
The food was so good that we both ordered additional menu items togo.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDrQcz7So_FgPV4M_TJ8yvUjsUhEaOgy7ohjCm&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Cat King","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVs0w4Gi6wbbwHozHIMXCxGOYXWgHMRV7NGZtPTmRmCUIubsOlj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my mother-in-law's favourite Thai food whenever she visits from Ottawa. We've been here a few times already, and we all believe the presentation of the food is on point every time.  Their flavour is great as well. We always order the Thai chilli sauce and crispy wraps. Their noodle soup dish was good too, but I forgot its name😅 unfortunately, this dish was a monthly special. I wish it came back though. Hopefully it will :) The only downside of the restaurant is that when we pick up the food, it  isn't as good as eating in at the restaurant. But that's the case for all restaurants so. Still, I would say the best Thai in Coquitlam. Just make sure to get their coconut rice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOb87rj0mXOnoCwN0B8gg8gk6BIrvt8yWQgk5EI&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-7-7"}]

Though I’m not a fan of spicy food, I keep coming back for their marinated pork loin. Their daily specials are also consistently great!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwp-rTWoJE1-fixtIROQGo3OHdrpllIlTRIxo3\u0026fid=0x0:0xc0a787d1e6fe6e2f"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Emman Parangue","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVI9VRFeIcmRJMCwuACY7DPU-J0uLE5dfq_qzX4ftVe_cCtEQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is really good! Serving is quite big. I ordered their Original Pork Cutlet and it comes with 2 cutlets with gravy, salad, rice and miso soup. They are really generous with the amount of gravy that they pour over my cutlets. The sauce is good and it has a slight taste of sweetness with it. So good!! Will come back again to try the other items in the menu🥰","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhXhBgFnN7bh9tnCg-Fg_wpW3IhFjnaja6xEfq\u0026fid=0x0:0xc0a787d1e6fe6e2f"],"When":"2024-2-1"},{"Name":"Matchalun Ahn (Helena)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2Bd8THUCtdw7ztqD6ief55FJ-ON2lSm6B1WgHBBqqrmyPPkai=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good place. Enough room for customer, food came out very hot and fresh. They did forget to bring us the coke we ordered though. Lady was kind, everything was good and I didn't feel sick after eating from here. Would definitely recommend. Portion sizes are also pretty big.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOEml2YX6gPy5kKzTWBq3xG_6khb9Oldx7xG-u0\u0026fid=0x0:0xc0a787d1e6fe6e2f"],"When":"2024-1-5"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious chicken cutlet with huge portions (2 large cutlets per order). Sauce is different from katsu pork (Japanese variety) and it is a bit sweeter. It also came with white rice, corn, and coleslaw. Luckily we shared between two people as we weren’t very hungry and it was perfect. We added the Korean kimchi soup for $1.99 and it made for a good meal. Restaurant itself is not very big but has a decent number of seats. Parking on street or nearby at Coquitlam Centre parking lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPD8Gr4Peopux9Nf_46mpMlnLcZvvQYSB0zSg-z\u0026fid=0x0:0xc0a787d1e6fe6e2f"],"When":"2023-7-21"},{"Name":"J Cheung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWL0BZ5HaxRtwQYUfB73F38XNmwqlCBtIEfl5nLaJnfdzlxAdl2qA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very big and thick port cutlets. The original gives you two pieces. I noticed the salads and rice portions got a bit smaller than few years ago but the price and what you get is very good deal. Tastes great as well","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXx24uZbcCDuZAqpt2tc-nT1gN9Z_2WXvZvzdJ1nj1GOrlWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I order take out regularly and it always delivers crispy and warm. Just an easy comfort food that tastes great! I recommend getting the sauce on side if you dine there.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"JP Cebuana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL89tm0m3JCB9sakwdX7ONp6bsswHXgvHJZdqDn87LGVaKivpE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Surprisingly amazing. Huge portions at a reasonable price. We had the Original Pork Cutler, Chicken Cutlet and Mushroom Burger Steak. They all come with rice, salad. We ordered 3 plates for 2 people and it was too much we gad to pack the other one to go. My favourite so far is the Chicken Cutlet. Highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPI-bGiVcKxX6H5E1D_rRa2rOjmFnteUYeTUcZ\u0026fid=0x0:0xc0a787d1e6fe6e2f"],"When":"2018-12-23"},{"Name":"Julie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6iqNbgJ99pEVigrdmqTpMQQRCYbL7zrrvCytBAxs45Tk47A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food and good price. Always leave full and satisfied","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPu3U2jxgGFSBVTghG5FxjuQWqfJQTult0EccbH\u0026fid=0x0:0xc0a787d1e6fe6e2f"],"When":"2024-8-17"}]
