[{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a great find! We loved the view of the ocean, the tea was devine, and food was yummy. They make their own sourdough bread as well. We liked our tea so much we bought a bag to enjoy at home. The drive was fun and we felt like we were far from the busy city. I look forward to visiting again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZxwjvX0-_n5Rw5TG4lMSWVZcFPreeqJFIEDBs&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-11-26"},{"Name":"Randy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSb09if5u7GFHKGhGpQrqg8HJqBQmEd3IDfG068mgp2Ghgte_T=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Booked a boat ride up to Indian arm for the Christmas tea festival. The spot was beautifully decorated. The hospitality was great  information on all the teas we sampled was very informative. It was a great night for a boat ride. We thoroughly enjoyed our whole evening there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQ0PN6AkM3zQ4jMdx90HeKNMpjssL8_HNhnI2D&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-11-29"},{"Name":"Hanah Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsf0-pXkdSTqGJecZlxwp3Bbml3NhidicNq-zEzWIQ7fexEd8QYg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's unbelievable that their fabulous afternoon tea towel was not just tasty but made with quality organic ingredients! Tha fantastic nature scene over the glass wall is a huge plus!
It was a great discover for our family trip in Vancouver trip this year and we will definitely visit again to try their quality tea options (and the rest of food menu).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_WM495E_CrwYXdyVTKzLVd2LApPNOALoKqHGH&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-4-16"},{"Name":"Jordan Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLFsjfnS-oiBTX7iRzPhMh-PXM_FEBemeI_C6-8CDhB4SzDFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a wonderful experience at 8 Corners! I loved the remote location as it felt like an adventure getting there. It was also very calm and the vibes were chill.

The building is sitting right off the water so there's a great view of the lake and mountains.

The service staff was very welcoming and friendly made me and my partner feel cozy and comfy.

The food was delicious and I liked that it felt homemade and fancy compared to being made elsewhere and shipped in.

All in all, a great experience, would highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWr3Obt5HJqdC_akITzItu4a7HFkDNtbbgkgpw&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-6-10"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They’re only open 2 days a week from 11am to 4pm so make sure that you visit them during that time!

They have authentic green tea imported all the way from South Korea and it clearly shows that they really care about their tea and knows their stuff.

The owner came out multiple times during our time there to ask how we were enjoying the tea and the sandwiches. Do t get me wrong, they can be a bit pricy but I think the whole experience is well worth it.

It takes a bit of an effort to make it out there but it only adds to the charm of the place. I would love to try out their high tea experience next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN02qEQo0Hmand3R-ml_1CphZqZtsdy5csJ8XAb&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2022-9-18"},{"Name":"Jihyun Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6QtUokr8e5CT7oQaQrOHr0gHr2y_Oz1hLcsCumlH7cfOpRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for a nice afternoon tea place and did some research to find out 8 Corners. Their photos on Google well represent what you’d get from the afternoon tea experience. Id say this is a best hidden gem i found recently. Stunning view, great selection of teas. Well explained finger foods and great staff as well. This place seems that it’d be nice for a wedding. The price for the afternoon tea is reasonable but dont forget you also get the view and inner peace.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNnUGZ9L1l8FJ5k1JcwxQ5IZ8fpqom7N5_35C-K&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-7-9"},{"Name":"Terri Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdHMQamP6ntk6cmD8m9VHj4cLgJWNXVSwfy5Jk1_ks8LpnASP1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Please check their website and READ through everything. This is not your commercial high tea cafe located on a big street. It's literally located deep inside a park and make reservations online. Very unique experience away from the city life. Just the drive alone is an experience. The food was ok though. The atmosphere and surrounding makes it worth it. The building next door seems to be a wedding venue too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNONYUafefHXdt0EAWE1xLMDL_yyi5ZA-70Yrhy&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2022-12-29"},{"Name":"Angela Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVbKkg8N4MGypttPdK2tiQGP6agzZ49zgTH9Ca58X1Et2jkg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Who knew this was hidden inside Belcarra! A very nice surprise. You need to make reservations and pay ahead of time ($65 a person and parties of 2-4). You can also attempt to drop by for their regular menu. We tried a regular set as well as a vegan set. Our favorite parts were the savoury sandwiches on their homemade sourdough bread. We wished that the desserts were more varied - they were heavily matcha/red bean centered and on the less sweet side because of the Korean owned establishment. The teas were great, and service was good as well. The road in isn’t paved, so be aware. The tea room can be a little stuffy since it’s an open kitchen, but it didn’t bother us too much. Overall, the grounds are lovely and it’s a unique experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPd8lODHOm9KVj3JShfBtYR6Og9Z6GwdRo9-s5U&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-12-7"}]

[{"Name":"Minipa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLkpsoXCUt-uCoPDrB_Mv40ZqSioejOqdNEdMQaklHEBDE1W1x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was decently fast, and apparently there are some risks if you park across (but they do reimburse your parking up to 1 hour).

The server went for the memorization tactic when it comes to taking orders (many pho restaurants do this although I personally dislike it). They got one thing wrong as we indeed had some individual changes to the bowls, but it was no biggy.

Overall, the food was good, service was fast and the price was reasonable.

4/5","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhjF1DO521SCQmow92NjRqTSN2GI-GG8Ud1WUt&fid=0x0:0xc1264c5355d4288f"],"When":"2023-5-30"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really enjoyed their house special, and the portions were so ample I had to take half home. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"PTTN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIVXQhrf96EsaD027m51yX-Uvc0Kdpt5n8uGLLy_w4vgEoUTTPd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This establishment won awards for good reason. I could not find a fault in anything we experienced there. We went after they received that national award. It was busy and the anticipated wait time was over an hour and a half! We were greeted with warmth and patience. As if we were the only people there. We ordered a drink and had it on the patio as we waited for our table. Truth be told, the owner got us in in under half and hour so we were EXTREMELY lucky and grateful. Drinks were delicious. Food was phenomenal. I can't stress enough the attention to detail these people have for every portion of dinner service. Well done and well deserved! Keep it up!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqaM9dL5KXg_NjYfLhmt2xgQmSQG7gSLfz1pdv&fid=0x0:0x914dae93368664f4"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"William Ting","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVROj5tKGe8MbrrNOhk8-59eVUA_x7_lmH6eRP-mRZLTzD9H6iPlA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our group of 4 had 3 pizzas and 1 pasta. It was more than enough for us! Delicious Naples style pizza.

A variety of unique flavours that you would not get anywhere else. It worked out to be $30 per person.

An absolutely great deal!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRnjle-60dbG3m6hECOokahqlC60-9Fo0TyW5d&fid=0x0:0x914dae93368664f4"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"Jacob Gilbert","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrUQKdbxQwz9AjjpsHYxJOv7HC_xp-KAOyVPcTzB05b6NESS0F=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely amazing experience! From the moment we walked in, we were warmly greeted at the door. Despite the restaurant being very busy (a testament to the incredible food), we were seated within 20 minutes at the pizza bar, which turned out to be such a treat. Watching the fire oven in action and seeing the pizzas being crafted added a whole new level of excitement to our visit.

We were served by the general manager, Vita, who was outstanding! She made us feel so welcome, almost like we were guests in her own home. Her warmth and attentiveness truly elevated the experience.

We ordered pizza, pasta, and truffle fries—all of which were phenomenal. Every bite was bursting with flavor, and it’s clear the quality of the food matches the hype.

Highly recommend this place to anyone looking for top-notch food and a great atmosphere. We’ll definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6fksMOtEGkiPkVmh_o_SVQGOJZ_x19PUAFUCQ&fid=0x0:0x914dae93368664f4"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Clara Chau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIoMWRC0cDGP4nCpQ1_Zdm86daXS0A0KJbVAa9QczqqbfD7fWIZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here after seeing a lot of buzz on Instagram and it lived up to the hype! We came for lunch and I suggest coming right at opening to make sure you get a table on weekend without waiting for too long. The pizza was delicious and had generous toppings. What I liked about the pizza is how thin the crust is but at the same time, it's chewy on the inside with a nice crunch on the outside. Each pizza was the perfect size to cut into 4 slices for sharing and we ended up ordering 4 different pizzas to try. The gnocchi was baked beautifully but the combo of cheese was too much for me but the rest of the table loved it! We also ordered the truffle risotto croquettes and it was my favourite dish. The truffle wasn't overpowering and it was fried really well on the outside. We have plans to come back another time to try other pizzas.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMlkIWYpKBwpgHUbEb7lAPZzbum8KOcKcBnMlbv&fid=0x0:0x914dae93368664f4"],"When":"2024-12-4"},{"Name":"Adriana Neradovicova","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqZwq8WG9dS74sb6OU2T1ULrs1Txr0UHRpcfrPsiphWlDMuA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After a long year I came back with my friends to dine in your marvellous restaurant. My last experience was amazing! Your restaurant looks great, food is spectacular and service was sensational! Coincidentally we were lucky to have same waiter year ago as a last night. Left was very kind to us and his service was outstanding in both cases.
After having very good time last year my friend and I, we ask Left to make a picture with us. He kindly agreed.
So after recognizing him tonight I couldn’t hold back, so I mentioned the fact we already met and I presented the picture from that day. 😀 He immediately remembered us 😃 We didn’t hesitate and had to capture this moment again!!!
Left really made our night unforgettable again and I hope we’ll have more chances to come back for more memories like this. 🙏
Thank you","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNd8r46ixHQKMHdkvaEfagU1S8RoFgigHGEFP3b&fid=0x0:0x914dae93368664f4"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Ellen Shi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKOAMbx6gFFkXfXX1M1IsnQtaa9zAErN_pvBjN5pKz7C9O5Nw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everything about my experience was excellent, from the delicious food to the outstanding service! I can confidently say this is the best pizza I've ever had. I’m already looking forward to returning to try other dishes from the menu!😊","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDM7X1P9NyS0Gf2ga-g0Aq-sqTbQxuLQ1q97cc&fid=0x0:0x914dae93368664f4"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Mohammadreza Behnejad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbfFjgusvHBDGevsLnSFlRH6CqkrxaSYgN1dtBgif3eqTdhnw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious dishes and staff are nice and professional
Great atmosphere and well designed inside
Traditional napoleon pizza are great specially comes with fresh mozzarella
Dough is fluffy and mouth watering

Pizza was a little over cooked and dough was burned

There are a couple of parking spots available and plenty of street parking

Highly recommend to do advance booking. Wait time over the weekend could be an hour easily","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNC7I4Czp97ghD76EJMNa45c5n0cB4Rpsjd-YA&fid=0x0:0x914dae93368664f4"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Shawn Johnson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqLU-WOCdxBtbaD48HbqFqhf-gwdu5I-zJsKM-w1J0K1gsKg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food here was unbelievable! The aged prosciutto was to die for & the focaccia was crispy on the outside, but pillowy on the inside. The pizza was also excellent! Although the dough was a bit soft in the middle, the flavour made up for it. If it wasn’t for our server who took over 15 minutes to even greet us & was generally slow with service, I’d give this place 5 stars. Definitely add it to your “must try” list.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGV2m3LmvzeJxcP3UgDg70aEa8Nwio_cA9w3yx&fid=0x0:0x914dae93368664f4"],"When":"2024-12-2"}]

[{"Name":"Ping D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-_KBk5-yIGzGmKAkX1L-6QPRrz_RZKkgRnIY4il5exhoL_sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"There was only one staff in the early morning but he was extremely efficient. The cranberry turkey sandwich was surprisingly delicious. Cream inside pistachio bun was on the sweeter side but would be a good choice as dessert. Wish price can be lower, so that I can come back regularly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNxEsqgdYQlHDlZlCYuy0cl7Drwho52YwlHjKCh&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Danilo Teodoro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_rV4_xok36vIezJ6uAhpzSfyECA8ogmjA4ehyXVTr4dBqIAFv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time I tried their bun with pistachio and the turkey bagel, and they were good! The cappuccino was good as well. I tried the Turkish coffee just because it's been years since the last one, and it was very strong, as usual. I'm glad I knew how this type of coffee is made and didn't stir the liquid.
The toilets needed some love..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHVVDDLtjxI1rM7Dy_3mg1tubzrGtmjT7wNGaz&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-6-11"},{"Name":"Alecia Hack","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0y1s7Bm_wrj5Zk4QFomT2h-qOh3c4CJw37lBhykQlV1HXtuw4ww=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve come here a couple of times and I’m completely obsessed with this place! I had the pistachio coffee bun and a salted caramel latte last time I was in, and while I wasn’t expecting the size, it was such an incredible treat. Cant wait to go back soon, thanks for a great experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyHEfOUN4bSSLdn0q7eE6t88Gu1R7qdGPR22CG&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Mavis Gevido","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVC-AP02ZE-ah41YCH68XbacnGEFbWfIc3R3T9FQiOBp_VcLYiP_A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great selection of coffee buns and the ones we tried were all so good! Relaxing atmosphere, good space. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUNszxgua9dx1DrmJ42Rm939D2PVomTSIp69Fc&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Ray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGVd5s-06Fr3JDo-bYWWNiziS7uiGN7g2hEorOk1Vp-qtDK_-cTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love the concept of their buns. They have a lot of different flavors, and I tried the pistachio one. The bun is better than what I expected-- I expected a flavorless, chewy/tough bun but it had a great fried flavor and chew to it, made indulgent by the toppings of cream and pistachios.
I also had a toasted salmon lox bagel which had a generous amount of cream cheese, I loved every bit of it.
Very friendly and welcoming service!
It was quite busy.
I would definitely come back if I were in the area 😆","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMEcOHD1pKqbcUepyj1ihb-fvVuAsZ3n-9iqr_&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"Zaayer Nasib","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkh0fpj6mvCROx8j1Ux0TdNtszR1GgFfGTRvlt6JMDCheOJwvK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ratings Scale 0 - 10
Variety: 8
Service or Product: 8
Customer Service: 8
Environment: 8
Cleaning: 8
Washroom: 7
Cost: 7

Tried a few of the buns, all of which were served fresh and hot! The ice cream bun was a delightful experience of warm bun and cold ice cream, but you have to be a little quick otherwise it starts melting really fast. The drinks were equally yummy. I had the hot chocolate which was perfect!
They have plenty of tables which was pretty good since there were quite a few people. There's only paid parking nearby though which was the only negative I see.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0IOQFvGUF-_OZnnytcmsz4gQreANuw04M0Tk6&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2021-5-16"},{"Name":"La Mc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3bmuxSiXCjm1iot5JpVUU_Lxxw4iPTmDpAUVL9Q9e-760ag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute place with fresh buns!

Very bright location with a few tables outside.

Need to come back and try other flavours!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQryY1DW2BwXBGxMAb_y7tat0BDpJD4G0vlOCs&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"Rochelle Barrett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfUfMrQqNwSQLSz_oSIsTrz93OXwAr4KrdgHWS4xUKxTxBh4cgIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first visit, despite living at the opposite end of the block!

I was there just after open and it was very quiet. I was able to stare at the menu without pressure, which I appreciated.

I got their Spanish latte. I'm not sure I have ever loved a coffee more. It was so dark and rich coffee flavours. I considered proposing to the barista, it was that good.

I hear their Turkey sandwich on cranberry sourdough, absolutely drool worthy!!! Creamy, savoury and sweet, perfect balance and the sour of the sourdough came through just enough.

Lastly, I had the gluten ginger cookie they out sourced from Wendell's. I did not love it. It was grainy but not their fault and I really appreciate they bring in options for multiple dietary requirements.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvTAeW_Ad9YU9AOS6XyvZZ8C-blZKGBy516Jo6&fid=0x0:0xda419efba462c144"],"When":"2021-6-13"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ruth Ruiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTnu7xFYlP7rD5mwZkeARHhfeUaoC3PNXoHdON7a1-uORvpN9C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this coffee shop! I come here very often to buy coffee or dessert with my baby and even though I know it's not a Mexican coffee shop, it reminds me a lot of my city, since there are many coffee shops of this style and when I lived at home (Mexico) I always used to go to coffee shops. The girls have always treated me very well and the atmosphere is pleasant.

The only bad thing I find is that sometimes the heating inside the café is too hot. I travel in the stroller with my baby, very bundled up because it is cold outside and that heat shock is not very good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPo8pP5cas-3RLhGVySsEy3VRc01x1oZXFCyuuu&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Anna Romaniuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUr2AFtzmK4eynrxAD-4PxdacLbRpvj3wICA9-bMinTX39gnZ09Ag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kaffi Espresso Bar is a delightful spot for coffee lovers. Their flat white with oat milk is smooth and perfectly balanced, a must-try for those who enjoy a creamy, non-dairy option. The macaroons are light and delicious, offering a sweet treat to pair with your coffee. If you're in the mood for dessert, the Pavlova is exceptional—crispy on the outside, soft and airy inside, with fresh toppings that elevate the experience. It is a cozy and charming place to unwind with great flavors! ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMpYWnT378aHyXniTDPHBRbUMIQ1bsocPrG8TnJ&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Stumbled upon Kaffi during a walk in the area, and ordered a decaf latte. The latte was nothing special, but was good! I liked the coffee flavour and mild sweetness it had. Service was alright! There were 2 staff working and the one taking my order seemed newer. They had to confirm with the other barista which drinks could be made decaf, and what non-dairy milk options they had. Unfortunately, after the fact, I noticed that on my receipt, they charged $0.75 for my oat milk substitution (their drink menu board lists non-dairy as an additional $0.50).

On a Sunday morning, it was quite a popular place with groups sitting in to chat as well as customers taking out. They also have a selection of baked goods at their front case, including some nice looking croissants.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8YYm3abZx1S-ePK76QQqcNpY2l-G_LVUg67Tx&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"jasmimaria R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4pJsI6zmjzg6T7Vv1nULcTI0hckuLuMTShtjT6u4cC-gzFPL6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Kaffi Espresso Bar offers a decent coffee experience with generally good service. However, the staff could be a bit friendlier to enhance the overall atmosphere. The espresso was delicious, perfectly brewed to bring out rich flavors. Unfortunately, the danish didn't quite live up to its appearance, as it was overbaked. Despite these small drawbacks, it's still a solid spot for a quality espresso.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwwA6O2uQcW6N72-BQDguSoLTJNsHUWJ0otUKO&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice little café with a cozy atmosphere. We ordered a latte and an Americano. Both were decent — nothing extraordinary, but enjoyable enough. The service was friendly, and the place was clean.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgOhDNVbIXowAFL-2vv3wvZY87Bg4LO5cdvImv&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Karla Vazquez Peniche","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDz1KwihcBNerOeAGgbA_zV52UY14XSBM9ioRoz9zK0FXfnKW8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kaffi Cafe is hands down my favorite spot. Their pastries and treats are always fresh, delicious, and perfectly baked. The staff are friendly, welcoming, and make you feel right at home. It's my go-to spot for a cozy atmosphere and a tasty treat. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUGCkbaOTjJ7BqCvlziDZkHVQkgMslwHg_BA9E&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-10-3"},{"Name":"Ana De Pinho Gast","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW56TF2vLF5XxLTSdTNkl6pqTWOu6vdMDM2MLXOpO50vFcc7x3-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kaffi espresso bar in Port Moody is definitely a hidden gem in the area. From friendly and skilled staff, to delicious pastries and personally my favorite coffee in the area. I have worked in Port Moody for almost a year now and stop by Kaffi at least twice a week and I can definitely say they service and quality of their items is always consistent and outstanding in my opinion. I will continue to frequent this establishment. Keep up the amazing work ladies! 🌸","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9Hdx7PvcBtMF0xrkwsS0l3wsz3S-27qOjX46Q&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Marcus L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZLCsGchamGOA-Wtg05cndL2yjt6EBGtYR9Y9cWGpcdNb3N09u=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently visited Kaffi and unfortunately, the experience didn’t meet my expectations. The service was disappointing; there was a mix-up with our order that wasn’t properly addressed, and the staff seemed indifferent, placing our food on the table without any interaction. The food quality was underwhelming—the mocha lacked the rich chocolate and espresso flavor I anticipated, and the latte was weak, missing the robust coffee taste one would expect. Overall, the visit was not as enjoyable as I had hoped, and improvements in both service and beverage quality are necessary.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1xPAvd9_22vrU4mRfRgtuKPvrDnpes9hXFJ8&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-8-10"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"K S H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUpfuZFJ8RwqNTmsEi_Ve_L99RruCBycZdik5Nf-7YZZhK-hRF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very elegant atmosphere and good quality fresh Asian dishes. Great seafood selection. Wholesome fish maw and corn soup. Loved their Vegetables \u0026 Shrimp dish and their Shrimp fried rice. Tea was also great. Staff were welcoming and friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5YuW39f9IY9fXyxfLF9aCAqXBhQc6gtDSMiAl\u0026fid=0x0:0x57f84f13a54db1e1"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This portion of the restaurant is open even when the dim sum portion is not. Prices are a bit higher than other Chinese restaurants. Lots of dish options however, including some dim sum. I really enjoyed the Yang chow fried rice as it has a lot of flavour and a good amount of shrimp. The place was also very accommodating for a wheelchair user and moved chairs and tables out of the way so that we can enter the restaurant properly and that the wheelchair wasn’t blocking anyone or the walkway. You will be charged for the flimsy takeout containers. Lots of parking spaces as this restaurant is located within Coquitlam Centre near the Atmopshere entrance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGDGeESXdIC8kIRfbPTVQiM6UFIZ1Tj_PGh_Qf\u0026fid=0x0:0x57f84f13a54db1e1"],"When":"2024-5-16"},{"Name":"Marnie Eudela-Umlas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXg_gVRD_Hd9V3XIUh6_P71KHCryea9xsHYGqrZHTuXW_jdxEU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We love Neptune restaurants and it was our first time here coz our friend recommended it. They serve dimsum for dinner which made me happy. Love all their foor and service was great. We will surely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO69uQnnjMIHicGkQzOmWibLCkVNcmjDHACqWHD\u0026fid=0x0:0x57f84f13a54db1e1"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Wendy T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLriWRd1X47lp1mjG8HN5wrIo_gOHccXRo_VUWS1JqXDDT6WyXc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is a great example of a restaurant you should definitely avoid. The waitress promoted the green veggie dish to us which turned out actually not fresh and way too spicy which she never mentioned to us. Then, the manager, an elder lady with short hair firmly refused to exchange with any other dish or refund. She said what she can only do is to take the veggie dish back to the kitchen get rinsed and stir fry it again for us.  This is just ridiculous. Basically it looks like whether you like it or not, you must accept what they serve to you here.  Moreover, we didn’t realize this dish is actually overpriced until we saw the bill. It’s 28.88 which the waitress never mentioned about when she promoted it earlier.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5hLoB7SzUCrVAvhhoMSJ7ZGaLFdkXLBJu15K2\u0026fid=0x0:0x57f84f13a54db1e1"],"When":"2024-5-20"},{"Name":"Kenny Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPZZirBvo0A4h9mBsQTblhWpjRI5s3b9jzZsDmMvuAnSg24xg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The 4 of us just wanted a simple but tasty meal for dinner. The food here did not disappoint. The total cost came to $130 including tax but before tip. There was enough food to take home for a second meal! The only thing I didn't like was the table was near the door - it was a cold evening so every time the door opened we got a really cold blast.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIk7nTUQQbmi2rl43RxT4jZyedTUWdQjUIUtF3\u0026fid=0x0:0x57f84f13a54db1e1"],"When":"2023-3-16"},{"Name":"Shy Allen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKpeG4IGumZdK0VO6Hs49O4o6xEQczbmaoYf41bx6FVUJ-1OQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If I could give zero stars I would. The absolute worst experience I have ever had in dinning in my whole life or I have ever heard of just happened at this restaurant. My family and friends have supported this restaurant since they opened. Today we went and had a dish that tasted so awful we sent it back Immediately and were told we still had to pay for it because it’s our fault we didn’t like it…..then the manger had to argue with the “boss” and sent the male “boss” out to Yell at us two women in the restaurant which was the most disgusting and disrespectful experience ever. He even said well if you don’t pay for it I have too and not doing that……. Definitely the worst customer service I’ve ever seen or heard of. Unfortunately the food is not good anymore and the service 1000% worse. We have gone to other Asian restaurants for over 20 years and they would never treat anyone this way. We have always been treated like family in other establishments. A huge mistake ever supporting this restaurant with ownership or “bosses” like that. Save yourself money and the disrespect and go elsewhere.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lily Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDGk1BBw-1vgJ9ulxVR0Qxl5Y2TOzVCkO980S0Usi15HFveto=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had lunch with friends total 3 people, ordered combo A and shrimp dim sum and eggplant dim sum, everything was good but not a big fan of chow mei with chicken because noodle was dry and did not have much flavour. title: Rosa's Cucina Italiana
address: 2331 Clarke St, Port Moody, BC V3H 1Y9
descriptions: Neighbourhood eatery for old-school Italian specialties, from baked pasta to grilled steak.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Viona Halim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5PMLEtvgkAwv2IjmL8XXm0-Ly_XpBo5Kd0Hv2pxoQ26_Hfy4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We visited this place around  3 weeks ago on our date night and we truly enjoyed it! It's quaint, small, cozy, and has that old Italian taverna charm.

Like I mentioned, the place is small so either arrive as soon as they're open or be prepared to wait in line especially if you come with a group of 4+. Highly recommended is their meatballs appetizers. They're HUGE and generous with the sauce! Good to feed 4 and I definitely suggest you use the bread to soak up all those sauce goodness. Their pasta also comes in generous portion, so you can always have enough leftover for tomorrow's lunch ;)

If you've been to Italy and you know how restaurants there usually have really good house wine on the cheap, this place also carries their house wine as well, though not as cheap as what you'd find in Italy. Therefore, might as well just get a whole bottle of wine. They'll put the stopper on and pack it up for you if you can't finish it there. We got the Ruffino and it went down pretty darn smooth. Yes, you'll pay 2-3X the price than getting it from the liquor store, but that's to be expected and it certainly makes the dining experience that much better :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTX-8-_2WPxc_BLoBwmJgk2XvXbyDPcF3vl-Kt&fid=0x0:0x893efbff8ce7540c"],"When":"2021-10-31"},{"Name":"Clara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJWIwshLULE3B_RdNi9aKWLWw8jS-s52J_rdUUXlZsGL8nMFDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Solid home-style Italian food. They do have some fancy specials as well, but the reason I go back is for that comfy, homey feel overall. The portions are huge. The service is great in terms of friendliness, but can be a bit slow due to limited staffing. It's a tight space, so be prepared for a bit of squish and volume, particularly if there are kids there at the time. It's great for families, but I'd be a bit wary of the atmosphere for a romantic date if you're not into noisy environments.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZGXQwQEK-z7e-HyEXZ2u9WP_5G6MTPBU_08sZ&fid=0x0:0x893efbff8ce7540c"],"When":"2018-12-29"},{"Name":"Sarah Grace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0P_FT3n0HZdmLMDEJ6UcRFNPyHbE7QJ8GW3gOL-SGGTFh-sFdQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is unbelievable! The food is homemade deliciousness from a true Italian Chef! The plates are huge! One plate is enough for two people. The atmosphere and interior is so cozy. A real italian family run gem! Everything is unbelievable and made perfect. “ Nonna’s Kitchen”","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHRjYxBPeZ7y_zoDYaRq8qPyGihEQzrlIx-RL0&fid=0x0:0x893efbff8ce7540c"],"When":"2021-3-3"},{"Name":"Chanelle D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCEGtGi_rnAXcez2UGfi8tPvkrtnC3uoCyaDz_NpX-tJAfWp2A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of the few restaurant gems in Port Moody. Very generous servings and really delicious food. My friend ordered ribs and it was Fred Flinstone sized. The canelloni I ordered was awesome, very tasty and rich. They offered us dessert (cheesecake) and a couple of glasses of wine on the house because my friend is a regular.. very gracious of them. The owners are excellent hosts and they talk to each table. It is family oriented. No wonder it is very busy. The restaurant is quaint and intimate and I don’t think it seats more than 50 people so you should try to get in before 5pm if you want to be seated for dinner time.

The restaurant is located in the old part of Port Moody and unfortunately, parking can be challenging but it depends on what time of day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHUsTaq2iyQa9oC8oSjsLr1FF6hSaqDIvE2aTI&fid=0x0:0x893efbff8ce7540c"],"When":"2018-5-27"},{"Name":"A Miraji","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKbtSn1-d3iEkTDQas0xH_xCGg1PKv8z1hKaZIhPkrsgM_kICp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best Italian restaurant in the Port Moody. A family running place with original recipes and homemade taste. If you love Italian food this is the place you should go. The wait time is a little bit too long but it worth the quality you get. The place is cozy and warm, feels like home and the staff/owners are very kind and respectful. Totally recommend this awesome place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMN4c9aVu7Uw2Y9QFY9iDs92o8YsCdg42dRsurr&fid=0x0:0x893efbff8ce7540c"],"When":"2018-9-16"},{"Name":"Thomas Tricarico","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKhws5bVYDwmrI4nzI8NtjFY5tCFNmhM_PZ57tj9M9bdO7Dag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Well...with all the hype about Rosa's we were very disappointed. Besides their No Reservations policy and having to wait 3hrs for seating..the service and meal was quite disappointing. Maybe it was just a bad kitchen nite...or the fact that they're closing down at the end of the month...but the venture just confirmed that I/we will never, ever wait for 3 or 2 or even less hrs for a table....no matter what the Restaurant hype is. We never had waited so long anytime, anywhere in all our dinning in all our travels here and abroad...and this restaurant certainly did Not live up to the wait. A wasted time. Plus the hostess 'list' her pad of paper with people's names on it...so after 3 hrs wait...she said "whoever is next come in". What an operation. Anyway, we grabbed a table and the hostess was friendly enough took our order for wine. We ordered a bottle of Italian/Sicilian Rose which was pretty good...since they ran out of the house red by the carafe (tho I saw another table served it).. We then shared their version of Caprese salad...with tons of onions on it...something we've never seen before.. with small pieces of mozzarella .. Looked like dressed up left overs.. and then our pasta entres. My wife's   Fetucinni Alfredo wasn't too bad..decent flavor and consistency and pasta cooked correctly. My spaghetti Riviera with Rose sause was a little thin in consistency and mediocre in flavour. The portions were generous but service was poor. The host/waitress never once stopped by to ask how things were.... A real disappointment. With all the hype and previous good reviews makes me wonder about others expectations or Italian food...but we figured we'd give Rosa's a shot before they close and retire. Maybe it's time ..
Cest la vie.
.
The last picture after the wine...is what a real Caprese looks like...(from another local restaurant)..imo..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfeuN0_-nvPJWK2rFH_VMmA5ti-CxJr3Q7Gl_H&fid=0x0:0x893efbff8ce7540c"],"When":"2022-8-21"},{"Name":"Kitty xoxo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQTO26917aKF_IYJ4SHsFaKj5YjGWMm61uhVtKUcV1UwU16aTd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I would give it 5 stars on my behalf but my fiance is Italian and hes the cook in the house so what he says is true, he felt it was pretty basic pasta and I had the meatballs (2 is good for one person) they had less juice and s lot of tomato sauce so it makes you pretty thirsty, though we enjoyed our meals, but i agree with that person who said Large portions doesn't mean better quality, and waiting outside makes a person confused if they're going in next or not, we waited just to see few people go in but it was sunny and it was ok for us.
Expect to wait 30+ minutes, the server is a nice lady. Also the wines are basic too but if you're very hungry for large portions, this is a great place to try.
ALSO they bring you free bread & butter and the appetizer looks like an entree so if you're not that hungry, don't order it lol (see salad) but it was yummy!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4fHeIrDh_Lo7LyQu7z3B0Vt0BZXxUc35mPAUR&fid=0x0:0x893efbff8ce7540c"],"When":"2019-7-11"},{"Name":"Lauren Bunsko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKfFvVK9KFivahwhI8uc_iCHDPEZbDpiOMUZJbvb6sOTcs_vg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very sad this Port Moody staple is closing. A quaint family run business with huge portions and lovely staff. Rosa’s you will be missed!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7Q30xpIl66E9idHDBNa60pF5f3uDhJn5wEyOd&fid=0x0:0x893efbff8ce7540c"],"When":"2022-8-27"}]

[{"Name":"Kimiya Namdar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ5NoUG9m0kwHJtkvaDA-UHALghW-sRI1Mo4nWzPLFWn5wQUVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"For our anniversary, we decided to stay local and chose Cactus Club, and it didn’t disappoint. We arrived 15 minutes early but were seated promptly. Moe, our host, was attentive and made sure we were well taken care of. We both ordered the steak, which was delicious and came in generous portions. When it came time to settle the bill, we were pleasantly surprised to find that our dessert was on the house—a thoughtful gesture for our special occasion. It’s the little touches like these that make all the difference.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlxtSajFGYkpR7ks7zBaxq3E_Rq1AoW205uJz3&fid=0x0:0x29de451081a450a0"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"jackie spears","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQSpIRsoeLZKzPhRjMQrTuHhWXI2eeJUv_G6fSe8jGwzpSrvc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Wish I could give no stars,but had to put something unfortunately.
So loud couldn't hear anything from my coworkers to the server. Food was cold and tasteless (had the chicken strips and truffle fries) fries weren't even seasoned and I paid extra $$$ for the upgrade only to have tasteless fries and cold chicken strips! Will not ever be returning to this location.
Also to add the Bellini I had was definitely definitely not worth the price I paid for either and had like no alcohol in it! Another major let down which is another staple CC is known for!
Have had mediocre service from this location before and now after this last service will definitely not be returning! For the $50 I paid for just myself it 100% was not at all worth the price. My co workers complained about the lack of attentiveness and poor food quality as well and said they won't be returning either. Usually cactus club is an A++ but they absolutely more than missed the mark on this night. So no thanks, I'll go to a much more reputable place that knows how to make properly cooked chicken and well seasoned truffle fries not just tossed under the heat lamp for a few seconds not even room temp fries 🍟
#nothankyou 😞","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTChYQLzDD-_sWCeaozWjveRAUsUuT4CBWbN2j&fid=0x0:0x29de451081a450a0"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Date night with my husband. The standout chef makes this branch exceptional. I highly recommend dining here. We ordered the spicy chicken bites, chicken karaage, and beef teriyaki, and each dish was fantastic. Just a heads-up: if you visit late, sushi might not be available as they switch to a late-night menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN49Ks3ddRv49CewTMfgD6DHa7mpOe76H01K6c&fid=0x0:0xa101649f28705"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"Nelson Mah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMvSq7-l8Kje4bUGcJFo_gjx31JEZujbDf7RAmASmnqxtIa8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came on a Saturday with my cousins. Very much enjoyed. Great location by Coquitlam centre.

Awesome roll was actually awesome. Glad we tried it. Mango roll is also a favorite. Sometimes the computer i-pad system to order food needs to be charged and thus have to order by server sometimes. Can be confusing for new customers. Maybe charge all the iPad's at night to help improve efficiency.

Was great experience. Server was kind to refill hot water and tea regularly. I recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMF9N9bDYccydaW7nM5ZX_3HWUgfoXb19TgbmXV&fid=0x0:0xa101649f28705"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"argh c","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2c34N4-KZC9sfBqKbqJSYJcFxkP3ce_vYTvsj7Y6T7ga6urdW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very crowded on a Sunday evening, fortunately we had a reservation. That said, we were competing with a bustling take out business in addition to the other patrons in the restaurant for kitchen time.  It took quite a while to get our order taken and although food started to arrive almost immediately we started to wonder if some things had missed being recorded (they hadn’t, it was just a long time start to finish). Noteworthy is that hot food arrived first, strangely the salad was delivered last.  Timing issues aside, the quality of food was very good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPR71aAmtNVdYdVWNqI5KToT7ZnsFk1gt_-3Pm_&fid=0x0:0xa101649f28705"],"When":"2023-7-8"},{"Name":"rob donnelly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWbVA4p6yG-H9CQp-_Eh3D0lvIffky01DTDsh0aIk6h_fTFkc3t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Long time Sushi Town customer, it’s always been very good, no complaints. However on this visit, all the portions are noticeably smaller. Awesome Roll definitely not awesome this visit. Definitely less fish on top, and at $14.95 we feel ripped off. Salmon nigiri, noticeably less salmon, and some of the rice not cooked properly. After many years and dollars spent in this restaurant, we won’t be coming back. Very disappointed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emmanuel Carino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJ9g6OsewbE5PvEJQG0W2MrejjY87xqZcS0O_-lbnLLATuQeGq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sushi Town in Coquitlam is a fantastic spot for delicious Japanese food at great prices. The menu has a wide selection of sushi, sashimi, and creative rolls, all served in generous portions. The quality of the food is excellent, with fresh ingredients and beautifully presented dishes that make each visit a treat. The atmosphere is casual and welcoming, perfect for both small gatherings and family meals. The staff is friendly and attentive, ensuring you have a pleasant dining experience. Whether you're a sushi lover or just looking to try something new, Sushi Town is a must-visit for a satisfying meal!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex Aanei","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5r3ZjSCmXMog20pYsE9fANH214snHKhL7fPna0KCOa7Y9FQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been going to sushi town for years and love it! Food comes out super quick and is yummy, and the service is great.
Highly recommend this place and they have the best potato croquette!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Leslie Fusco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVy-3kobnwSD_xhSlW0mhuDwnDu4W0x4cKEqPED13yiIvOHsjspVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing service from our server, Yoon!! Wheelchair accessible washroom and parking.  Plenty of parking available.  Prices are reasonable.  They are a must check out place!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOopCAGmjqnOdOpyxFpVeAkYLMHD2EV5q8vmwEX&fid=0x0:0xa101649f28705"],"When":"2023-1-5"}]

[{"Name":"Martin Matahari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAn1gLSlBMeGXZBHUnKkSJRx9LUQmHP9VKEpiPVA6PU8EOwPbl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My experience with Mountain Meadows School in Port Moody has been nothing short of disappointing. From the very beginning, it was clear that this institution lacked the basic elements of effective education.

The staff's lack of communication and disorganization was frustrating. It often felt like they were just going through the motions, with no genuine interest in the students' well-being or progress. Despite being entrusted with the education of my five sons, the teachers seemed indifferent and unengaged.

The curriculum appeared outdated and uninspiring, failing to capture the attention of my children. It felt like a struggle to get them excited about learning, as the school failed to offer any innovative or engaging teaching methods.

Furthermore, the facilities were lackluster at best. Cramped classrooms, outdated technology, and a general lack of upkeep were glaring issues. It's disheartening to see my sons' potential stifled by an environment that lacks the resources needed to foster growth and development.

In summary, Mountain Meadows School has been a regrettable choice for my children's education. The lack of enthusiasm, outdated curriculum, and subpar facilities make it clear that this institution falls far short of providing the quality education my sons deserve.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dorothy Beavington","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjGJNfeB4zyLfdD4oe6w4aYNsryj4X223WZWUodYsHP2ry1w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am the grandmother of Annika and Lukas Vine (Coxe) and have attended every Christmas concert.to see my beloved grandchildren perform.  I have been very impressed with the spirit in the school and how the concerts were handled.  My grandchildren have nothing but good to say about their teachers and the staff.  I am happy to know they are in a school that has the highest standards and also knows how to make education fun and lively. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really nice aesthetic at this coffee shop, which is situated alongside a presentation centre and also features a small pop-up shop from Fable (housewares). The layout is very open but still features a good amount of comfortable seating including seating for large groups, and a beautiful patio out back. The service was friendly.
I had a blackberry & brie grilled cheese, a vegan rye cookie, and a tropical espresso spritz (seasonal drink, like an espresso tonic with coconut and pineapple flavours). Everything was really good! I love fruit with brie cheese so the grilled cheese was an easy winner for me. The blackberry spread was tart and jammy which balanced out the rich brie cheese. I loved the funky flavour of rye in the cookie and the chewiness. The espresso spritz was very refreshing in this hot weather! It had deflated a little by the time I took the picture, but it had an impressively foamy crema layer. Even though nothing was really fancy or experimental, all the food/drink items I tried had something to make them a little unique.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCEBQuCDIsCUWtrbHKFNiwZ3ZKq7ylWlDlHn48&fid=0x0:0x775eee3d482be6bc"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Vicente Barreiros","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWXXjeDynmf81Pwbj0gtZnbrkTAQXze5uhpr2fBUeDvR8QxnMvZfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely fantastic experience at The Outpost Café in Coquitlam! From the moment we walked in, we were greeted with friendly smiles and a warm atmosphere. The coffee was exceptional, rich and flavorful, and the pastries were fresh and delicious. The menu offers a great variety, with something for everyone, including vegan options. The service was prompt and attentive, making us feel right at home. The cozy decor and comfortable seating made it the perfect spot to relax, play some cards, and enjoy our meal. Highly recommend The Outpost Café for anyone looking for a top-notch café experience. Five stars all the way!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4wvHezthRzyRsko09vUr_HYZOtSR2BH7Mwg61&fid=0x0:0x775eee3d482be6bc"],"When":"2024-7-5"},{"Name":"Penny Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCDgTL2OCcG7L7sb4kqDmHWrJHfxt_0ygdBvV9n-aV-_JDvgc9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place to have a cute cafe moment.
The coffee was great, the breakfast was good.
Great seating area, friendly staff and everything fits a relaxing work from cafe vibe.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcO0eFIZ_w7h0KLt86R7SxjHYM-KQnPOHfMhxM&fid=0x0:0x775eee3d482be6bc"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"First time here. We both found the espresso acidic, and my latte was watery, so not an enjoyable combination. $15 avocado toast got us a cold hard boiled egg on a slice of bread. Bizarrely there was dill in it which wasn’t nice. It was as if AI was asked to create a recipe for avocado toast and this was the result. Service was basic and gets three stars. Atmosphere was the best part and gets five stars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwTG5Fyw5A_PZTIuU9hJ9zw5QI8f6DPjm6FLG5&fid=0x0:0x775eee3d482be6bc"],"When":"2024-6-2"},{"Name":"Mahsa Haghjoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRSnT0Wip7Pbg6Z8m0cglGHkWd61YfkTkUIlG6b0IkPWIUcJi2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such a lovely clean place with indoor and outdoor sitting area. Absolutely delicious matcha tea latte and almond croissant ( super crisp and not too sweet).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3AZ75H1zqQhXLwfTg9Rv_YKW4qW3nOf8lfejs&fid=0x0:0x775eee3d482be6bc"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"candy L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgq2OgnXFRsC1icGye-CTgUf_6kEV0cPoOgzI7ANMes5eDT-Xz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Today I  visited this coffee shop that was recommended by a friend, and I was impressed by the uniqueness of both the interior and exterior design. The outdoor seating area was adorned with lights and some seats even had heaters above them. The indoor area also had a distinct and interesting design.
I ordered a mocha and a Cosmic Candy espresso, and only saw two types of pastries  available at the counter, so I chose  chocolate cookies. As we had our dog with us, we decided to sit outside. The mocha had a great taste, but the espresso wasn’t  my preferred flavor .. The chocolate cookie had a soft texture and a slightly salty taste, which I really enjoyed. I was glad I bought two pieces of it.

Overall, the experience was good, although the staff wasn't particularly friendly. I'm interested in trying their Creamy Artichoke sandwich next time I visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9A_Cv05HzQq_5O4EKmblsVBpUzkioEsGnz9YF&fid=0x0:0x775eee3d482be6bc"],"When":"2023-4-9"},{"Name":"Corey Zinger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV82isKGUntRlZNnI9zQqSVHTPsmJ3vp2B6JTmGSqHV-uQo84g1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"4.5 stars - Just a stones throw away from Moody Centre Park and Ride this place great for studying or meeting up with a close friend. I got the a sausage roll and some great pour over coffee by Timbertrain while I worked on some homework.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5BE_p-2WHy5hvqzkodL_GcUWiQtaIcTpgL95a&fid=0x0:0x775eee3d482be6bc"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Mika K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGiz4azZW5wkWaIdFsmuEWpFVVqFlnlD2Y0OOU7L-FnirjYrpaqA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really nice spot, big and bright. Modern feel and lofty vibe. Lots of places to work and many plugs. Cool spot. The coffee is great and the baristas are very good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMFoZ9ljuSfOP2ZFFImQWY6rqFwDoukSmBtJm5&fid=0x0:0x775eee3d482be6bc"],"When":"2024-6-23"}]

[{"Name":"Brittany","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHTcuSM-4ly1uIP3q2-jgQ_2Vqi7GhBmGO9JykCcOlnN1NYOmqYg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Came after sampling the Lavender Sour at Chickpea and being absolutely drawn in.

The experience as a whole was disappointing at the taproom: It might have been an off evening due to Halloween festivities/weather, but upon arriving, a few of the tap handles were sold out - Taps that would have made Moody Ales stand out amongst the others that do the usual IPAs and pales. Compared to the other taprooms themselves, Moody felt tight. Closely packed in families with little space or cohesion in the room.

I’d love to update my review when I come back to the row and try more beers/when it might be less crazy. There’s truly nothing like their Lavender Sour out there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJCYqqFkCQuwTHjZHQs2-VRILDRxidYTivcAxN&fid=0x0:0x2ab68beb4fa0d9d6"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Kayla Bell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPYYItX53_JFRw1bvGvWQbBS_a-Al_HMey-fawhYa_cPyuUqUv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visit this brewery regularly, and it’s been even better since the new leadership team has come in. The new food menu is fantastic, and their seasonal beer variety is always a winner along Brewery Row.

Most recently, we attended Taylor Swift trivia, and it was so well run. It was the first time I’ve attended one of their trivia nights, and it definitely won’t be the last.

The host was fantastic, even while having to deal with a table of self proclaimed SFU professors that weren’t there for trivia, but made sure to state their claim on a reserved table and be obnoxious and rude to the host and other guests. I digress.

Other than the blatant misogyny of the one man in the SFU group, the experience was amazing. Great beer, great staff, great atmosphere, great event. Can’t wait to visit again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwBfwAoIcn840TD4azZYI3oMf2OiWRXCxXf4fi&fid=0x0:0x2ab68beb4fa0d9d6"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"Tony Sebastian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiWqdXCEwpIVB9StmiemuyGnyCJmr0IdMdtYRQU_cWFPEJXoA8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Moody Ales is and can be the only start to port moody beer crawl. Fantastic brewery!
Can’t say how much I love this place and the people!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9INWLwOIOj7qoDEEgRRPDIyHbZve3o9eGrWbb&fid=0x0:0x2ab68beb4fa0d9d6"],"When":"2024-12-11"},{"Name":"Adrienne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvS1YiBi1kAYmplCTkzo9NqyjbLMViYayHxaEQA-dKyQUyyA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came here specifically for the lobster roll, and it did not disappoint! There were large chunks of lobster and the flavor was amazing. We enjoyed the patio and appreciated that they allow dogs. We also got the rib dinner, which was flavorful but we found the portion a bit small. Definitely coming back for the lobster rolls!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKMs6e5h77w4u1xXxlBZS3MsC1U8z0X1soWwD4&fid=0x0:0x2ab68beb4fa0d9d6"],"When":"2023-7-9"},{"Name":"L K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7gOAyi31eGNkFBxsrBMX35BqtBkhbQww42uWrb70nTnOgyUwd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent staff and beer selection to drink myself away as my kids do volleyball tryouts at harry Jerome sports centre near by. 🍺🍺🍺🤘","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOL_swPCE6GVMAcjhHyCITymYoTQCzu1oeRsfR7&fid=0x0:0x2ab68beb4fa0d9d6"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Christina Swanson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNWxyzlnDsWbzgDQ8_CWAvQAx_6I-ake3OPyqbMMREgPal9Ngk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My friends & I love coming to the trivia nights at Moody Ales! Serena is the best host & we always have a great time at these events. The food offered here is great too! Staff is friendly and welcoming. The beermosa with the strawberry kiwi beer is great!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Grant Truesdell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYnlna-_GRxIxqy6nGy2CX0YwzOYaR6NSIYfz0eWEQHv9tJ_uh=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Decent beer and staff. One of the staff members running a Taylor Swift trivia night was very rude to our table telling us multiple times to be quiet. I’m sorry, I didn’t realize we were drinking in a library.  She continued to banter with us to the point where we just left. Not sure if I’ll ever come back due to this interaction as the rest of the place wasn’t anything special to out weigh the rude staff.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjk0RWTEVeJgIqKKHovYpwJFKGyrzLouw5T0F1OmXxGyJKuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best brewery on the strip! The beer, the food and the fabulous staff! Thank you for having us, see you soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6yrxQl09W6POSjR1Orekq-60jKPsxgev5Cfvt&fid=0x0:0x2ab68beb4fa0d9d6"],"When":"2024-8-7"}]

I was there only for an hour before close to use the hot tub, sauna and steam room for medical reasons. First I think the centre could have a reduced fee for the use of the centre for one hour, but that is not the issue I had. The issues were related to the poor maintenance and supervision of that area. The hot tub had rust stains on the floor, then the sauna was closed and finally, the tile in the steam room had a bunch of cracks. I know this area is not heavily used as it is in other places because there is no pool, but we are still paying customers. For supervision the issue I had was that there was a guy there in his underwear (boxers but still!). It was very uncomfortable. How is this allowed? The young lady at the front desk was great, no issues there!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kevin Ao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkBvZ6ce_zHnWsLqA5ojfX0nMQ_CDE0WIX5k8yhZ46T8a1BLiA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I recently visited the Port Moody Recreation Complex and I was impressed with the variety of options available. There is a weight room, basketball court, and ice rink. The weight room was busy during the peak hours, so I had to wait for equipment. However, the staff was very friendly and helpful. The Complex is very clean and spacious. Best of all, parking is free! Overall, I had a great experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNj4Wi2VqMAxtMtVzGzfHNAG8iAWqITJ1Y-MHqL&fid=0x0:0x494c199cdd56d654"],"When":"2022-7-4"},{"Name":"Courtenay A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDjSuS-4nP18WlGHtsYD6AAMxP39BDv68Epp0TMQ0H4Nv1COG2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Huge parking lot which is busy a lot of times & if you haven’t been here before they have so many activities/sports/community services etc. going on it’s hard to know which doors to go into. On the other hand they have a support desk inside with very helpful people working there - who helped me locate where I was to go.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"rom g","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJoL35CYNNEemnRv8N-GjBP5IjLHDkshj-x2ca-XymH_qoAig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My Kids love it
plenty of activities and clases to take
Or just the framers markt every week
Skating and hocky
Parking can be a pain at times","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kiryl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0D0PIVxIL_Jl_E9EpJGpzBeo_flNCR9emhn5s61S_fNFCUBfE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Probably the best facility in Tri-Cities to maintain a healthy lifestyle at an affordable price. Well equipped gym, hot tub, sauna, tennis courts, always helpful and positive staff. Always very clean. There’s a nice cafe to sit inside and outside as well in the complex.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cristina Gutierrez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNlsAfN86nRSztKx392kgA6bbxVUjILDORH4PK0mz7Qd6Ga_CGOA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Perfect for momas to hang out, I love they just bought new toys and furniture for the jungle gym, the music class with Tracy is the best! And waves after class the best treat","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lisa Simmons","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLUCbM7Sv-M1pAApVUnGKleUtAL_QtjEhlmjRjJZl7LJUXJqg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What an awesome facility! Easily accessible.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqcyMIBKDqjKffGL3Vkm7DVvekhawRnTdIxs1n&fid=0x0:0x494c199cdd56d654"],"When":"2023-9-15"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Diane (Dineoutwithdee)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJfHVJSjIKAcPEXNIfUcWAtOeYHaXavqJYPtVJZ3lhCbCbpeo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a great place to get authentic Greek food at reasonable prices. Great value here and delicious food, too! The place is busy so best to come early to grab a seat. I recommend the lamb shoulder, calamari and the chicken & beef souvlaki!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP42asUKI5KLp9y9RM9Fit82mrJ9Qd6-ziYb3Sh&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Emily Lu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKEvwebxzOOvHfn2UnHwr4i_lsQ_4WBBcdmwEUmGOtZoyfwO9Mg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really good food and great flavour! The pita bread is probably the best in the lower mainland! The portion is also generous. We took the dinner home and that was a whole other meal in and out of itself.
The place is quite bit but it gets 80% full and becomes busy even at 4:30 pm! The space between tables is small so I had to move my chains/out of the way for people/waiters to pass through all the time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_rakdPK5k-z808EXZ_h6jLZlPrNWM6u9uhOQY&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"duane r neufeld","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhhlb1lcJQnDlyAPy1R2d_GOddZm-jMhyJJsiO9YhD02HRj38=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow these folks have it dialed in!!! Do not come here unless you have a LARGE appetite.  Monster serving size and you will love eating it all to the last morsel.  Every aspect of the food is perfect.  Come with your friend with a large appetite.  They will not be disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDW_s96eeWP-6cW7H05QxCPA7hObO2L0nmcgN1&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Bella Mills","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9Ii_MUe1yBHkf4i7hAtgKoYsTZWvSgOMwOkR9qA3QXh9dyYpPrg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We are here at 4:00 pm on Saturday and luck to have table without making reservation.
Food and service are great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyHTwJlp2n1QQowmTTyN0vMGdc4AOtJgiUnj4G&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good thing I made a reservation cuz wow it was so full on a weekday night. They try to squeeze as many tables in there and my seat bumps into the person behind me. Parking is limited to a few in front and a few on the sides.

We quickly got seated and ordered our meals. Everything was enormous. The mostly I've seen at any greek restaurant. Definitely worth the price.

Calamari was standard. I would have liked it with some seasoning.

The lamb chops were fantastic! I asked for medium rare and it was perfect and tender. There were 6 pieces!

The roast lamb was just ok. My husband likes the Stephos version better. It was a big chunk of meat though.

As with all greek restaurants, the carbs portion is way too much - rice, potato, and pita. The pita not soft unfortunately.

Definitely would come back for the lamb.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOATDXGeayXLsJ-091SfEA30U9Aiv4xc1ccZC0M&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Justine H (Sunny)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmvMXm-P_-zaDju2DtLb4mJNuo8OiXNtbw6zPhVOcICWtiAOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place! We ordered the calamari from their dinner menu and their souvlaki. Their calamari was very fresh and crunchy. Their meat was a little hard but you're able to request if you prefer it to be well done, medium rare, etc.

The restaurant is much cleaner than other Greek restaurants we have been to and their prices are standard so we probably keep coming back time to time. :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9BOPAe0Tu_IZ0MhDzHLYvccA1b9J6cef-PjwK&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"TK FIRE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMwgiWW4CWTw18dhib5ASUUbKOwvxPibgN0xFiOf9nH6Ji-EXH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a great place for Greek food! The atmosphere, and food portions are exactly what I thought of when trying this Greek restaurant and they did not disappoint me at all!

I would recommend this place
The chicken isn't dry it's nice and falvorful. The chicken Santorini is a hearty meal, the beef and chicken souvlaki are great and so is the calamari dinner!

All great foods in a great space! Parking is a bit tricky but there is usually spots available","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMtkT9fytHaneOUKAwGkMRNUwRJnYjKLZx-52V1&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"Suman Bhandari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLrnk9wt3gtXf77pcTHOn49F7Cf4BXrdzL7G_AYfSWCGcgKJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food portion is good, tastes good as well. Can be a bit crowded and loud and may be a bit of wait. Parking can be tricky but theres spots back of the restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOhZhnwczMR-KMwYPxw9fjlMAlg7XqN849JKnd&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-7-21"}]
